module.exports={"hyatt-zilara-cancun-vs-hyatt-zilara-riviera-maya":{"keyDifferences":"Both are adults-only, upper-upscale Hyatt Zilara properties in Mexico, but their ratings diverge meaningfully across several dimensions. Hyatt Zilara Cancun scores noticeably higher overall (9.4 vs 8.6), and the gap widens on beach (7.5 vs 5.5), pool (8.4 vs 7.1), and atmosphere (8.1 vs 7.5). Cancun also carries a heated pool and swim-up bar that Riviera Maya lacks entirely. Location scores favor Cancun (9.1 vs 8.5), reflecting its position on Cancun's Hotel Zone with easy access to the city, nightlife, and shopping. Riviera Maya sits in Solidaridad, closer to Playa del Carmen and the jungle interior, offering a quieter, more removed setting. Both score similarly on rooms (9.2 vs 9.1), cleanliness (9.4 vs 9.3), and service (9.4 vs 9.0), so the core hospitality experience is comparable. The decisive factors are Cancun's stronger beach, better pool setup with a swim-up bar, and more energetic location versus Riviera Maya's greater seclusion and slightly lower price-to-value proposition.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples or solo travelers who want a polished Cancun all-inclusive with a strong beach, heated pool, swim-up bar, and convenient access to Cancun's Hotel Zone restaurants, nightlife, and shopping at a premium but well-justified price point.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adults-only couples who prioritize a quieter, more secluded Riviera Maya setting away from Cancun's bustle, and who are willing to trade a weaker beach and fewer pool amenities for proximity to Playa del Carmen and the jungle-coastal atmosphere of Solidaridad.","whenToVisit":"Both properties benefit from the same broad peak season of December through April, when dry, sunny weather dominates the Yucatán Peninsula. Shoulder months of May and November offer lower rates with mostly good weather. Hurricane season runs June through October, with September carrying the highest risk at both locations. Cancun's Hotel Zone feels livelier during spring break in March, which may appeal to some and deter others.","activities":"At Cancun, diving is available on-site and the Hotel Zone puts guests within reach of Isla Mujeres day trips, water parks, and cenote excursions. At Riviera Maya, the proximity to Playa del Carmen opens up the Fifth Avenue dining and shopping scene, while Tulum ruins, cenote networks, and Xcaret eco-parks are all reachable within an hour. Both resorts offer spa services, evening entertainment, and gym facilities on property."},"hyatt-zilara-cancun-vs-hyatt-zilara-rose-hall":{"keyDifferences":"Both are adults-only Hyatt Zilara properties at the same price tier, but their ratings tell meaningfully different stories. Hyatt Zilara Cancun outscores Rose Hall across nearly every category: overall (9.4 vs 8.9), food (8.2 vs 7.8), pool (8.4 vs 7.4), atmosphere (8.1 vs 7.5), room (9.2 vs 8.8), and value (8.9 vs 8.5). The beach gap is the starkest difference — Cancun scores 7.5 versus Rose Hall's 5.8, reflecting the well-known contrast between Cancun's Hotel Zone beachfront and Rose Hall's narrower Jamaican shoreline. Cancun adds a heated pool and diving; Rose Hall counters with tennis and a nightclub. Cancun's location rating (9.1 vs 8.7) reflects its position on the Hotel Zone strip with easy access to Cancun's broader dining and nightlife scene. Rose Hall sits near Montego Bay with its own cultural draw, but guests consistently rate the overall experience lower. If you want the stronger beach, better pool, and higher-rated food and atmosphere, Cancun is the clear pick within the same brand and price bracket.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples or solo travelers who want a premium Cancun all-inclusive with a standout beach, heated pool, diving, and consistently top-rated service and rooms. Those who value strong food scores and a well-located base for exploring the Hotel Zone and beyond.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adults-only couples who specifically want a Jamaican all-inclusive experience near Montego Bay, with tennis, a nightclub, and the island's distinct culture and music scene as part of the draw — and who can accept a weaker beach and lower food scores relative to the Cancun sibling.","whenToVisit":"Cancun's peak season runs December through April when weather is driest and crowds are highest; May through November brings lower rates but hurricane risk. Rose Hall follows a similar Caribbean pattern — December through April is prime, while summer and early fall sit in Jamaica's wetter, quieter season. Both properties command premium rates over Christmas and spring break regardless of conditions.","activities":"Cancun guests can dive directly from the resort, swim in the heated pool, and access Cancun's Hotel Zone for additional dining, nightlife, and day trips to Isla Mujeres or Chichen Itza. Rose Hall guests can play tennis, use the nightclub on-site, and venture into Montego Bay for Bob Marley landmarks, Dunn's River Falls excursions, and the Hip Strip's bars and craft markets."},"hyatt-vivid-punta-cana-vs-hyatt-zilara-cancun":{"keyDifferences":"Hyatt Vivid Punta Cana and Hyatt Zilara Cancun are both adults-only, premium-priced Hyatt all-inclusives sharing identical location scores (9.1) and service ratings (9.4), but they diverge meaningfully on the amenities and experiences that define a resort stay. Vivid Punta Cana posts a higher overall score (9.8 vs. 9.4) and edges ahead on rooms (9.4 vs. 9.2), yet Zilara Cancun outperforms it in nearly every experiential category: food (8.2 vs. 7.4), beach (7.5 vs. 6.5), pool (8.4 vs. 6.9), atmosphere (8.1 vs. 7.2), and sleep quality (9.1 vs. 8.9). Zilara's confirmed amenity list includes a heated pool, diving, spa, swim-up bar, evening entertainment, and reservation-free restaurants, giving guests a clearer picture of what to expect. Vivid Punta Cana's lower food and pool scores suggest a property that impresses on cleanliness and rooms but hasn't yet matched Zilara's more rounded resort experience. Zilara Cancun is the stronger all-around performer; Vivid Punta Cana may suit guests prioritizing accommodation quality over resort programming.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults who want a pristine, room-forward adults-only all-inclusive in the Dominican Republic and are willing to trade a slightly weaker food and pool experience for an immaculate property with outstanding cleanliness (9.5) and room comfort (9.4) at a strong value score of 8.7.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adults seeking a well-rounded adults-only Mexican all-inclusive in Cancun where food (8.2), pool (8.4), and atmosphere (8.1) all score meaningfully higher, backed by confirmed amenities including a heated pool, spa, diving, swim-up bar, and evening entertainment for a complete resort experience.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations are warm year-round. Cancun's peak season runs December through April, with hurricane season peaking August through October; the sweet spot for Zilara is November or early December for lower crowds and good weather. Punta Cana shares a similar hurricane window, with January through March being the driest and most reliable months for Vivid. Both resorts carry premium pricing throughout high season.","activities":"At Zilara Cancun guests can dive, use the spa, work out in the gym, and enjoy swim-up bar and evening entertainment without leaving the property, with Cancun's Hotel Zone shopping, cenotes, and Mayan ruins accessible nearby. Vivid Punta Cana's on-site activity data is thinner, but the broader Punta Cana area offers snorkeling, catamaran excursions, zip-lining, and the natural pools of Saona Island within easy reach."},"hyatt-zilara-cancun-vs-hyatt-ziva-punta-cana":{"keyDifferences":"Hyatt Zilara Cancun is an adults-only Mexican all-inclusive on the Cancun Hotel Zone with a heated pool, spa, diving, swim-up bar, and evening entertainment, scoring notably higher on atmosphere (8.1 vs 7.6) and pool (8.4 vs 7.4). Hyatt Ziva Punta Cana is a family-oriented Dominican Republic all-inclusive with a kids club, teen club, yoga, tennis, and mini golf, pulling ahead on room quality (9.5 vs 9.2) and cleanliness (9.6 vs 9.4). Both share identical food scores (8.2) and location ratings (9.1), but Zilara's beach scores lower (7.5 vs 8.2), reflecting the narrower, more urban Cancun Hotel Zone shoreline versus Punta Cana's wider beach. Zilara delivers a livelier adults atmosphere with a spa and evening entertainment program; Ziva trades that in for family infrastructure and slightly superior accommodations. Both sit at the same price tier, making the adults-only versus family distinction the clearest deciding factor.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults and couples who want a polished, lively all-inclusive on the Cancun Hotel Zone with spa access, diving, a swim-up bar, and evening entertainment, and who prioritize atmosphere and pool experience over beach width.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families with children of all ages who want a clean, well-appointed Dominican Republic all-inclusive with outstanding rooms, a kids club, teen club, tennis, yoga, and mini golf on a strong Punta Cana beach.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations peak December through April when dry, sunny weather dominates and hurricane risk is low. Cancun's shoulder months of May and November offer good value before and after spring break crowds. Punta Cana's peak aligns similarly, though its eastern exposure makes it slightly more vulnerable to Atlantic weather in September and October. Either resort rewards an early December or late January booking for the best combination of weather, pricing, and availability.","activities":"At Zilara Cancun, guests can dive directly from the resort, use the spa, and access Cancun's Hotel Zone attractions, shopping, and nightlife nearby. At Ziva Punta Cana, the focus is on-property with tennis, yoga, mini golf, and dedicated kids and teen programming. Both resorts are near international airports. Neither property lists watersports beyond Zilara's diving, so guests wanting sailing or snorkelling excursions at either resort will need to book off-property tours."},"hyatt-zilara-cancun-vs-hyatt-ziva-barbados":{"keyDifferences":"Hyatt Zilara Cancun is an adults-only all-inclusive on Mexico's Hotel Zone with a heated pool, diving, spa, swim-up bar, and evening entertainment, earning a standout overall rating of 9.4 and a location score of 9.1 on one of the Caribbean's most accessible beach strips. Hyatt Ziva Barbados is a family all-inclusive in Barbados with strong room and cleanliness scores matching Zilara's (9.2 and 9.4 respectively), but trails meaningfully on food (6.0 vs 8.2), pool (7.4 vs 8.4), atmosphere (7.5 vs 8.1), and value (7.6 vs 8.9). Zilara Cancun is the stronger all-inclusive package by nearly every metric, particularly for couples prioritizing dining quality, pool experience, and overall value. Ziva Barbados competes on room comfort and cleanliness, and its beach score edges Zilara slightly (7.7 vs 7.5), but the food rating of 6.0 is a significant weakness. If you want a polished, high-value adults-only all-inclusive in Cancun with excellent dining and a full amenity set, go to Hyatt Zilara Cancun. If you want a family-friendly Hyatt property in Barbados where room quality and service are strong despite weaker dining, go to Hyatt Ziva Barbados.","whoShouldChooseA":"Couples and adult travelers who want a premium adults-only all-inclusive in Cancun with consistently high scores across food, pool, service, and value. The 9.4 overall rating and 8.2 food score make it the choice for guests who refuse to compromise on dining quality or atmosphere.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families drawn to Barbados who prioritize spotless rooms and attentive service over a standout dining or pool experience. Those for whom the island's distinct Caribbean character and slightly better beach score justify the weaker food rating and higher relative price-to-value gap.","whenToVisit":"Cancun's peak season runs December through April when weather is driest and demand highest; May through October brings lower rates but increased hurricane risk. Barbados sits slightly south of the main hurricane belt, making it a safer year-round destination, though its own peak season mirrors the Caribbean norm of mid-December through mid-April. Shoulder months of May and November offer better pricing at both properties.","activities":"Hyatt Zilara Cancun guests can dive the Mesoamerican Reef, explore Chichen Itza and Tulum on day trips, or shop and dine along Cancun's Hotel Zone. Hyatt Ziva Barbados puts guests near Harrison's Cave, the Barbados Wildlife Reserve, rum distillery tours at Mount Gay, and catamaran snorkeling excursions along the island's calm west coast. Both resorts offer on-site watersports, spa services, and pool programming."},"excellence-el-carmen-vs-finest-punta-cana":{"keyDifferences":"Excellence El Carmen and Finest Punta Cana are both Dominican Republic $$$$-tier all-inclusives with identical beach scores (6.5), location scores (8.8), and cleanliness scores (9.3), but they diverge sharply in concept and atmosphere. Excellence El Carmen is adults-only in the quieter Uvero Alto corridor, scoring higher on food (8.2 vs 7.8), pool (8.5 vs 8.2), atmosphere (8.3 vs 7.8), sleep quality (9.0 vs 8.6), and overall (9.3 vs 9.2). Finest Punta Cana is a family resort in the busier Punta Cana hub, compensating with a waterpark, kids club for under-4s, babysitting, pool slides, watersports rentals, yoga, room service, and rooms for five or more guests. Finest edges Excellence on room score (9.2 vs 9.1). The atmosphere gap of 0.5 and sleep quality gap of 0.4 likely reflect the difference between a serene adults-only environment and an active family resort. Both skip reservations for restaurants, making dining equally accessible. The choice is essentially adults-only tranquility versus family-forward infrastructure.","whoShouldChooseA":"Couples and adults who want a quieter, more refined Dominican Republic all-inclusive away from the Punta Cana strip. The higher atmosphere and sleep quality scores, adults-only policy, heated pool, and Uvero Alto location suit those prioritizing relaxation, romance, and consistently strong service without children present.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families with children of any age, including infants. The kids club for under-4s, waterpark, babysitting, pool slides, watersports rentals, yoga, and rooms that sleep five or more make Finest Punta Cana a genuinely comprehensive family operation in the familiar and well-connected Punta Cana area.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from the Dominican Republic's dry season, roughly December through April, when rainfall is lowest and trade winds keep temperatures comfortable. Peak Christmas and New Year weeks drive prices highest at both properties. Finest Punta Cana's family amenities make it especially popular during US and European school holidays, so couples considering it in the off-season shoulder months of May or November may find better value and fewer crowds.","activities":"Both resorts offer diving, snorkelling, swim-up bars, tennis, evening entertainment, spa services, and gym access. Finest Punta Cana adds watersports equipment rentals, yoga classes, a waterpark for young children, and pool slides. Beyond the resorts, Uvero Alto guests at Excellence can arrange excursions to Macao Beach and Hoyo Azul, while Finest's Punta Cana location gives easier access to Bavaro's shops, golf courses, and organized catamaran day trips."},"sandals-dunns-river-vs-sandals-saint-vincent":{"keyDifferences":"Sandals Dunn's River and Sandals Saint Vincent are both adults-only, premium-tier Caribbean all-inclusives that score nearly identically across most categories — overall 9.4 vs 9.3, rooms 9.5 vs 9.6, pools 8.5 vs 8.5, food 8.1 vs 8.2, and beaches a modest 6.8 vs 6.5. The meaningful gaps lie in guest type and destination character. Dunn's River admits all adults and adds a nightclub, making it more social and lively; Saint Vincent is couples-only and swaps the nightclub for diving, signaling a quieter, more intimate focus. Atmosphere favors Saint Vincent at 8.7 vs 8.4, suggesting couples find it more romantic, while service edges to Dunn's River at 9.5 vs 9.3. Dunn's River sits in well-trodden Ocho Rios with the famous waterfall nearby; Saint Vincent is a genuinely off-the-beaten-path Eastern Caribbean island with volcanic scenery and far fewer tourists. Value is marginally better at Dunn's River, 8.7 vs 8.5.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult groups or couples who want a lively Sandals property in Jamaica's Ocho Rios with a nightclub, evening entertainment, and easy access to Dunn's River Falls — and who prefer a more social, energetic all-inclusive atmosphere over seclusion.","whoShouldChooseB":"Committed couples who want an intimate, couples-only Sandals experience on an undiscovered Eastern Caribbean island, with diving on-site, a slightly more romantic atmosphere rating, and the novelty of Saint Vincent's volcanic landscape away from mainstream resort crowds.","whenToVisit":"Both islands peak December through April in dry season. Jamaica's Ocho Rios can see rain year-round but is generally reliable mid-December to mid-April. Saint Vincent sits just outside the main hurricane belt, making it slightly lower risk in the June–November shoulder season, though both properties are best visited in high season for optimal weather and beach conditions.","activities":"At Dunn's River, the iconic waterfall climb is steps from the resort, with Ocho Rios town, Mystic Mountain, and river tubing nearby. At Saint Vincent, diving is included on-site, and guests can explore the La Soufrière volcano, black-sand beaches, and the Grenadines by boat. Both resorts offer spa treatments, swim-up bars, and evening entertainment programs on property."},"sandals-dunns-river-vs-sandals-grenada":{"keyDifferences":"Sandals Dunn's River is an adults-only Jamaican all-inclusive in Ocho Rios, while Sandals Grenada is a couples-only property on Pink Gin Beach in Grenada — a meaningful policy distinction, as Dunn's River admits all adults whereas Grenada is restricted to couples. Dunn's River edges out on several key ratings: overall (9.4 vs 9.2), pool (8.5 vs 7.7), atmosphere (8.4 vs 8.1), room (9.5 vs 9.3), and cleanliness (9.7 vs 9.5). Both resorts score identically on food (8.1) and beach (6.8), suggesting neither beach is a standout strength. Dunn's River adds a nightclub for late-night entertainment, while Sandals Grenada counters with tennis and diving, making it stronger for active couples. Grenada's location benefits from a less-developed, quieter Caribbean island feel compared to the busier Ocho Rios corridor. If you want higher-rated rooms, a nightclub, and Ocho Rios's lively surroundings, Dunn's River wins. If you want diving, tennis, and a quieter, more remote Caribbean island experience as a couple, Grenada delivers.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult travellers — solo, friends, or couples — who want a high-rated Jamaican all-inclusive in Ocho Rios with a nightclub, strong room quality (9.5), and easy access to one of Jamaica's most iconic attractions, Dunn's River Falls, right on the doorstep.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples specifically seeking a quieter, more remote Caribbean escape with diving and tennis included, on a less-touristed island. Those who prioritise an intimate atmosphere over nightlife and don't mind slightly lower pool and atmosphere scores in exchange for Grenada's distinctive, unhurried character.","whenToVisit":"Both Jamaica and Grenada enjoy warm weather year-round. Jamaica's dry season runs December through April, with Ocho Rios prone to brief tropical showers in summer and autumn. Grenada sits south of the main hurricane belt, making it one of the Caribbean's safer bets during the August–October hurricane season, giving Sandals Grenada a meaningful edge for late-summer travel when Jamaica carries higher weather risk.","activities":"At Sandals Dunn's River, the legendary Dunn's River Falls climb is a short trip away, and Ocho Rios offers zip-lining, dolphin encounters, and Blue Hole excursions. At Sandals Grenada, on-site diving opens up colourful reefs and even a sunken ship, while tennis is available without leaving the resort. Grenada's spice markets, Grand Etang rainforest, and chocolate estate tours make for rich day-trip options on an island that rewards exploration beyond the beach."},"sandals-dunns-river-vs-sandals-south-coast":{"keyDifferences":"Sandals Dunn's River and Sandals South Coast are both adults-only Jamaican Sandals properties at the same price tier, but their ratings and guest profiles diverge in meaningful ways. Dunn's River scores higher across nearly every category: overall (9.4 vs 8.9), rooms (9.5 vs 8.8), pool (8.5 vs 7.7), atmosphere (8.4 vs 7.8), and value (8.7 vs 8.3). South Coast edges ahead only on beach (7.5 vs 6.8), sleep quality (9.3 vs 8.7), and offers paid Wi-Fi versus free at Dunn's River. South Coast is couples-only and adds diving and tennis to its amenity list, while Dunn's River is adults-only more broadly and includes free Wi-Fi. Dunn's River sits in Ocho Rios near the famous waterfall attraction, giving it a location score of 9.3 versus South Coast's 8.7 in the more remote White House area. If you want higher-rated rooms, pools, and atmosphere in a well-connected Ocho Rios location, choose Dunn's River. If you want a slightly better beach, scuba diving, and a more secluded couples-only setting on Jamaica's less-traveled south coast, choose South Coast.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult couples or groups of adults who want a highly rated Ocho Rios base with top-scoring rooms, a strong pool scene, free Wi-Fi, and easy access to Dunn's River Falls and other north coast attractions without a couples-only restriction.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples specifically who want a more secluded, quieter south coast setting with a better beach score, scuba diving, tennis, and higher sleep quality ratings, and who are comfortable with paid Wi-Fi and a more remote location.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Jamaica's dry season between December and April, when rainfall is lowest and beach conditions are best. South Coast's more remote location on Jamaica's south shore can see slightly different weather patterns than the north coast, occasionally benefiting from calmer seas. Both properties carry premium pricing during the Christmas and New Year period, so January through March offers the best combination of good weather and relative value.","activities":"Dunn's River guests can climb the iconic Dunn's River Falls minutes away, explore Ocho Rios town, take excursions to Mystic Mountain, or visit Bob Marley's Nine Mile birthplace. South Coast guests have on-site scuba diving and tennis, and can explore the Black River Safari, YS Falls, and Pelican Bar, a rustic offshore watering hole accessible only by boat and one of Jamaica's most memorable experiences."},"sandals-dunns-river-vs-sandals-grande-st-lucian":{"keyDifferences":"Sandals Dunn's River in Ocho Rios, Jamaica, and Sandals Grande St Lucian in Gros Islet, Saint Lucia, are both adults-only, premium Sandals properties at the same price tier, but they diverge meaningfully across several key ratings. Dunn's River scores higher overall (9.4 vs 9.0), with notably stronger room (9.5 vs 8.6), cleanliness (9.7 vs 9.1), service (9.5 vs 9.1), and location (9.3 vs 9.0) ratings. Grande St Lucian hits back hard on beach quality (8.3 vs 6.8), a significant gap that matters for beach-focused couples, and also edges ahead on sleep quality (8.9 vs 8.7). Grande St Lucian is couples-only, while Dunn's River admits all adults. On amenities, Grande St Lucian adds diving, snorkelling, tennis, and room service, making it the more activity-rich option. Dunn's River's pool rating (8.5 vs 7.4) and value score (8.7 vs 8.2) give it a clear edge there. Choose Dunn's River for immaculate rooms and standout service; choose Grande St Lucian for a superior beach and a broader watersports program.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples or friends who prioritize pristine rooms, exceptional service, and strong pool and value ratings over beach quality, and who want proximity to Ocho Rios landmarks like Dunn's River Falls. Not restricted to couples only.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples exclusively seeking a Saint Lucian setting with a significantly better beach (8.3 vs 6.8), plus diving, snorkelling, tennis, and room service rounding out a fuller activity roster, and who are comfortable trading slightly lower pool and room scores for those gains.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations share a similar Caribbean dry season from mid-December through April, when rainfall is lowest and conditions are most reliable. Jamaica's Ocho Rios and Saint Lucia's Gros Islet both see higher humidity and hurricane-season risk from July through October. Shoulder months of May and November can offer lower rates with generally acceptable weather at either property.","activities":"At Sandals Dunn's River, guests can visit the iconic Dunn's River Falls, explore Ocho Rios town, and enjoy the on-site spa, swim-up bar, and evening entertainment. At Sandals Grande St Lucian, on-site diving, snorkelling, and tennis expand the activity menu considerably, while the nearby Pigeon Island National Landmark, Rodney Bay marina, and Saint Lucia's volcanic landscapes offer compelling excursions beyond the resort gates."},"sandals-dunns-river-vs-sandals-royal-curacao":{"keyDifferences":"Sandals Dunn's River and Sandals Royal Curacao are both adults-only, couples-focused Sandals properties at the same price tier, but they diverge sharply on destination character and several key ratings. Dunn's River scores notably higher overall (9.4 vs 8.8), in room quality (9.5 vs 9.2), cleanliness (9.7 vs 9.4), service (9.5 vs 9.0), atmosphere (8.4 vs 8.1), and value (8.7 vs 8.3). The most dramatic gap is beach: Dunn's River rates 6.8 versus a very low 4.8 at Royal Curacao, making neither a standout beach resort but Curacao noticeably weaker. Royal Curacao adds diving and snorkelling to its amenity list, giving it an edge for underwater enthusiasts. Dunn's River sits in Ocho Rios with proximity to the famous Dunn's River Falls, while Royal Curacao offers a genuinely different Dutch-Caribbean island setting in Nieuwpoort. If room quality, service, and atmosphere scores matter most, Dunn's River leads across the board. If you want diving, snorkelling, and a less-visited Caribbean island experience, Curacao is the trade-off.","whoShouldChooseA":"Couples who prioritize exceptional service, immaculate rooms, and a lively Jamaican atmosphere in Ocho Rios. The proximity to Dunn's River Falls and strong ratings across nearly every category make this the better all-around Sandals choice for those who want a polished, high-performing Jamaica experience.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples who want to explore a distinctive Dutch-Caribbean island destination and have a strong interest in diving and snorkelling. Sandals Royal Curacao suits those drawn to Curacao's unique cultural character over conventional Caribbean resort settings, and who are willing to accept a weaker beach in exchange for underwater activities.","whenToVisit":"Jamaica's Ocho Rios is best visited December through April, when rainfall is lowest and trade winds keep temperatures comfortable; avoid September and October during peak hurricane season. Curacao sits outside the hurricane belt, making it a reliable year-round destination, though December through April still delivers the driest, sunniest conditions. Curacao's storm-free status gives it a timing advantage for travelers flexible outside peak Caribbean season.","activities":"At Dunn's River, the iconic waterfall climb is the unmissable excursion, complemented by zip-lining, river tubing, and Mystic Mountain nearby. Sandals Royal Curacao unlocks the island's exceptional dive sites and snorkel reefs, with Willemstad's UNESCO-listed historic waterfront a short trip away for colorful Dutch colonial architecture, local restaurants, and the famous floating market. Both resorts offer on-site spa, gym, nightclub, and evening entertainment programs."},"sandals-dunns-river-vs-sandals-halcyon-beach":{"keyDifferences":"Sandals Dunn's River is an adults-only Jamaican all-inclusive in Ocho Rios with a beach, gym, spa, swim-up bar, nightclub, and evening entertainment, posting a standout overall rating of 9.4 and exceptional scores for rooms (9.5), cleanliness (9.7), and service (9.5). Sandals Halcyon Beach is a couples-only Saint Lucia all-inclusive near Castries with a broader activity set including diving, tennis, and fishing, but trails Dunn's River across nearly every rating category: overall (9.0 vs 9.4), atmosphere (7.7 vs 8.4), pool (6.9 vs 8.5), and rooms (8.4 vs 9.5). Dunn's River also edges Halcyon on food (8.1 vs 7.8), beach (6.8 vs 6.5), and value (8.7 vs 8.3). One practical difference: Wi-Fi is free at Dunn's River and paid at Halcyon. If you want the higher-rated, more polished adults-only experience with stronger rooms and atmosphere, go to Sandals Dunn's River. If you want a couples-only Saint Lucia setting with diving, tennis, and fishing, go to Sandals Halcyon Beach.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult couples or friends who want a high-performing Jamaican all-inclusive in Ocho Rios with exceptional rooms, service, and cleanliness, a lively nightclub and swim-up bar, and convenient access to Dunn's River Falls without paying extra for Wi-Fi.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples specifically seeking a quieter, activity-rich Saint Lucia setting with diving, tennis, and fishing on offer, and who are comfortable with a slightly lower overall polish and a paid Wi-Fi policy in exchange for the lush Castries backdrop.","whenToVisit":"Both Jamaica and Saint Lucia follow similar Caribbean patterns: peak season runs December through April when rainfall is lowest and temperatures are most comfortable. Jamaica's Ocho Rios can see heavier rain from September to November, while Saint Lucia's wet season peaks between June and November. For either resort, January through March offers the most reliable dry-weather conditions and the highest demand, so book well in advance.","activities":"Guests at Sandals Dunn's River are within easy reach of the famous Dunn's River Falls, Mystic Mountain, and Ocho Rios town. At Halcyon Beach, diving is included on-site, and Castries offers local markets, historical sites, and access to Saint Lucia's volcanic landscape and botanical gardens. Both resorts offer beach access, swim-up bars, spas, nightclubs, and evening entertainment, while Halcyon adds tennis and fishing to the mix."},"sandals-dunns-river-vs-sandals-montego-bay":{"keyDifferences":"Sandals Dunn's River and Sandals Montego Bay are both adults-only Jamaican all-inclusives in the same brand family, but they differ meaningfully in guest policy, ratings, and setting. Dunn's River accepts all adults, while Montego Bay is strictly couples-only. Dunn's River outscores Montego Bay across nearly every rating category: overall (9.4 vs 8.7), atmosphere (8.4 vs 7.7), room (9.5 vs 8.6), pool (8.5 vs 6.9), cleanliness (9.7 vs 9.0), service (9.5 vs 9.0), and value (8.7 vs 8.3). The beach scores are identical at 6.8. Montego Bay adds tennis and diving that Dunn's River lacks, and its location near Sangster International airport is a practical advantage for short-haul travelers, though it scores lower on location overall (8.5 vs 9.3). Dunn's River sits closer to its famous namesake waterfall attraction in Ocho Rios, which anchors a stronger location score. If ratings and room quality are the priority, Dunn's River leads decisively. If diving, tennis, or a quick airport transfer matter more than overall scores, Montego Bay remains a solid couples option.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult couples or friend groups who want the highest-rated Sandals experience in Jamaica, with superior room quality, atmosphere, and cleanliness scores, and easy access to Dunn's River Falls and the Ocho Rios area without the couples-only restriction.","whoShouldChooseB":"Strictly couples who want diving and tennis included in their Sandals stay, or those flying into Sangster International who prefer a shorter transfer time and don't mind trading some atmosphere and pool quality for added watersport amenities.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Jamaica's dry season, mid-December through April, when humidity drops and rainfall is minimal. Montego Bay's proximity to the airport makes it marginally easier to reach during peak holiday travel. Summer visits are possible but expect afternoon showers at both properties, with Ocho Rios typically receiving slightly more rainfall than the northwest coast.","activities":"At Dunn's River, the iconic waterfall climb is minutes away, and Ocho Rios offers dolphin encounters, river tubing, and Blue Hole excursions. At Montego Bay, Rose Hall Great House, ATV tours, and Rocklands Bird Sanctuary are nearby. Both resorts provide spa treatments, swim-up bars, and evening entertainment on site, while Montego Bay adds certified diving and tennis courts."},"sandals-dunns-river-vs-sandals-negril":{"keyDifferences":"Sandals Dunn's River in Ocho Rios and Sandals Negril in Negril are both adults-only Jamaican Sandals properties at the same price tier, but they diverge sharply on beach versus room quality and who they admit. Dunn's River scores a notably higher room rating (9.5 vs 8.6) and overall score (9.4 vs 8.9), with standout cleanliness (9.7 vs 9.1) and service (9.5 vs 9.1), but its beach rating is a weak 6.8 compared to Negril's exceptional 9.5. Negril's Seven Mile Beach is one of the Caribbean's finest stretches of sand and that shows clearly in the numbers. Negril also adds diving and snorkelling, while Dunn's River compensates with a higher atmosphere score (8.4 vs 7.8) and proximity to Dunn's River Falls. Negril is couples-only, narrowing its appeal further, while Dunn's River welcomes all adults. If top-rated rooms, service, and lively atmosphere matter more than beach quality, Dunn's River wins. If the beach is the whole point of the trip, Negril is the clear choice.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult travellers, including friends or solo guests, who prioritise exceptional rooms, service, and cleanliness over beach quality, and want easy access to Ocho Rios attractions like Dunn's River Falls with a livelier on-resort atmosphere.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples only who want one of Jamaica's best beaches as the centrepiece of their holiday, with diving and snorkelling available alongside the classic Negril Seven Mile Beach sunset experience, and who are willing to accept a more modest pool and room rating.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Jamaica's dry season, mid-December through April, when rainfall is lowest and trade winds keep temperatures comfortable. Negril's exposed western coast can see stronger winds in winter, which may affect watersports. The shoulder months of May and November offer lower rates at both properties with generally manageable weather.","activities":"Near Dunn's River, guests can visit the famous eponymous waterfall climb, explore Mystic Mountain, or take river tubing excursions in Ocho Rios. At Negril, the resort's own diving and snorkelling program covers nearby reefs, and guests can visit Rick's Cafe for cliff diving at sunset. Both properties offer spa treatments, evening entertainment, and nightclub access on-site."},"sandals-dunns-river-vs-sandals-regency-la-toc":{"keyDifferences":"Sandals Dunn's River is an adults-only Jamaica all-inclusive in Ocho Rios with a beach, swim-up bar, spa, nightclub, and evening entertainment, posting standout scores in overall satisfaction (9.4), rooms (9.5), cleanliness (9.7), and service (9.5). Sandals Regency La Toc is a couples-only Saint Lucia all-inclusive near Castries with diving, snorkelling, golf, tennis, spa, and a nightclub, scoring meaningfully lower across most categories: overall (8.8), food (7.8 vs 8.1), beach (5.8 vs 6.8), pool (6.9 vs 8.5), and atmosphere (7.7 vs 8.4). Dunn's River edges La Toc on nearly every metric and is open to all adults, while La Toc restricts to couples only and compensates with a broader activity roster including golf and diving. If you want a top-rated adults Jamaica all-inclusive with exceptional rooms and service in Ocho Rios, go to Sandals Dunn's River. If you want a couples-only Saint Lucia all-inclusive with golf, diving, and snorkelling despite weaker pool and beach scores, go to Sandals Regency La Toc.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults travelling solo, with friends, or as couples who want a high-performing Jamaica all-inclusive in Ocho Rios with exceptional rooms, service, and cleanliness scores, a swim-up bar, and a lively evening entertainment program without a couples-only restriction.","whoShouldChooseB":"Committed couples who want a Saint Lucia all-inclusive with a golf course, diving, and snorkelling built into the package, and who are comfortable trading lower pool and beach scores for a more activity-rich Caribbean island setting near Castries.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts sit in the Caribbean's dry season window of December through April, which offers the most reliable sunshine and lowest humidity. Jamaica's Ocho Rios and Saint Lucia's Castries share similar hurricane-season risk from June through November, with September and October the most active months. Shoulder months of May and November offer reduced rates with generally acceptable weather at both properties.","activities":"At Sandals Dunn's River, guests are minutes from the famous Dunn's River Falls climb, Mystic Mountain, and Ocho Rios town. At Sandals Regency La Toc, on-site golf, diving, and snorkelling are the draws, with Castries market, the Pitons, and sulphur springs accessible nearby. Both resorts offer spa treatments, evening entertainment, and nightclub access on property."},"beaches-negril-vs-sandals-dunns-river":{"keyDifferences":"Beaches Negril is a large family all-inclusive on Jamaica's famous Seven Mile Beach in Negril, loaded with a waterpark for big and little kids, lazy river, kids club for under-4s, babysitting, diving, snorkelling, fishing, and rooms accommodating 5 or more guests. Sandals Dunn's River is an adults-only all-inclusive in Ocho Rios, near the famous waterfall attraction, with a dramatically stronger showing in rooms (9.5 vs 8.5), cleanliness (9.7 vs 9.0), service (9.5 vs 9.1), and overall score (9.4 vs 8.9). Beaches Negril holds a commanding beach edge (9.5 vs 6.8) owing to its Seven Mile Beach frontage, while Sandals Dunn's River counters with better pools (8.5 vs 7.4) and atmosphere (8.4 vs 7.8). Beaches Negril wins on sheer family infrastructure; Sandals Dunn's River wins on refinement, room quality, and a couples-focused ambience. Both sit at the same price tier, so the choice is essentially family chaos versus polished adult retreat.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a sprawling Negril all-inclusive with a waterpark, lazy river, dedicated kids club for toddlers, babysitting, diving, and one of the Caribbean's best beaches on their doorstep.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples and honeymooners who want a polished, high-scoring Jamaican all-inclusive near Ocho Rios with outstanding rooms, impeccable cleanliness, strong service ratings, and a refined atmosphere without children.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Jamaica's dry season, roughly mid-December through April, when rainfall is lowest and trade winds keep temperatures comfortable. Negril can be slightly windier in winter, which suits watersports. Ocho Rios sits on Jamaica's north coast and tends to see more localised afternoon showers year-round, though shoulder months of May and November offer quieter crowds and lower rates at both properties.","activities":"Beaches Negril guests can dive, snorkel, fish, use the waterpark, and explore Negril's cliffs and Rick's Cafe nearby. Sandals Dunn's River guests can visit the iconic Dunn's River Falls a short drive away, explore Ocho Rios town, and take excursions to Mystic Mountain or Green Grotto Caves. Both resorts offer evening entertainment and nightclub facilities on-site."},"sandals-dunns-river-vs-sandals-royal-caribbean":{"keyDifferences":"Sandals Dunn's River and Sandals Royal Caribbean are both adults-only Jamaican Sandals properties at the same price tier, but they differ meaningfully across nearly every rating category. Dunn's River leads in overall score by 0.8 points (9.4 vs 8.6), with particularly striking gaps in room quality (9.5 vs 8.6), atmosphere (8.4 vs 7.7), and pool (8.5 vs 7.1). Cleanliness and service are strong at both, though Dunn's River edges ahead on cleanliness (9.7 vs 9.1). Royal Caribbean holds a slight advantage in sleep quality (8.8 vs 8.7) and adds more activities — diving, snorkelling, fishing, tennis, room service, and a lazy river — that Dunn's River lacks. Beach scores are modest at both resorts (6.8 vs 6.3), so neither should be chosen primarily for beach quality. Royal Caribbean is couples-only and sits in Montego Bay near the airport, while Dunn's River is near the iconic Dunn's River Falls in Ocho Rios and allows any adult configuration. For raw resort quality and atmosphere, Dunn's River rates higher; for activity variety and airport convenience, Royal Caribbean has the edge.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult friends, solo travelers, or couples who prioritize room quality, atmosphere, and overall resort experience above activity breadth. The Ocho Rios location puts Dunn's River Falls and other north-coast attractions within easy reach, making it the stronger base for guests who want to explore Jamaica.","whoShouldChooseB":"Committed couples who want the widest activity menu — diving, snorkelling, fishing, tennis, a lazy river — and the convenience of a short Montego Bay airport transfer. Those who value room service and a fuller amenity list over top-tier atmosphere ratings will find Royal Caribbean the better fit.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Jamaica's dry season, mid-December through April, when rainfall is lowest and trade winds keep temperatures comfortable. Montego Bay at Royal Caribbean tends to be slightly drier than Ocho Rios. Hurricane season runs June through November; September and October carry the highest risk at both locations. Shoulder months of May and early December offer lower rates with generally acceptable weather.","activities":"Dunn's River guests can combine the resort's swim-up bar, spa, and evening entertainment with off-site excursions to the famous Dunn's River Falls, Mystic Mountain, and Blue Hole, all close to Ocho Rios. Royal Caribbean guests can pursue on-site diving, snorkelling, fishing, tennis, and the lazy river, and explore Montego Bay's Hip Strip, Pelican Bar, and Rose Hall Great House nearby."},"beaches-turks-and-caicos-vs-sandals-dunns-river":{"keyDifferences":"Beaches Turks & Caicos is a large, family-focused all-inclusive on Providenciales with a near-perfect pool rating of 9.8 and beach rating of 9.6, anchored by a waterpark, FlowRider, lazy river, and one of the Caribbean's most celebrated stretches of sand. Sandals Dunn's River is an adults-only Jamaican all-inclusive in Ocho Rios where the standout numbers are rooms (9.5), service (9.5), cleanliness (9.7), and value (8.7) — but the beach scores just 6.8, reflecting the more limited shoreline typical of that coastline. Beaches wins decisively on beach and pool infrastructure; Sandals wins on room quality, service polish, cleanliness, and value. Beaches carries a lower value score (7.9 vs. 8.7), which reflects its premium pricing for its sprawling family amenity set. Atmosphere is closer than expected (8.1 vs. 8.4), though the contexts are entirely different — one is a lively family resort, the other a couples retreat. If beach and water-activity breadth matter most, Beaches is the clear choice; if room quality, service, and value define the trip, Sandals Dunn's River delivers more per dollar.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of any age who want the Caribbean's most complete waterpark-and-beach combination, with kids clubs from infants upward, a FlowRider, lazy river, diving, and rooms that sleep five or more — all on one of the finest beaches in the region.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples who prioritize immaculate rooms, exceptional service, and strong value over beach quality, and who want a well-located Ocho Rios base near Dunn's River Falls with a nightclub and a notably high cleanliness standard throughout the property.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations peak December through April when rainfall and hurricane risk are lowest. Turks and Caicos runs slightly drier year-round and avoids Jamaica's wetter May–November shoulder. Sandals Dunn's River sits on Jamaica's north coast, which sees less rainfall than the south but remains more weather-exposed than Providenciales in summer and early fall. Both resorts command highest rates over the Christmas–New Year and Presidents' Day windows.","activities":"Beaches Turks & Caicos guests have diving, snorkelling, tennis, and a full waterpark on-site, plus access to Grace Bay's calm turquoise flats. Sandals Dunn's River guests are steps from the famous Dunn's River Falls climb, with Mystic Mountain, ATV excursions, and Ocho Rios town nearby. On-site, Sandals offers a swim-up bar, spa, gym, and evening entertainment, though the activity roster is considerably leaner than Beaches."},"sandals-dunns-river-vs-sandals-ochi-beach-resort":{"keyDifferences":"Both are adults-only Sandals properties in Ocho Rios at the same price tier, but their ratings diverge sharply across nearly every category. Sandals Dunn's River leads in overall score (9.4 vs 8.5), rooms (9.5 vs 8.4), cleanliness (9.7 vs 8.7), service (9.5 vs 8.6), atmosphere (8.4 vs 7.1), pool (8.5 vs 6.5), and beach (6.8 vs 4.5). The beach gap is particularly stark — neither property is a standout beach resort, but Dunn's River's 6.8 is meaningfully better than Ochi's 4.5. Dunn's River also adds a nightclub and evening entertainment that Ochi lacks. Sandals Ochi enforces a couples-only policy, making it the stricter romantic retreat of the two, while Dunn's River welcomes any adult pairing. For the same nightly rate, Dunn's River delivers higher guest satisfaction across the board. The only area where Ochi closes the gap is value (8.2 vs 8.7), suggesting Dunn's River guests feel they get more for their money.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults — couples, friends, or solo travelers — who want the best overall Sandals experience in Ocho Rios. Dunn's River suits guests who prioritize spotless rooms, attentive service, a nightclub, and evening entertainment, and who want a notably better beach and pool experience than Ochi offers.","whoShouldChooseB":"Committed couples who specifically want a couples-only environment and are willing to accept lower scores on beach, pool, and atmosphere in exchange for that stricter romantic exclusivity. Best suited to guests for whom the couples-only policy itself is the primary draw.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts sit in Ocho Rios, so timing applies equally. Jamaica's dry season runs mid-December through April, offering the most reliable sunshine and lowest humidity — peak pricing applies. May through June and November offer a shoulder-season sweet spot with fewer crowds and better rates before and after the main hurricane season months of August through October.","activities":"Ocho Rios is one of Jamaica's most activity-rich destinations. Dunn's River Falls — one of the Caribbean's most famous natural landmarks — is minutes from both resorts. Guests can also explore Bob Marley's birthplace in Nine Mile, go river tubing on the White River, take ATV excursions into the hills, snorkel or dive offshore reefs, or visit Mystic Mountain for zip-lining and a bobsled ride through rainforest canopy."},"sandals-dunns-river-vs-sandals-grande-antigua-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Sandals Dunn's River in Ocho Rios, Jamaica and Sandals Grande Antigua in St. John's, Antigua are both adults-only, premium-priced Sandals properties, but they diverge sharply across several key metrics. Dunn's River leads on overall rating (9.4 vs 8.5), rooms (9.5 vs 8.5), cleanliness (9.7 vs 8.9), service (9.5 vs 8.6), and atmosphere (8.4 vs 7.7), suggesting a tighter, more polished operation. Grande Antigua flips the script on beach (8.5 vs a notably weak 6.8) and matches Dunn's River on sleep quality (8.7). Dunn's River's pool scores higher (8.5 vs 6.9), while Grande Antigua adds diving, tennis, and fishing that Dunn's River lacks. Grande Antigua also charges for Wi-Fi, where Dunn's River includes it. Dunn's River skews toward couples and solo adults; Grande Antigua is formally couples-only. If pristine rooms, exceptional service, and a lively Jamaican atmosphere matter more than beach quality, Dunn's River wins. If a genuinely excellent beach and watersport variety in Antigua are the priority, Grande Antigua is the stronger call.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults and couples who prioritize impeccable rooms, top-tier service, and a polished resort experience in Jamaica and can overlook a beach that scores below average. Proximity to Dunn's River Falls and Ocho Rios gives the location strong sightseeing appeal for guests who want to explore beyond the property.","whoShouldChooseB":"Committed couples who want a formally couples-only Sandals experience anchored by one of the Caribbean's better resort beaches, with added activities like diving, tennis, and fishing. Guests who spend more time in the water or on the sand than in the pool or the rooms will find Grande Antigua the more rewarding choice.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations peak from December through April when rainfall is lowest and trade winds moderate heat. Jamaica's Ocho Rios can see heavier rain from September to November, while Antigua's drier climate gives it a slight edge for shoulder-season travel in May and November. Either property is best booked well in advance for the Christmas and New Year window when rates and occupancy peak across the Caribbean.","activities":"Dunn's River guests can climb the iconic Dunn's River Falls minutes from the resort, explore Ocho Rios town, or take boat tours along Jamaica's north coast. Grande Antigua guests can dive the island's reef systems, fish offshore, play tennis on resort courts, and day-trip to Nelson's Dockyard or Antigua's 365 beaches. Both resorts offer spa treatments, evening entertainment, and nightclub access on property."},"sandals-dunns-river-vs-sandals-royal-bahamian":{"keyDifferences":"Sandals Dunn's River in Ocho Rios and Sandals Royal Bahamian in Nassau are both adults-only Sandals properties at the same price tier, but their ratings and amenity sets diverge meaningfully. Dunn's River leads on nearly every metric: overall (9.4 vs 8.2), food (8.1 vs 7.7), pool (8.5 vs 8.1), atmosphere (8.4 vs 7.5), room (9.5 vs 8.4), value (8.7 vs 7.7), cleanliness (9.7 vs 8.9), and service (9.5 vs 8.6). Royal Bahamian edges ahead only on beach (7.8 vs 6.8) and sleep quality (8.9 vs 8.7). Dunn's River carries a substantially richer amenity package — gym, swim-up bar, spa, buffet, evening entertainment, and a nightclub — while Royal Bahamian lists only beach access. Dunn's River also restricts to couples only, whereas Royal Bahamian welcomes all adults. For the money, Dunn's River delivers more on almost every measurable dimension; Royal Bahamian's appeal rests primarily on its Bahamian setting, slightly better beach scores, and a quieter, more couples-focused atmosphere.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults who want a high-performing Sandals property with a full amenity stack — swim-up bar, spa, nightclub, evening entertainment — and don't mind a modest beach score. The location rating of 9.3 reflects easy access to Dunn's River Falls and Ocho Rios, making it ideal for guests who plan to explore Jamaica beyond the resort.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples who prioritize a Nassau address, a marginally better beach, and quieter nights over a packed activity schedule. Those drawn to the Bahamas specifically — for day trips to Atlantis, local dining, or island-hopping — and willing to accept lower food and value scores for that setting will find Royal Bahamian fits the bill.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations peak December through April when Caribbean weather is driest and most settled. Jamaica's Ocho Rios can see brief rain year-round but remains pleasant outside hurricane season (June–November). Nassau follows a similar pattern, with summer months bringing heat and humidity. For the best rates at either property, shoulder months like May or November offer lower prices before or just after peak season.","activities":"At Sandals Dunn's River, the iconic Dunn's River Falls climbing excursion is minutes away, with Ocho Rios offering snorkelling, river tubing, and ATV tours. On-site, the spa, nightclub, and swim-up bar keep guests busy without leaving. At Royal Bahamian, Nassau provides access to Atlantis Paradise Island, cable beach, local straw markets, and casino gaming, complementing the resort's quieter on-property beach experience."},"sandals-barbados-vs-sandals-dunns-river":{"keyDifferences":"Sandals Barbados sits in the lively St. Lawrence Gap on Barbados's south coast, while Sandals Dunn's River is positioned near Ocho Rios in Jamaica, close to one of the Caribbean's most visited natural attractions. On nearly every rated dimension, Dunn's River pulls ahead: overall rating 9.4 versus 8.4, rooms 9.5 versus 8.7, service 9.5 versus 8.7, cleanliness 9.7 versus 9.0, pool 8.5 versus 7.4, and value 8.7 versus 7.8. Barbados edges out on location perception at 8.7 versus 9.3 — though Dunn's River actually scores higher there too — and both share strong sleep quality scores. The beach ratings are similarly modest at both properties, 7.0 and 6.8 respectively, so neither should be chosen primarily for beachfront quality. Barbados offers a distinct island experience with a more English-Caribbean cultural flavour, while Dunn's River benefits from a recently renovated or high-performing product that clearly resonates with guests. If price and island variety matter, Barbados has its own appeal, but the ratings gap is substantial and difficult to ignore.","whoShouldChooseA":"Couples who specifically want to experience Barbados — its distinct culture, south coast dining strip, and English-Caribbean character — and are less focused on maximising resort quality metrics. A good fit for those with a Barbados bucket-list motivation rather than a purely resort-driven trip.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples who want the strongest all-around Sandals product available, with top-tier room quality, service, and cleanliness scores, plus easy access to Dunn's River Falls and the broader Ocho Rios area. Ideal for those prioritising resort experience over island destination choice.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations share a similar Caribbean dry season from December through April, making that window the safest bet for settled weather. Barbados sits slightly outside the main hurricane belt, giving it a mild advantage during the June-to-November shoulder season. Jamaica carries somewhat more hurricane exposure, so visiting Sandals Dunn's River between December and April is the stronger call for weather certainty.","activities":"Sandals Dunn's River guests have direct access to the iconic Dunn's River Falls climb, Mystic Mountain, and Ocho Rios's craft markets and river tubing. Both resorts offer beach and watersports access. Dunn's River features a swim-up bar, spa, gym, buffet, evening entertainment, and a nightclub on property. Sandals Barbados guests can explore St. Lawrence Gap's restaurant and bar scene steps from the resort, along with south coast water sports and Bridgetown's historic Garrison area."},"sandals-dunns-river-vs-sandals-royal-barbados":{"keyDifferences":"Sandals Dunn's River and Sandals Royal Barbados share the same price tier and nearly identical beach scores (both 6.8), but diverge sharply across most other metrics. Dunn's River leads overall (9.4 vs 8.1), on room quality (9.5 vs 8.9), service (9.5 vs 8.5), cleanliness (9.7 vs 9.0), value (8.7 vs 7.5), atmosphere (8.4 vs 7.8), and pool (8.5 vs 7.6). Royal Barbados edges ahead only on sleep quality (9.0 vs 8.7). Dunn's River sits in Ocho Rios, steps from the famous waterfall climb, with a nightclub, buffet, and an entertainment-forward program. Royal Barbados is couples-only — no singles or groups — in a quieter Oistins setting with a more restrained, refined tone. If the ratings are the guide, Dunn's River simply outperforms Royal Barbados in nearly every category at the same price point, making it the stronger all-around pick unless a Barbados location or the strict couples-only policy is a specific draw.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult couples or groups of friends who want a high-performing Jamaican all-inclusive near Ocho Rios with outstanding service, immaculate rooms, a nightclub, and easy access to Dunn's River Falls — and who want strong value at the luxury price point.","whoShouldChooseB":"Committed couples — and only couples — who specifically want a Barbados base in the laid-back Oistins area, prioritize peaceful sleep and refined atmosphere over lively entertainment, and are comfortable trading some value for a quieter, more intimate Caribbean setting.","whenToVisit":"Jamaica's Ocho Rios is driest December through April, with hurricane risk peaking August through October. Barbados sits south of the main hurricane belt, making Royal Barbados a more weather-reliable year-round option. Both properties carry peak-season pricing from mid-December through mid-April, with shoulder savings available May through July before the Atlantic storm season intensifies.","activities":"Dunn's River guests can climb the resort's namesake waterfall, snorkel, and explore Ocho Rios's craft markets and Mystic Mountain. Royal Barbados guests are well-placed for the Oistins Friday Night Fish Fry, Harrison's Cave, and coastal cycling along the south shore. Both resorts offer on-property watersports and spa services typical of the Sandals brand."},"beaches-barbados-vs-sandals-dunns-river":{"keyDifferences":"Beaches Barbados is a family all-inclusive on the western coast of Barbados with dedicated kids clubs for toddlers and older children, strong room (9.1), service (9.1), and cleanliness (9.1) scores, but a notably weak food rating (6.0) that stands out as a liability. Sandals Dunn's River is an adults-only luxury all-inclusive in Ocho Rios, Jamaica, with a swim-up bar, spa, nightclub, gym, and evening entertainment, posting stronger scores across food (8.1 vs 6.0), pool (8.5 vs 7.4), atmosphere (8.4 vs 7.5), and an exceptional overall rating of 9.4. Beaches Barbados wins on location (8.1 vs 9.3 goes to Sandals) and suits families traveling with very young children, while Sandals Dunn's River is the clear choice for couples prioritizing dining quality, resort amenities, and a polished adults-only atmosphere. The food gap alone — 2.1 rating points — is the single most decisive differentiator between these two properties.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with toddlers and young children who want a dedicated Barbados base with strong service and clean, comfortable rooms. The Barbados location suits those who want a quieter, less party-driven island, and the under-4 kids club makes it genuinely practical for parents of very young children.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples seeking a premium adults-only Jamaican all-inclusive with serious dining, a spa, swim-up bar, and nightclub. Sandals Dunn's River's near-perfect cleanliness (9.7) and service (9.5) scores, combined with strong value (8.7) at a luxury price point, make it ideal for honeymoons or romantic getaways near Ocho Rios.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations share a Caribbean dry season from December through April, making that window the safest bet for either resort. Barbados sits south of the main hurricane belt, giving Beaches Barbados a slight edge in shoulder-season reliability from June through August. Jamaica's hurricane season peaks in August and September, so Sandals Dunn's River is best avoided then unless rates justify the weather risk.","activities":"Beaches Barbados guests can explore Barbados's calm west-coast waters, visit Bridgetown's UNESCO-listed historic district, or take catamaran cruises to swim with sea turtles. Sandals Dunn's River guests have the famous Dunn's River Falls practically on their doorstep, along with Mystic Mountain, ATV excursions, and the broader Ocho Rios town for local market browsing and river tubing day trips."},"beaches-exuma-vs-sandals-dunns-river":{"keyDifferences":"Beaches Exuma is a family all-inclusive on Great Exuma in the Bahamas, a quieter, more remote island destination with a kids club for toddlers and older children, exceptional rooms and sleep quality (both 9.2 and 9.0), and a standout beach rating of 9.0 — but it trails significantly on food (6.4) and pool (6.9). Sandals Dunn's River is an adults-only all-inclusive near Ocho Rios, Jamaica, with a swim-up bar, spa, nightclub, gym, and buffet, earning strong marks across nearly every category: food 8.1 versus 6.4, pool 8.5 versus 6.9, and an overall rating of 9.4. The beach at Beaches Exuma (9.0) clearly outperforms Sandals Dunn's River (6.8), making the Bahamas property the better choice purely for beach time. Sandals wins on food, pool, atmosphere, and value (8.7 versus 7.4). If you want a remote Bahamian family escape with a spectacular beach and excellent rooms, choose Beaches Exuma. If you want a polished adults-only Jamaican resort with strong food, nightlife, and amenities, choose Sandals Dunn's River.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children who want a quiet, remote Bahamian all-inclusive where the beach and rooms are the main draw. Those willing to accept more limited food and pool options in exchange for the natural beauty and uncrowded setting of Great Exuma.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and adults who want a high-rated, amenity-rich Jamaican all-inclusive near Ocho Rios with strong food (8.1), a swim-up bar, spa, nightclub, and consistently excellent service and cleanliness scores. Not suitable for families with children.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations are best visited between December and April, when Caribbean weather is driest and most stable. Great Exuma can feel especially remote and slow outside peak season, so timing matters more there. Ocho Rios has more consistent infrastructure year-round. Both locations carry hurricane risk from June through November, with September being the peak of the season.","activities":"At Beaches Exuma, the calm turquoise waters of the Exuma cays invite snorkelling, swimming with nurse sharks, and visiting the famous swimming pigs — experiences unique to this part of the Bahamas. At Sandals Dunn's River, guests can visit the iconic Dunn's River Falls a short distance away, explore Ocho Rios town, and take advantage of on-site watersports, spa treatments, and evening entertainment within the resort."},"finest-playa-mujeres-vs-finest-punta-cana":{"keyDifferences":"Both Finest properties are premium family all-inclusives at the same price tier with nearly identical room scores (9.3 vs 9.2) and strong service ratings, but meaningful gaps emerge in beach, atmosphere, and a few key amenities. Finest Playa Mujeres edges ahead on beach (7.5 vs 6.5), atmosphere (8.1 vs 7.8), food (8.1 vs 7.8), and sleep quality (9.1 vs 8.6), suggesting a quieter, more polished environment on Mexico's less-trafficked Playa Mujeres peninsula. Finest Punta Cana counters with diving, snorkelling, watersports rentals, yoga, and rooms accommodating five or more guests — making it the stronger pick for larger families or active watersports households. Playa Mujeres adds a heated pool and nightclub not found at Punta Cana. Location scores favour Playa Mujeres (9.1 vs 8.8), reflecting its secluded positioning away from busy resort corridors. If you want a slightly more refined Mexican all-inclusive with better beach scores, a nightclub, and heated pool, choose Playa Mujeres. If you want a Dominican family all-inclusive with diving, snorkelling, yoga, and space for larger family groups, choose Punta Cana.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families and couples who want a premium, quieter Mexican all-inclusive on a less crowded peninsula, with a heated pool, nightclub, and consistently higher scores across beach, atmosphere, food, and sleep quality.","whoShouldChooseB":"Larger families of five or more, or active families who want diving, snorkelling, and watersports rentals built into their Dominican all-inclusive stay alongside strong kids programming and babysitting.","whenToVisit":"Finest Playa Mujeres is best visited November through April, when Mexico's Yucatán coast avoids hurricane season and humidity is manageable. Finest Punta Cana suits the same November–April window for the Dominican Republic. Both resorts sit in the Caribbean hurricane belt, so summer and early-fall travel carries weather risk at either property.","activities":"At Finest Playa Mujeres, guests can explore the nearby Isla Mujeres by ferry, visit Cancún's lagoon zone, or snorkel the Mesoamerican Reef. At Finest Punta Cana, on-site diving, snorkelling, and watersports rentals open up the Dominican coast directly, with excursions to Saona Island, cenote parks, and Altos de Chavón a short drive away. Both resorts offer tennis, spa, and evening entertainment on property."},"beaches-runaway-bay-vs-sandals-dunns-river":{"keyDifferences":"Beaches Runaway Bay is a Jamaican family all-inclusive built around kids programming, with clubs for toddlers and older children, strong room scores (9.0), excellent cleanliness (9.1), and solid service (9.0), but it lags noticeably on food (5.5) and pool (6.9) compared to its rival. Sandals Dunn's River is an adults-only couples resort in Ocho Rios rated among the stronger Sandals properties, posting a 9.4 overall with food at 8.1, pool at 8.5, rooms at 9.5, cleanliness at 9.7, and a location score of 9.3 that reflects its proximity to Dunn's River Falls. The food gap is striking — 2.6 points — and pool quality follows a similar pattern. Beaches wins on family infrastructure; Sandals wins on nearly every experiential metric. If you want a Jamaica family all-inclusive with dedicated kids clubs for all ages including under-4s and reliably clean, comfortable rooms, go to Beaches Runaway Bay. If you want a premium adults-only Jamaican resort near Ocho Rios with superior dining, pools, and rooms at a high but justified price point, go to Sandals Dunn's River.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children, including toddlers, who want a dedicated Jamaican all-inclusive with structured kids programming for every age group. The high cleanliness, service, and room scores make it a reliable, comfortable base for parents who need the resort to handle entertainment as much as they do.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples without children who want a polished, adults-only Jamaican all-inclusive near Ocho Rios. High scores across food, rooms, pool, and service justify the premium price tag, and the Dunn's River Falls location adds a genuinely iconic excursion just outside the door.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts sit on Jamaica's north coast and share the same seasonal logic. December through April is peak season — dry, breezy, and busy, with prices to match. May and June offer a quieter shoulder window before the Atlantic hurricane season peaks July through November. For families working around school calendars, late November and early December hit a useful sweet spot of good weather and slightly lower demand.","activities":"Both resorts offer beach and watersports access along Jamaica's north coast. Sandals Dunn's River holds the location advantage with Dunn's River Falls — one of the Caribbean's most visited natural landmarks — essentially at its doorstep. From either property, guests can reach Ocho Rios town, Mystic Mountain, and river tubing excursions within a short transfer. Beaches Runaway Bay sits on a quieter stretch with Discovery Bay and the Green Grotto Caves nearby for families wanting low-key half-day outings."},"beaches-saint-vincent-vs-sandals-dunns-river":{"keyDifferences":"Beaches Saint Vincent is a family all-inclusive on the lesser-visited island of Saint Vincent, with a kids club for all ages including under-4s, and standout scores in room quality (9.2), cleanliness (9.3), service (9.3), and sleep quality (9.2), though its food rating (6.0) is notably low and beach score (7.2) is modest. Sandals Dunn's River is a premium adults-only all-inclusive in Ocho Rios, Jamaica, with a swim-up bar, spa, gym, nightclub, and buffet, posting stronger scores across food (8.1), pool (8.5), cleanliness (9.7), service (9.5), and value (8.7), though its beach score (6.8) is the weakest number on its sheet. The food gap of 2.1 points is the sharpest differentiator and will matter to guests who prioritize dining. Beaches Saint Vincent suits families wanting a quiet, well-serviced Caribbean escape, while Sandals Dunn's River delivers a polished, amenity-rich adults experience in a well-connected Jamaican location near the famous Dunn's River Falls.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children, including toddlers, who want a quiet, uncrowded Caribbean escape with exceptional room quality, cleanliness, and service. Guests happy to sacrifice dining variety and lively nightlife for a relaxed, well-run property on an unspoiled island away from the mainstream resort circuit.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and adult travelers who want a premium, amenity-loaded Jamaican all-inclusive with excellent food, a swim-up bar, spa, nightclub, and access to Ocho Rios attractions. Those who prioritize polished service, strong value for a luxury price point, and a lively evening atmosphere will feel right at home.","whenToVisit":"Both destinations share a broadly similar Caribbean climate. Saint Vincent's dry season runs January through May, with the island sitting outside the main hurricane belt, making it reliable year-round. Ocho Rios is best visited December through April to avoid Jamaica's wetter summer months and reduce hurricane risk. Shoulder months like May and November can offer lower rates at Sandals with manageable weather.","activities":"Beaches Saint Vincent guests can explore Saint Vincent's volcanic landscapes, botanical gardens, and hiking trails, with snorkeling and water sports available on island. Sandals Dunn's River guests have direct access to the iconic Dunn's River Falls, plus watersports, on-site spa and gym, and the broader Ocho Rios dining and excursion scene. Ocho Rios offers more organized excursion infrastructure, while Saint Vincent rewards independent exploration."},"impression-moxche-by-secrets-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Impression Moxché by Secrets is an adults-only ultra-luxury all-inclusive on the Riviera Maya with a near-perfect pool rating of 10 and room rating of 9.8, delivering an immersive, high-end experience in Playa del Carmen with a nightclub, spa, and buffet alongside à la carte dining requiring no reservations. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly boutique all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with golf, yoga, tennis, and a swim-up bar, but trails Moxché meaningfully on food (8.2 vs 9.4), pool (7.3 vs 10), and atmosphere (8 vs 9.3). Both share weak beach ratings—Moxché scores 5.5 and Zoëtry a very poor 3.5—reflecting the swimming limitations of their respective coastlines. Moxché's overall rating edges ahead at 9.4 vs 9.3, but the gap widens sharply on food, pool, and atmosphere. Zoëtry counters with golf, tennis, and yoga, offering more land-based activity variety for families. If you want a polished, adults-only Riviera Maya all-inclusive with exceptional rooms and dining, choose Moxché. For a family-friendly Los Cabos boutique resort with sport and wellness programming, choose Zoëtry.","whoShouldChooseA":"Couples and adult groups who want an ultra-premium adults-only Riviera Maya experience with flawless rooms (9.8), outstanding food (9.4), a perfect-rated pool, and a nightclub—where the focus is indulgence and atmosphere rather than beach swimming or family programming.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families and wellness-oriented couples seeking a refined boutique all-inclusive in Los Cabos with golf, tennis, yoga, and a spa. Those who prioritise a quieter, activity-rich environment over a party atmosphere and can accept a weaker beach and pool experience.","whenToVisit":"Playa del Carmen's peak season runs December through April when humidity drops and rain is rare; avoid September and October during hurricane season. Los Cabos enjoys dry, sunny weather year-round with peak season also December through April. Both destinations command highest prices over the Christmas and spring break windows, so shoulder months like November or early May offer comparable weather at better rates.","activities":"Near Impression Moxché, guests can explore Playa del Carmen's Fifth Avenue, dive cenotes, visit Tulum ruins, and snorkel the Mesoamerican Barrier Reef. Zoëtry Casa del Mar sits close to San Jose del Cabo's art gallery district, whale-watching tours (December–April), sport fishing, ATV desert excursions, and the dramatic rock arch at Land's End accessible by boat from Cabo San Lucas."},"impression-isla-mujeres-by-secrets-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Impression Isla Mujeres by Secrets and Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos share the same overall rating (9.3) and price tier, but diverge sharply in beach quality and atmosphere. Impression's beach scores 7.8 versus Zoëtry's strikingly low 3.5, a gap that reflects Los Cabos's notoriously rough, non-swimmable Pacific surf. Impression also leads on atmosphere (9.3 vs. 8.0), food (9.4 vs. 8.2), pool (8.9 vs. 7.3), and room quality (9.7 vs. 9.2). Zoëtry counters with a golf course and tennis, amenities Impression lacks, and welcomes families where Impression is strictly adults-only. Impression's Caribbean island setting on Isla Mujeres — accessed by ferry from Cancún — delivers a more immersive, destination-feel experience, while Zoëtry sits in the manicured San Jose del Cabo corridor. If you want superior food, beach, pool, and an adults-only Caribbean island retreat, choose Impression. If you want a family-friendly Los Cabos base with golf, tennis, and proximity to Cabo's dining and nightlife scene, choose Zoëtry.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples or groups seeking a high-end Caribbean island experience with outstanding food (9.4), immaculate rooms (9.7), snorkelling, diving, and a genuinely remote-feeling location on Isla Mujeres — without children and without compromising on beach or pool quality.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families or mixed-age groups who prioritise a polished Los Cabos address with golf, tennis, spa, and easy access to San Jose del Cabo's restaurants and galleries, and who can accept that swimming happens in the pool rather than the ocean.","whenToVisit":"Impression Isla Mujeres shines December through April when Caribbean winds are calm and seas are clear for snorkelling and diving; hurricane season (June–October) carries real risk. Zoëtry Los Cabos is best November through May when Baja temperatures are mild and desert landscapes are at their most inviting; summer brings humidity and the occasional tropical storm to the Cabo corridor.","activities":"At Impression, guests snorkel and dive the crystal Caribbean, visit Isla Mujeres village and its sea-turtle sanctuary, or take a short ferry to Cancún's broader offerings. At Zoëtry, guests golf nearby courses, play tennis on-site, explore San Jose del Cabo's art district and weekly gallery walk, take ATV or whale-watching excursions, or drive twenty minutes to Cabo San Lucas for deep-sea fishing and nightlife."},"zoetry-agua-punta-cana-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Both are boutique Zoëtry properties at the luxury price tier with near-identical overall scores (9.2 vs 9.3), but the differences that matter are beach and pool. Zoëtry Agua Punta Cana sits in Uvero Alto on the Dominican Republic's Atlantic coast and earns a 6.5 beach rating — decent but not exceptional — alongside a stronger pool score of 7.8 and a lazy river, making water time more diversified. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos posts a strikingly low 3.5 beach score, reflecting the Pacific's notoriously rough surf at San Jose del Cabo, where swimming in the ocean is largely off-limits. Its pool score of 7.3 is also lower. Atmosphere skews livelier at Punta Cana (8.4 vs 8.0), while Los Cabos edges ahead on service (9.5 vs 9.4) and adds golf and tennis. Food ratings are close (8.4 vs 8.2). If a swimmable beach is central to your trip, Punta Cana wins clearly. If golf, yoga, and desert-meets-sea scenery appeal more than the water itself, Los Cabos makes the case.","whoShouldChooseA":"Guests who want a boutique Dominican luxury all-inclusive where a swimmable beach, lazy river, diving, and fishing are part of the experience. Ideal for couples or small families who want genuine Caribbean water access paired with high-end service and room quality in a quieter, less crowded corridor of Punta Cana.","whoShouldChooseB":"Guests drawn to Baja's dramatic desert-coastal scenery who won't miss swimming in the ocean. Best suited to couples or small families who prioritize golf, tennis, yoga, and impeccable service over beach use, and who want a refined, tranquil boutique base near San Jose del Cabo's art galleries and restaurants.","whenToVisit":"Punta Cana's peak season runs December through April when Atlantic weather is dry and settled; hurricane season spans June through November, with September the riskiest month. Los Cabos is most reliably sunny October through June, with July through September bringing occasional tropical storms and high humidity. Both destinations can see elevated rates over Christmas and New Year.","activities":"At Zoëtry Agua, guests can dive, fish, swim in the lazy river, or use the adult pool and spa on-site; excursions to Samaná and Indigenous Eyes Ecological Park are within reach from Uvero Alto. At Zoëtry Casa del Mar, on-site golf, tennis, and yoga anchor the activity menu, while nearby San Jose del Cabo offers art walks, whale watching from January through March, sport fishing, and ATV tours through the Baja desert."},"zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos-vs-zoetry-villa-rolandi-isla-mujeres":{"keyDifferences":"Both Zoëtry properties share identical overall (9.3), pool (7.3), cleanliness (9.4), and location (9.0) scores, making the real distinctions visible only in specific subcategories. Casa del Mar Los Cabos scores notably higher on service (9.5 vs 9.4) and value (8.8 vs 8.5), but its beach rating is a stark 3.5 compared to Villa Rolandi's 6.0 — a meaningful gap that reflects the rough, non-swimmable Pacific surf typical of Los Cabos versus the calm Caribbean waters off Isla Mujeres. Villa Rolandi counters with better food (8.8 vs 8.2), sleep quality (8.9 vs 8.6), and an adults-only policy that shapes its quieter atmosphere. Casa del Mar is a family-friendly resort with a swim-up bar, tennis, golf access, and evening entertainment; Villa Rolandi is an intimate adults-only boutique with diving, snorkelling, and fishing on a tranquil island reachable only by ferry. If you want a family-friendly Pacific Mexico all-inclusive with golf, tennis, and strong service, go to Casa del Mar. If you want a refined, adults-only Caribbean retreat with better food, a swimmable beach, and water-based activities, go to Villa Rolandi.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families and active couples who want a luxury Los Cabos all-inclusive with golf, tennis, a swim-up bar, and evening entertainment, and who are content with a scenic but non-swimmable Pacific beach offset by a strong service score of 9.5.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples seeking a quiet, intimate all-inclusive on a car-free Caribbean island, where better food ratings (8.8), calmer swimmable waters, and activities like diving, snorkelling, and fishing define the experience over resort-style entertainment.","whenToVisit":"Casa del Mar Los Cabos is best from November through May when Baja weather is dry and settled; summer brings heat and occasional hurricanes. Villa Rolandi on Isla Mujeres suits visits from December through April for calm Caribbean conditions, though the island is warm year-round. Both properties sit in the upper $$$$ tier, so shoulder months like May or November offer the same luxury at reduced rates.","activities":"At Casa del Mar, guests can play golf on nearby Los Cabos courses, take yoga classes, use the tennis courts, and explore San Jose del Cabo's art district and whale-watching excursions. At Villa Rolandi, the focus shifts to the water — diving, snorkelling, and fishing trips depart directly from the resort, and the ferry ride to Cancun or a golf cart tour of Isla Mujeres village adds easy off-property variety."},"secrets-tides-punta-cana-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Tides Punta Cana is an adults-only Dominican Republic all-inclusive on the Punta Cana coast with diving, snorkelling, a nightclub, swim-up bar, and evening entertainment, earning a strong beach score of 6.5 and a pool score of 8.4. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly Mexican boutique all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with yoga, tennis, golf, a heated pool, and a spa, but its beach scores just 3.5 — a significant gap reflecting the notoriously rough, non-swimmable Pacific surf at Los Cabos. Secrets Tides edges out on pool (8.4 vs 7.3) and overall score (9.1 vs 9.3), while Zoëtry leads on service (9.5 vs 9.2) and food (8.2 vs 7.9). Secrets Tides is the stronger choice for guests who want a true beach-and-ocean experience with watersports and nightlife, while Zoëtry suits those who prioritise refined service, wellness, and a quieter Mexican Baja atmosphere over actual swimming beaches.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples or groups who want a lively Dominican Republic all-inclusive with genuine beach and ocean access, watersports including diving and snorkelling, a nightclub, and high room quality at a competitive price point in Punta Cana.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families or couples who prioritise exceptional service, yoga, tennis, golf, and a tranquil boutique atmosphere in San Jose del Cabo, and who understand that the Los Cabos Pacific beach is scenic but not swimmable — pool time replaces beach time here.","whenToVisit":"Punta Cana peaks December through April when Caribbean trade winds keep humidity low and rain minimal; avoid September and October during hurricane season. Los Cabos is best October through June when temperatures are comfortable and desert rainfall is minimal; July through September brings heat, humidity, and occasional tropical storms to Baja.","activities":"Secrets Tides guests can dive, snorkel, and use watersports directly from the resort, with Punta Cana's shopping and excursions nearby. Zoëtry guests can play golf, join yoga classes, and explore the art galleries and restaurants of San Jose del Cabo's charming historic town centre, a short drive away — a cultural offering that Punta Cana's resort strip cannot match."},"secrets-moxche-playa-del-carmen-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Moxche Playa del Carmen is an adults-only luxury all-inclusive on Mexico's Caribbean coast with a standout pool rating of 9.5, strong food scores of 9.2, a nightclub, buffet, and no-reservation restaurants, built for guests who want a lively, amenity-rich Riviera Maya experience. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly boutique all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo on the Pacific side with a golf course but significantly weaker scores for pool (7.3) and beach (3.5 versus Secrets' already modest 5.7), reflecting the notoriously rough surf of the Los Cabos coastline. Secrets edges out on food (9.2 vs 8.2), pool (9.5 vs 7.3), and atmosphere (8.7 vs 8.0), while Zoëtry holds a slight overall rating lead (9.3 vs 9.1) and adds golf. Both are priced at $$$$. If you want an adults-only Caribbean all-inclusive with a nightclub, excellent pools, and strong dining in Playa del Carmen, choose Secrets Moxche. If you want a family-friendly boutique resort with golf access and a quieter Baja atmosphere in Los Cabos, choose Zoëtry Casa del Mar.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult couples and groups who want a high-energy, amenity-packed Caribbean all-inclusive in Playa del Carmen with excellent pools, a nightclub, strong dining scores, and no-reservation restaurants in a lively Riviera Maya setting.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families and low-key travelers who want a refined, intimate boutique all-inclusive in Los Cabos with golf access, attentive service, and a tranquil Baja California atmosphere, and who won't miss a swimmable beach or a large pool scene.","whenToVisit":"Secrets Moxche benefits from Playa del Carmen's dry season, November through April, when heat is manageable and rainfall minimal; avoid hurricane season, June through October. Zoëtry Los Cabos is best visited October through June, when Baja temperatures are comfortable; July and August bring heat and occasional tropical storms, though Los Cabos sees less hurricane impact than the Caribbean.","activities":"At Secrets Moxche, guests swim in heated pools, join yoga classes, use the spa and gym, play tennis, and access Playa del Carmen's famous Fifth Avenue for shopping and nightlife nearby. At Zoëtry Los Cabos, guests can golf, practice yoga, use the spa and gym, play tennis, and explore San Jose del Cabo's art district and galleries, with whale watching excursions available seasonally from January through March."},"secrets-la-romana-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets La Romana is an adults-only Dominican Republic all-inclusive in Bayahibe with a strong beach score of 8.3, a waterpark, lazy river, casino, nightclub, diving, snorkelling, and fishing — a full-amenity resort built for active couples who want variety. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly boutique all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with a strikingly low beach score of 3.5 (the Sea of Cortez here is typically not swimmable), but it compensates with exceptional service rated 9.5, room quality at 9.2, cleanliness at 9.4, yoga, a heated pool with swim-up bar, and a golf course nearby. Secrets La Romana edges ahead on beach and water activities, while Zoëtry wins on service, rooms, and cleanliness. The core tradeoff is a genuinely swimmable Caribbean beach with broad entertainment amenities at Secrets versus a refined, serene Baja experience built around exceptional hospitality and room quality rather than ocean access at Zoëtry.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples or groups who want a lively Dominican Republic all-inclusive with a real swimmable beach, waterpark, lazy river, casino, nightclub, diving, and snorkelling — a resort where keeping busy and having structured evening entertainment is part of the appeal.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families or couples who prioritize impeccable service, beautifully appointed rooms, and a serene Baja California atmosphere over beach swimming — particularly those drawn to Los Cabos for its scenery, golf, yoga, and the distinctive charm of San Jose del Cabo's art and culture scene nearby.","whenToVisit":"Secrets La Romana benefits from the Dominican Republic's dry season from December through April, avoiding peak hurricane risk from August through October. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos enjoys reliably sunny weather from November through June, with Los Cabos' brief hurricane season running September through October. Both resorts share similar seasonal logic — late autumn through spring offers the most dependable weather at either destination.","activities":"Secrets La Romana guests can dive and snorkel the reef near Bayahibe, visit nearby Isla Saona on a catamaran excursion, and explore Altos de Chavón's hilltop village. Zoëtry Casa del Mar guests are minutes from San Jose del Cabo's gallery district, can arrange whale-watching from January through March, explore Cabo Pulmo's UNESCO-protected reef, and access nearby golf courses — a notably different set of excursions oriented around scenery and culture rather than watersports."},"dreams-la-romana-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams La Romana and Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos are both four-dollar-sign family all-inclusives with matching overall ratings (9.2 vs 9.3) and identical value scores (8.8), but they diverge sharply in focus and setting. Dreams La Romana is a large Dominican Republic family resort in Bayahibe built around activity and entertainment: a waterpark for both age groups, lazy river, pool slide, kids and teen clubs, casino, nightclub, and diving. Zoëtry Casa del Mar is a boutique Mexican property in San Jose del Cabo where intimacy and quality take precedence, posting noticeably higher scores for food (8.2 vs 7.5), room (9.2 vs 8.8), atmosphere (8.0 vs 7.1), cleanliness (9.4 vs 9.0), and service (9.5 vs 9.0). The critical trade-off is beach: Dreams La Romana scores 7.8 versus a damaging 3.5 at Zoëtry, reflecting Los Cabos's rocky Pacific surf conditions. Dreams delivers volume and family infrastructure; Zoëtry delivers refinement, quieter spaces, yoga, golf, and a superior room and service experience with no beach to speak of.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a high-energy Dominican Republic all-inclusive with waterparks, a lazy river, kids and teen clubs, a casino, nightclub, and a proper swimmable Caribbean beach. Best for those who want maximum amenities and entertainment under one roof.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples or families with older children who prioritize exceptional service, beautiful rooms, refined food, and a tranquil boutique atmosphere in the Los Cabos corridor. Guests who don't need a swimmable beach and are drawn to golf, yoga, and the polished Zoëtry experience will feel most at home here.","whenToVisit":"Dreams La Romana sits in the Dominican Republic's southeast, where the dry season runs November through April and hurricane season peaks August through October. Zoëtry Casa del Mar enjoys Los Cabos's famously sunny desert climate year-round, though late summer brings occasional tropical storms. Both resorts offer their best conditions December through April, making that window ideal for either destination.","activities":"Dreams La Romana guests can explore the UNESCO-listed Altos de Chavón village, dive the reef at Catalina Island, and use the resort's full waterpark and casino. Zoëtry Casa del Mar guests can play golf on nearby championship courses, take whale-watching tours from November through March, explore the colonial streets of San Jose del Cabo, and visit the iconic Land's End arch at Cabo San Lucas, about 45 minutes away."},"secrets-the-vine-cancun-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets The Vine Cancun is an adults-only all-inclusive on the Cancun hotel strip, delivering strong room (9.3) and service (9.3) scores alongside a beach rating of 8.3, a heated pool, nightclub, diving, and no-reservation restaurants. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with a slightly higher overall (9.3 vs 9.2) and service score (9.5 vs 9.3), but a strikingly low beach rating of 3.5 — a direct consequence of the Pacific swells that make Los Cabos coastline largely unswimmable. Zoëtry compensates with yoga, tennis, a golf course, and a swim-up bar, and edges ahead on sleep quality (8.6 vs 8.4) and value (8.8 vs 8.7). Pool scores are modest at both properties (7.8 and 7.3 respectively). The fundamental split is between a swim-and-beach Cancun adults resort with a nightclub and diving, versus a wellness-leaning family property in Cabo where the ocean is scenic rather than swimmable.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples or groups who want a lively Cancun all-inclusive with genuine beach access, diving, a nightclub, and strong room quality on the Caribbean side of Mexico where calm, swimmable water is a given.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families or wellness-focused couples who prioritize exceptional service, yoga, tennis, and golf in the dramatic Los Cabos landscape, and who understand that the Pacific beach is for scenery rather than swimming.","whenToVisit":"Secrets The Vine Cancun is best from December through April, avoiding hurricane season (June–November) when Caribbean weather turns unpredictable. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos suits the same winter window, when Baja desert temperatures are pleasant and dry. Both properties carry a premium in the holiday peak weeks around Christmas and New Year.","activities":"Secrets The Vine guests can dive Cancun's reef system, explore the Nichupte Lagoon, visit Isla Mujeres, or tour Chichen Itza. Zoëtry Casa del Mar guests can whale-watch off Cabo during winter months, tour the iconic Land's End arch, play golf on courses across the Los Cabos corridor, and visit the art galleries and restaurants of San Jose del Cabo's historic town center."},"secrets-puerto-los-cabos-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Both resorts sit in San Jose del Cabo at the same price tier, share identical beach ratings (3.5) and cleanliness scores (9.4), and are separated by only 0.1 points on food (8.1 vs 8.2) and rooms (9.1 vs 9.2). The meaningful gaps appear in service (9.1 vs 9.5), sleep quality (8.1 vs 8.6), location (8.6 vs 9.0), and overall score (8.9 vs 9.3), all favoring Zoëtry. Secrets compensates with a significantly broader amenity set: archery, nightclub, mini golf, fishing, a buffet, and a no-reservation restaurant policy that Zoëtry lacks. Secrets is adults-only with a livelier entertainment program; Zoëtry is a quieter, family-eligible boutique property where the higher service rating and better sleep quality suggest a more refined, less stimulating atmosphere. If you want activity variety, a nightclub, and a full entertainment program in an adults-only setting, Secrets wins on breadth. If you want measurably better service, quieter nights, and a more intimate boutique experience that also accommodates families, Zoëtry has the edge.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples or groups who want a wide activity menu — archery, fishing, mini golf, nightclub — alongside golf and spa access in San Jose del Cabo, and prefer open-seating dining without reservation logistics at a lively, amenity-heavy resort.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families or couples who prioritize exceptional service (9.5), quieter sleep (8.6), and a more intimate boutique atmosphere over a packed activity roster, and value a slightly stronger location score within the San Jose del Cabo corridor.","whenToVisit":"Los Cabos runs warm and dry year-round, making it reliably bookable in most months. November through May offers the most stable, rain-free conditions. Summer and early fall bring higher humidity and occasional tropical storm risk but also lower rates. Both resorts sit in the same area, so timing advice applies equally to both.","activities":"Both resorts offer golf course access, yoga, spa treatments, and swim-up bar lounging. Secrets adds fishing charters, archery, and mini golf on property. The broader San Jose del Cabo area provides sport fishing excursions, whale watching from January through March, ATV desert tours, snorkeling at Cabo Pulmo, and the historic San Jose del Cabo art district within easy reach of either property."},"breathless-cabo-san-lucas-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Breathless Cabo San Lucas is an adults-only all-inclusive on the Pacific side of Cabo San Lucas with a nightclub, evening entertainment, and a lively atmosphere built for partying couples and social travelers. Zoëtry Casa del Mar is a family-friendly boutique all-inclusive in the quieter San Jose del Cabo corridor, where the standout ratings are service (9.5 vs 9.1), food (8.2 vs 7.5), room quality (9.2 vs 8.9), and sleep quality (8.6 vs 7.9), making it the more refined, restful choice. Breathless wins on atmosphere energy and location buzz, while Zoëtry delivers a noticeably calmer, higher-quality stay. The beach ratings tell a stark story: Breathless scores 6.5 while Zoëtry scores just 3.5, reflecting the notoriously rough, swim-unfriendly beaches of the East Cape corridor. Breathless adds fishing and a nightclub; Zoëtry counters with golf, yoga, tennis, and a swim-up bar. If you want a lively adults-only Cabo party resort with nightlife, go to Breathless. If you want a polished, family-capable boutique experience with superior food and service in San Jose del Cabo, go to Zoëtry Casa del Mar.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples and social travelers who want a high-energy Cabo San Lucas all-inclusive with a nightclub, evening entertainment, and a prime location score of 9.2, and who are not prioritizing beach swimming or quiet downtime.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples, honeymooners, and families who want a refined, quieter Los Cabos all-inclusive with top-tier service (9.5), excellent food (8.2), superior room quality (9.2), and amenities like golf, yoga, and tennis, accepting that the beach is not swim-friendly.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Los Cabos' dry, sunny climate from November through May, when rainfall is minimal and temperatures are comfortable. Summer months bring heat, humidity, and hurricane risk, with September being the most active storm month. The shoulder months of late October and early November offer good value before peak-season pricing kicks in around Christmas and New Year.","activities":"At Breathless, guests fish off Cabo's famous sportfishing fleet, take sunset cruises, and explore the Land's End arch and marina strip. At Zoëtry, golf on nearby East Cape courses, take yoga classes, and play tennis on-site; San Jose del Cabo's art district and weekly Thursday gallery walks are a short drive away. Both properties offer spa treatments, heated pools, and easy access to whale watching during the December–April migration season."},"secrets-royal-beach-punta-cana-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Royal Beach Punta Cana is an adults-only Dominican Republic all-inclusive on a legitimate beach (rated 8.0) with a casino, nightclub, lazy river, diving, and no-reservation restaurants in a lively Punta Cana resort corridor. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly boutique Mexican all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with a heated pool, golf, yoga, and exceptional service, but a beach rated just 3.5 — a significant drawback reflecting the rough, non-swimmable surf typical of that Baja coastline. Zoëtry edges Secrets on overall score (9.3 vs 9.1), service (9.5 vs 9.2), food (8.2 vs 7.9), and cleanliness (9.4 vs 9.2), suggesting a more polished, intimate operation despite fewer amenities. Secrets counters with actual beach and pool use, a casino, nightclub, and diving that Zoëtry cannot match. If you want an adults-only Caribbean all-inclusive with real beach access, nightlife, and a full activity roster in Punta Cana, choose Secrets. If you want a refined, service-first boutique experience in Los Cabos with golf and yoga but can accept a non-swimmable beach, choose Zoëtry.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples or groups who want a lively Punta Cana all-inclusive with genuine beach and pool access, a casino, nightclub, diving, and a broad dining program without reservation hassles — prioritizing Caribbean beach time and evening entertainment over boutique refinement.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families or couples who prioritize exceptional service, immaculate rooms, yoga, and golf in a quieter San Jose del Cabo setting, and who understand upfront that the beach is decorative rather than swimmable — pool relaxation and cultural proximity to Cabo are the draws here.","whenToVisit":"Secrets Royal Beach benefits from Punta Cana's dry season, December through April, when humidity drops and hurricane risk is minimal. Zoëtry Casa del Mar enjoys near-perfect weather from October through June, with Los Cabos summers bringing heat and occasional tropical storms. Both properties command premium pricing over the North American winter holidays, so shoulder months like November or early May offer better value at either resort.","activities":"At Secrets, guests can dive Caribbean waters, play tennis, use the casino, lounge on a swimmable beach, or catch nightclub and evening entertainment without leaving the property. At Zoëtry, golf at nearby Los Cabos courses, yoga classes, spa treatments, and the cultural restaurants and galleries of San Jose del Cabo town — walkable from the resort — are the main draws. Neither property lacks for on-site programming, but Secrets skews toward water and nightlife while Zoëtry leans toward wellness and land-based exploration."},"dreams-cap-cana-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Cap Cana and Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos are both premium family all-inclusives rated 9.3–9.4 overall, but they diverge sharply in beach quality and amenity breadth. Dreams Cap Cana holds an 8.5 beach rating against Zoëtry's strikingly low 3.5, a gap that reflects the Pacific-side conditions at San Jose del Cabo where rough surf makes swimming largely impractical. Dreams also edges ahead on value (9.1 vs 8.8) and location (9.5 vs 9.0). Zoëtry counters with stronger food scores (8.2 vs 7.7), slightly better service (9.5 vs 9.4), and a more curated atmosphere (8.0 vs 7.6), leaning into yoga, spa, tennis, and a heated pool rather than beach life. Dreams Cap Cana offers a kids club for under-4s, a buffet, and reservation-free dining that suits families wanting flexibility, while Zoëtry's smaller, wellness-oriented setup feels more refined. If beach access is central to your trip, Dreams Cap Cana is the clear choice. If you prioritize food quality, spa culture, and a quieter atmosphere and can accept a largely non-swimmable beach, Zoëtry delivers.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children, including toddlers, who want a high-rated Dominican Republic beach resort with strong location scores, a kids club from infancy, reservation-free dining, and excellent value at a premium price point. Best suited to guests for whom beach quality is non-negotiable.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and families who prioritize food quality, wellness amenities, and a refined boutique atmosphere over beach access. Well-suited to guests drawn to yoga, spa treatments, golf, and tennis in a smaller, calmer Los Cabos setting, and who understand the beach limitations of the Pacific Baja coast.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Cap Cana is best visited November through April, avoiding the Dominican Republic's Atlantic hurricane season peaking August to October. Zoëtry Casa del Mar suits travel from November through May, when Los Cabos enjoys dry, sunny weather. Both resorts see peak pricing over US holidays and spring break. Summer brings heat and humidity to both destinations, with added storm risk in the Caribbean.","activities":"At Dreams Cap Cana guests enjoy a swimmable Caribbean beach, swim-up bar, kids club programming, and Cap Cana's marina and nearby Scape Park for cave swimming and zip-lining. At Zoëtry Casa del Mar, guests can use the resort's tennis courts, yoga classes, spa, and heated pool, then venture to San Jose del Cabo's art district, whale watching excursions from January through March, and world-class sport fishing available year-round in the Sea of Cortez."},"dreams-royal-beach-punta-cana-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Royal Beach Punta Cana is a large family all-inclusive on Bavaro beach in the Dominican Republic, rated 9.1 overall, with an extensive amenity list including a waterpark, lazy river, kids club for under-4s, teen club, casino, nightclub, diving, snorkelling, babysitting, and restaurants that require no reservations. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a boutique Mexican all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo rated 9.3 overall, with notably higher scores for food (8.2 vs 7.5), rooms (9.2 vs 8.8), cleanliness (9.4 vs 9.1), and service (9.5 vs 9.1), but a critically low beach rating of 3.5 versus Dreams' 8.0, reflecting the notoriously rough, non-swimmable Pacific surf at Los Cabos. Dreams wins decisively on activity breadth and beach quality; Zoëtry wins on intimacy, food, and service polish. If you want a large Dominican family resort with a swimmable beach, waterpark, and full entertainment program, choose Dreams. If you want a refined, quieter Mexican boutique experience with exceptional service and rooms but no usable beach, choose Zoëtry.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a lively Dominican Republic all-inclusive with a genuine swimmable beach, waterpark, lazy river, kids and teen clubs, babysitting, casino, and nightclub under one roof at a competitive price.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples or families with older children who prioritize exceptional service, elevated food, and beautifully appointed rooms in a boutique San Jose del Cabo setting, and who are comfortable with a non-swimmable beach and a quieter, more intimate atmosphere.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Royal Beach benefits from the Dominican Republic's year-round warmth, though December through April offers the driest, most reliable weather. Zoëtry Casa del Mar is best visited October through June to avoid Los Cabos hurricane season, with February through April particularly ideal for warm, dry days and calmer Pacific conditions.","activities":"Dreams guests can dive, snorkel, play tennis, use the waterpark and lazy river, or explore Bavaro's lively strip of shops and excursions nearby. Zoëtry guests can play golf on a nearby course, practice yoga, enjoy spa treatments, and take day trips to San Jose del Cabo's art galleries, the famous arch at Land's End, or whale watching from January through March."},"secrets-vallarta-bay-puerto-vallarta-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Vallarta Bay Puerto Vallarta is an adults-only all-inclusive on Mexico's Pacific coast in Puerto Vallarta, with a nightclub, buffet, swim-up bar, evening entertainment, and no-reservation restaurants, rated highly for rooms (9.0), cleanliness (9.2), and service (9.2), but with a notably weak beach score (6.0) and modest pool rating (7.4). Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with yoga, golf, spa, and swim-up bar, earning stronger marks for overall score (9.3 vs 9.0), food (8.2 vs 7.9), service (9.5 vs 9.2), and atmosphere (8.0 vs 7.5), though its beach score is even lower at 3.5, typical of the Sea of Cortez's rougher surf. Secrets Vallarta leans into lively adults-only nightlife and entertainment in a vibrant city setting, while Zoëtry Casa del Mar offers a quieter, wellness-oriented experience suited to families and couples seeking refinement over a party atmosphere. Both share the same price tier, but Zoëtry edges ahead on nearly every quality metric.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples or groups who want a lively Puerto Vallarta all-inclusive with a nightclub, evening entertainment, swim-up bar, and strong room quality in a well-connected city location where beach quality matters less than atmosphere and convenience.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families and couples prioritizing exceptional service (9.5), superior food quality, yoga, golf, and a refined wellness-focused atmosphere in Los Cabos, and who are comfortable with a non-swimmable beach in exchange for a polished, quieter all-inclusive experience.","whenToVisit":"Puerto Vallarta's dry season runs November through April, making winter the prime window for Secrets Vallarta Bay. Los Cabos enjoys more year-round sunshine but peak season similarly falls October through May before summer humidity arrives. Both destinations are best avoided during hurricane season, which peaks August through October, with Cabos carrying slightly higher storm risk in September.","activities":"Secrets Vallarta Bay guests can explore Puerto Vallarta's lively Malecón boardwalk, old town, zip-lining, whale watching in season, and deep-sea fishing. Zoëtry Casa del Mar sits near San Jose del Cabo's charming art district, the Estero San Jose nature reserve, world-class sport fishing, ATV desert tours, and easy access to the famous arch at Land's End via boat excursion."},"secrets-papagayo-costa-rica-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Papagayo Costa Rica is an adults-only all-inclusive on Costa Rica's Gulf of Papagayo with diving, fishing, a swim-up bar, buffet, and evening entertainment on a volcanic Pacific coastline. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly boutique all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo, Mexico, with yoga, golf access, room service, and an intimate atmosphere in the Baja desert setting. Zoëtry edges out Secrets on nearly every rated dimension: overall (9.3 vs 9.0), food (8.2 vs 7.7), service (9.5 vs 9.2), cleanliness (9.4 vs 9.2), room quality (9.2 vs 8.9), and sleep quality (8.6 vs 8.2). Neither excels at beach — Secrets scores a modest 6.0 while Zoëtry's Pacific Baja beach rates a weak 3.5, making pools the practical focus at both. Secrets adds active water pursuits like diving and fishing that Zoëtry lacks, while Zoëtry counters with yoga, golf, and room service in a quieter, more refined setting. Secrets suits adventure-minded adults; Zoëtry suits those prioritizing refined service and calm.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults seeking an active all-inclusive on Costa Rica's Pacific coast who want diving, fishing, and evening entertainment in a lively Gulf of Papagayo setting. Strong service and cleanliness at a competitive price, with the tradeoff of a below-average beach.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families and couples who prioritize exceptional service, polished rooms, and a tranquil boutique atmosphere in Los Cabos. Yoga, golf access, and room service make this the more refined choice, though guests should arrive knowing the beach is the weakest element of the property.","whenToVisit":"Secrets Papagayo is best visited during Costa Rica's dry season, December through April, when the Gulf of Papagayo sees consistent sun and calm waters. Zoëtry Casa del Mar suits year-round visits given Baja's desert climate, though October and November bring hurricane-season risk. Both properties avoid peak-season crowds most effectively in late April through early June.","activities":"At Secrets Papagayo, diving and sport fishing are the standout pursuits alongside tennis and water sports on the Gulf of Papagayo, with nearby Guanacaste offering zip-lining and national park excursions. At Zoëtry Casa del Mar, yoga and golf complement the pool and spa, while San Jose del Cabo's art district, glass-blowing studios, and whale-watching charters from November through March provide strong off-property options."},"dreams-flora-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Flora Resort & Spa is a large Dominican Republic family all-inclusive in Cabeza de Toro with a waterpark, kids club, teen club, babysitting, nightclub, and restaurants requiring no reservations—built for families who want maximum amenity coverage at a busy beach resort. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a boutique Mexican all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with a heated pool, swim-up bar, golf course, yoga, tennis, and exceptionally high service and cleanliness scores. The numbers tell an important story: Zoëtry scores notably higher on food (8.2 vs 7.6), atmosphere (8.0 vs 7.4), room quality (9.2 vs 8.9), service (9.5 vs 9.0), and cleanliness (9.4 vs 9.1), while Dreams Flora leads significantly on beach (6.8 vs 3.5—Cabo's Pacific surf makes swimming difficult) and offers far broader family infrastructure. Dreams Flora is the choice for families who need a kids club, babysitting, waterpark, and nightclub; Zoëtry suits those prioritizing refined service, better dining, and a quieter, more polished atmosphere over beach access.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children who want a comprehensive Dominican Republic all-inclusive with a waterpark, kids club for under-4s, teen club, babysitting, nightclub, and rooms accommodating five or more people—maximum coverage for an active, entertainment-driven family holiday.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples or families with older children who want a boutique, service-driven Mexican all-inclusive where elevated dining, impeccable cleanliness, golf, yoga, and tennis matter more than a swimmable beach or a large-scale kids program.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Flora benefits from the Dominican Republic's dry season, December through April, when rainfall is minimal and trade winds keep temperatures comfortable. Zoëtry Casa del Mar sits on Los Cabos' arid Pacific coast, where conditions are sunny and warm nearly year-round, though hurricane season technically runs June through November—September being the highest-risk month for both destinations.","activities":"Dreams Flora guests can use the onsite waterpark, nightclub, and spa, and explore Punta Cana's broader strip of water sports, buggy excursions, and cenote tours nearby. Zoëtry Casa del Mar guests have access to the resort's golf course, tennis courts, and yoga classes, with San Jose del Cabo's art galleries, sport fishing, whale watching, and the dramatic Land's End rock formation all close at hand."},"sunscape-cancun-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Sunscape Cancun Resort & Spa is a large family all-inclusive on Mexico's Caribbean coast with a waterpark for little kids, kids club, teen club, nightclub, diving, fishing, babysitting, and rooms for groups of five or more. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a boutique wellness-leaning all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo on the Pacific side, with yoga, a swim-up bar, golf, tennis, and a notably higher overall rating of 9.3 versus Sunscape's 8.8. The rating gaps tell the real story: Zoëtry leads significantly on food (8.2 vs 6.3), rooms (9.2 vs 8.3), service (9.5 vs 8.5), atmosphere (8.0 vs 6.1), and cleanliness (9.4 vs 8.7). Sunscape counters with a far better beach score (7.3 vs 3.5), a much broader family activity roster, and a genuine nightlife program. Sunscape is the better pick for families who need kids infrastructure and a Caribbean beach; Zoëtry is for guests who prioritize refined service, excellent food, and a tranquil boutique atmosphere over a swimmable beach.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children and teenagers who want a large Caribbean all-inclusive with a waterpark, kids and teen clubs, babysitting, nightclub, diving, and fishing on a proper Cancun beach. Best for those who need activity breadth and group-sized rooms at a value-conscious price.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples or families with older children who prioritize exceptional service, outstanding food, and a serene boutique atmosphere in Los Cabos. Ideal for guests who value room quality and cleanliness above a swimmable beach and who want yoga, golf, and tennis alongside polished all-inclusive dining.","whenToVisit":"Cancun's peak season runs December through April when the Caribbean is calm and dry; hurricane season runs June through November. Los Cabos enjoys year-round sunshine with minimal rain, though September brings the highest storm risk. Both resorts are busiest over US holidays and spring break, so booking well ahead for those windows is essential at either property.","activities":"At Sunscape Cancun, guests can dive, fish, visit the waterpark, and explore Cancun's Hotel Zone shopping and nightlife nearby. At Zoëtry Casa del Mar, guests can play golf, take yoga classes, play tennis, and access the historic art galleries and restaurants of San Jose del Cabo's downtown just minutes away. Both properties offer spa treatments and evening entertainment on-site."},"secrets-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Playa Mujeres is an adults-only all-inclusive on Mexico's Caribbean coast near Cancún, with a nightclub, buffet, swim-up bar, and evening entertainment across a large resort footprint on a proper Caribbean beach (beach rated 7.5). Zoëtry Casa del Mar is a boutique family-friendly all-inclusive in San José del Cabo on the Pacific side, where yoga, room service, and exceptional service (9.5 vs. 9.2) define the experience, but the beach is notoriously rough and nearly unusable (rated just 3.5 vs. 7.5). Secrets scores higher on pool (8.0 vs. 7.3) and atmosphere (8.0 vs. 8.0 tied), while Zoëtry edges it on overall score (9.3 vs. 8.8), rooms (9.2 vs. 9.0), service, and value (8.8 vs. 8.6). Secrets is the livelier, beach-forward adults resort; Zoëtry is the quieter, more intimate property where the draw is Baja scenery, wellness, and personalized service rather than any usable beachfront.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples or friends who want a lively Caribbean all-inclusive with a proper swimmable beach, nightclub, swim-up bar, golf, and evening entertainment near Cancún at a luxury price point without sacrificing energy or variety.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families or couples who prioritize exceptional personalized service, yoga, Baja atmosphere, and intimate boutique surroundings in Los Cabos, and who are not expecting a swimmable beach as part of the experience.","whenToVisit":"Secrets Playa Mujeres sits in the Caribbean hurricane belt; avoid late August through October. Peak season is December through April. Zoëtry Casa del Mar in San José del Cabo enjoys reliable sunshine nearly year-round, with October and November offering lower rates and still-warm weather. Both properties are at their busiest and priciest over the Christmas and New Year holiday window.","activities":"At Secrets, guests can swim, play golf on-site, use the tennis courts, visit the spa, and join evening entertainment and nightclub programming. Zoëtry offers golf access, yoga classes, tennis, and spa treatments, with the dramatic Baja landscape nearby. Both properties sit close to town centers — Isla Mujeres and the ferry to Cancún from Secrets, and the galleries and restaurants of San José del Cabo from Zoëtry."},"secrets-huatulco-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Huatulco and Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos are both upscale Mexican adults-oriented all-inclusives at the same price tier, but they diverge sharply on setting, vibe, and a few key ratings. Secrets Huatulco is an adults-only resort on Oaxaca's Pacific coast with a nightclub, snorkelling, buffet, and no-reservation dining, scoring well on beach (6.8 vs 3.5), pool (7.4 vs 7.3), and atmosphere (7.9 vs 8.0). Zoëtry Casa del Mar is a family-friendly boutique property in San Jose del Cabo with yoga, tennis, a golf course, and a heated pool, scoring meaningfully higher on service (9.5 vs 9.1), cleanliness (9.4 vs 9.1), rooms (9.2 vs 8.9), food (8.2 vs 7.9), and overall (9.3 vs 8.8). Zoëtry's beach rating of 3.5 is a serious caveat — Los Cabos is not a swimming beach destination. Secrets Huatulco wins on beach usability and nightlife energy; Zoëtry wins on refined, intimate service and room quality.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples or friends who want a lively Pacific Mexico all-inclusive with a real swimmable beach, nightclub, snorkelling, and no-reservation dining flexibility in a well-located Huatulco setting at a strong value.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families or couples who prioritise exceptional personalised service, immaculate rooms, yoga, tennis, and golf in a refined boutique Los Cabos setting, and who are comfortable with a beach that is scenic but not suitable for swimming.","whenToVisit":"Huatulco's dry season runs November through May, making those months ideal for Secrets with reliable sun and calm Pacific waters. Los Cabos is sunny nearly year-round, though September and October bring hurricane risk to both coasts. Both properties peak in winter and spring; budget travellers can find value in early summer before hurricane season intensifies.","activities":"At Secrets Huatulco, guests can snorkel the protected bays of Huatulco's national park, explore nine bays by boat tour, visit the town of La Crucecita, or hike coastal trails. At Zoëtry Casa del Mar, guests can golf at nearby courses, take yoga classes, play tennis, visit the charming art galleries and restaurants of San Jose del Cabo's historic downtown, or arrange whale-watching tours from November through March."},"dreams-onyx-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Onyx Resort & Spa is a large Dominican Republic family all-inclusive in Punta Cana with a waterpark, lazy river, kids and teen clubs, babysitting, adult pool, and rooms for groups of five or more, built for families who want maximum activity coverage. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a smaller, more refined Mexican all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with yoga, tennis, a golf course, heated pool, and standout service and room ratings, but a beach score of just 3.5 versus Dreams Onyx's 6.5, reflecting the notoriously rough, non-swimmable Pacific surf at Los Cabos. Dreams Onyx scores higher on pool (7.4 vs 7.3) and beach, while Zoëtry leads meaningfully on food (8.2 vs 7.6), rooms (9.2 vs 8.7), atmosphere (8.0 vs 7.4), service (9.5 vs 9.0), and cleanliness (9.4 vs 9.1). If you want a bustling Dominican family resort with waterparks, a lazy river, and built-in kids programming, choose Dreams Onyx. If you want a quieter, higher-service Mexican boutique experience with exceptional rooms and dining but no real swimming beach, choose Zoëtry.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a large, activity-packed Dominican Republic all-inclusive with a waterpark, lazy river, kids and teen clubs, babysitting, and a swimmable beach, all at a price that rewards the breadth of what's on offer.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples or families with older children who prioritize exceptional service, refined dining, and elegant rooms over beach access, and who are happy to swap Atlantic surf for a polished, tranquil Los Cabos setting with yoga, tennis, and golf nearby.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Onyx is best visited November through April when Dominican Republic humidity drops and hurricane risk is lowest. Zoëtry Casa del Mar suits visits October through June, avoiding the late-summer hurricane season that can affect Los Cabos. Both resorts sit in the same broad price tier, so timing decisions hinge more on weather tolerance than cost.","activities":"Dreams Onyx guests have waterpark slides, a lazy river, swim-up bar, and evening entertainment on-site, with Punta Cana's excursion market offering zip-lining, dune buggies, and cenote tours nearby. Zoëtry guests can use the on-site golf course, yoga classes, and tennis courts, with San Jose del Cabo's art district, whale watching from January through March, and world-class sport fishing all easily accessible."},"secrets-bahia-mita-surf-and-spa-resort-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Bahia Mita Surf & Spa Resort is an adults-only all-inclusive on Mexico's Pacific coast near Punta de Mita, with a nightclub, buffet, swim-up bar, evening entertainment, and a room quality rating of 9.1 in a surf-adjacent setting. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with golf, tennis, yoga, and the highest service rating of the two at 9.5 versus Secrets' 9.2. Zoëtry edges out Secrets on overall score (9.3 vs 8.9), food (8.2 vs 7.8), atmosphere (8.0 vs 7.7), and service (9.5 vs 9.2), while Secrets leads on pool (7.8 vs 7.3) and offers a nightclub Zoëtry lacks. Both have weak beach scores, but Secrets rates slightly better there too (5.0 vs 3.5). Secrets suits couples wanting a livelier Pacific coast adults-only escape; Zoëtry suits families and wellness-minded guests who prioritize attentive service, golf, and tennis in a quieter Los Cabos setting.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples or groups who want a Pacific coast all-inclusive near Punta de Mita with a nightclub, swim-up bar, and strong room quality. Guests who value a surf-town atmosphere, open-seating restaurants, and lively evening entertainment over a polished wellness-focused experience.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families or couples who prioritize exceptional service, golf, tennis, and yoga in a refined San Jose del Cabo setting. Guests willing to forgo a nightclub in exchange for a calmer, higher-service atmosphere and the flexibility of a family-welcoming resort with consistent quality across food and rooms.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts enjoy Mexico's dry season from November through April, making those months ideal for either destination. Punta de Mita's surf season peaks June through September but brings more rain. Los Cabos summers are hot and humid with hurricane risk through October. For either resort, December through March offers the most reliable weather and the busiest crowds.","activities":"At Secrets Bahia Mita, guests can surf nearby breaks, snorkel, and explore the Riviera Nayarit coastline, with Sayulita village a short drive away. At Zoëtry Casa del Mar, guests can play golf on nearby Los Cabos courses, take tennis or yoga classes, and access the Sea of Cortez. Both areas offer sport fishing, whale watching from January through March, and ATV excursions into surrounding desert or jungle terrain."},"dreams-huatulco-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Huatulco Resort & Spa is a full-service family all-inclusive on Mexico's Pacific coast in the quieter Tangolunda bay, with a kids club for under-4s, archery, snorkelling, windsurfing, fishing, babysitting, and no-reservation restaurants, rated 7.3 for beach and 6.9 for pool but a strong 9.1 for cleanliness and 9.0 for service. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a boutique adults-leaning family property in San Jose del Cabo with a heated pool, swim-up bar, tennis, golf access, and a notably higher food score of 8.2 versus Dreams' 7.5, a room score of 9.2 versus 8.6, and a service score of 9.5 versus 9.0, but a beach score of just 3.5 reflecting Los Cabos' notoriously rough, non-swimmable surf. Dreams is the stronger pick for water-based family activity and a proper beach experience; Zoëtry is the pick for refined rooms, exceptional service, and a boutique atmosphere where the pool, not the ocean, is the draw.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children who want a full amenity Pacific Mexico all-inclusive with a kids club for toddlers, babysitting, watersports including snorkelling and windsurfing, fishing excursions, and a genuine swimmable beach in the calm, uncrowded bay of Tangolunda.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and families with older children who prioritise exceptional service, refined rooms, and elevated dining over beach swimming, and who want a boutique Los Cabos experience with golf, tennis, a heated pool, and a swim-up bar in a polished, intimate setting.","whenToVisit":"Huatulco's dry season runs November through April, with calmer seas ideal for snorkelling and watersports; the rainy season from June to October brings humidity and occasional storms but far fewer crowds. Los Cabos enjoys year-round sunshine with very little rainfall, making it a reliable destination anytime, though July through October carries some hurricane-adjacent weather risk. Both resorts peak in price over the Christmas and New Year window.","activities":"At Dreams Huatulco, guests can snorkel the bays of Huatulco's national marine park, try archery on-site, windsurf, fish offshore, or join yoga classes. Los Cabos offers whale watching from January to March, sport fishing for marlin and dorado, ATV tours into the desert, golf on world-class courses near the resort, and day trips to the famous El Arco rock arch at Cabo San Lucas, about 45 minutes away."},"secrets-playa-esmeralda-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Playa Esmeralda is an adults-only Dominican Republic all-inclusive in the remote Miches area, rated 8.2 overall, with standout scores for sleep quality (9.1), cleanliness (8.8), and service (8.6), set on a strong beach (8.5). Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly Mexican all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo, rated 9.3 overall, with exceptional marks for service (9.5), cleanliness (9.4), rooms (9.2), and location (9.0), though its beach rating is a strikingly low 3.5, reflecting the rough Pacific surf typical of Los Cabos. Secrets commands a mid-luxury price point and prioritizes a serene, adults-only beach experience in an off-the-beaten-path Dominican setting, while Zoëtry Casa del Mar charges premium rates for superior rooms, service, and a polished boutique atmosphere in a town with excellent dining and golf nearby. The 1.1-point overall gap and Zoëtry's near-perfect service score signal a meaningfully more refined experience, but guests who prioritize actual beach use should note Secrets wins that category by 5 full points.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults seeking a quieter, beach-forward Dominican Republic escape at a more accessible luxury price point. The combination of a strong beach rating (8.5), excellent sleep quality (9.1), and a remote Miches location suits couples who want genuine seclusion without sacrificing service.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families or couples willing to pay premium rates for exceptional service (9.5), immaculate rooms (9.2), and a refined boutique atmosphere in San Jose del Cabo. Ideal for guests who prioritize land-based amenities like golf, yoga, tennis, and town access over swimming in the ocean.","whenToVisit":"Secrets Playa Esmeralda is best visited November through April, when Dominican Republic humidity and hurricane risk drop significantly. Zoëtry Casa del Mar suits travel from October through June, avoiding Los Cabos's late-summer hurricane season and peak heat. Both properties offer a drier, more comfortable experience in their respective winter and spring months.","activities":"At Secrets Playa Esmeralda, guests have beach access, a spa, gym, and buffet dining without reservations. Zoëtry Casa del Mar adds heated pool, swim-up bar, yoga classes, tennis, golf, and evening entertainment. Off-property, Los Cabos offers world-class sport fishing, whale watching from January through March, and the vibrant dining scene of San Jose del Cabo's art district, while Miches provides access to Laguna Redonda and eco-tourism excursions."},"dreams-playa-mujeres-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Playa Mujeres is a large family-focused Mexican all-inclusive on the Playa Mujeres strip north of Cancún, built around extensive kids infrastructure: a kids club for under-4s, a teen club, a waterpark for both age groups, a lazy river, mini golf, babysitting, and a nightclub for adults. Zoëtry Casa del Mar is a smaller, quieter Mexican all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo aimed at families seeking a more refined, wellness-oriented experience, with yoga, tennis, a heated pool, and notably higher service (9.5 vs 9.0) and cleanliness (9.4 vs 9.2) ratings. The most striking gap is beach quality: Dreams rates 7.5 while Zoëtry scores just 3.5, reflecting Los Cabos's famously rough, non-swimmable Pacific surf. Zoëtry edges Dreams on overall score (9.3 vs 8.9), food (8.2 vs 7.9), and value (8.8 vs 8.4). Dreams wins on sheer activity volume and kids programming depth. If you want a large, entertainment-heavy Caribbean family all-inclusive with waterparks and a nightclub, choose Dreams. If you want a quieter, wellness-leaning boutique experience in Baja with superior service, choose Zoëtry.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a full-spectrum Caribbean all-inclusive with waterparks, a lazy river, dedicated kids and teen clubs, babysitting, evening entertainment, and a nightclub, all on a swimmable beach north of Cancún.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and families with older children who prioritize exceptional service, a wellness-oriented atmosphere with yoga and tennis, and a boutique feel in San Jose del Cabo, and who are comfortable with a non-swimmable beach and a pool-focused stay.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Playa Mujeres benefits from the Yucatán's dry season, November through April, avoiding peak hurricane risk from August to October. Zoëtry Casa del Mar in Los Cabos is best visited October through June, when Baja's desert climate is mild and dry. Both properties command premium pricing over Christmas and New Year; shoulder months like November and early May offer the best balance of weather and value.","activities":"Dreams guests can golf on-site, snorkel in the Caribbean, use the waterpark and lazy river, and take day trips to Isla Mujeres or Cancún's hotel zone just south. Zoëtry guests can golf nearby at world-class Cabo courses, take yoga classes, play tennis, explore the charming art galleries and restaurants of San Jose del Cabo's historic town center, whale-watch from January through March, and arrange excursions to the famous Land's End arch at Cabo San Lucas."},"dreams-jade-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Jade Resort & Spa is a large family all-inclusive on Mexico's Caribbean coast in Puerto Morelos, with a kids club for under-4s, teen club, lazy river, adult pool, nightclub, archery, diving, fishing, babysitting, and restaurants that require no reservations. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a smaller, more refined Baja California family resort in San Jose del Cabo with a golf course, yoga, and a notably higher overall rating of 9.3 versus Dreams Jade's 8.8. The ratings tell a revealing story: Zoëtry leads on service (9.5 vs 8.8), cleanliness (9.4 vs 8.9), rooms (9.2 vs 8.6), food (8.2 vs 7.4), and atmosphere (8.0 vs 6.8), while Dreams Jade wins on sheer amenity breadth and family infrastructure. Both share weak beach scores — Dreams Jade at 4.8, Zoëtry at 3.5 — so neither is a beach destination. Dreams Jade is the activity-rich family machine; Zoëtry is the quieter, higher-quality boutique experience where polish and service outperform volume.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children who want a sprawling Caribbean Mexico all-inclusive with a kids club from infancy, teen club, lazy river, nightclub, diving, fishing, and a full entertainment program across large, well-priced rooms accommodating five or more guests.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and families with older children who prioritize exceptional service, spotless rooms, and refined dining over activity volume, and want a boutique Baja California setting near San Jose del Cabo with golf, yoga, and a noticeably more intimate atmosphere.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Jade in Puerto Morelos benefits from dry season visits between November and April to avoid Caribbean hurricane season and heavy summer humidity. Zoëtry Casa del Mar in Los Cabos is most comfortable October through June, sidestepping the hot, humid Baja summer and the late-summer hurricane window. Both resorts offer relatively stable winter pricing, though Zoëtry's shoulder seasons in spring and fall offer good value.","activities":"Dreams Jade guests can dive, fish, play tennis, cycle, and practice archery on-site, with the Mesoamerican Reef and Puerto Morelos village close by for snorkelling and local exploration. Zoëtry guests can golf, practice yoga, and play tennis, with San Jose del Cabo's art district, whale watching excursions from January to March, and East Cape sportfishing all accessible from the resort's well-rated location."},"dreams-vista-cancun-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Vista Cancun Golf & Spa Resort is a large family all-inclusive on the Cancun hotel strip with a flowrider, waterpark for little kids, teen club, arcade, nightclub, diving, windsurfing, and babysitting across an expansive amenity set at a lively beach destination. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a boutique, quieter all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with a swim-up bar, tennis, and a notably smaller amenity footprint, but it outperforms Dreams Vista on nearly every quality metric: overall rating 9.3 vs 8.9, food 8.2 vs 7.6, atmosphere 8.0 vs 7.1, service 9.5 vs 9.0, and cleanliness 9.4 vs 9.2. Dreams Vista's beach scores slightly higher (4.0 vs 3.5), though neither resort excels on that front. Dreams Vista wins on breadth of programming and activity variety for families with children of all ages. Zoëtry wins on refinement, food quality, and a more intimate atmosphere at a comparable price tier. Choose Dreams Vista for activity-rich family chaos; choose Zoëtry for a polished, quieter Baja experience.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want maximum programming under one roof — flowrider, waterpark, teen club, arcade, diving, nightclub, and babysitting — in Cancun's well-connected hotel zone, without sacrificing strong room quality or value at the $$$ price level.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples or families with older children who prioritize exceptional service (9.5), superior food quality (8.2), and a calm boutique atmosphere over a packed activity schedule, set in the more characterful surroundings of San Jose del Cabo rather than Cancun's busier strip.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts sit in Mexico's peak winter window of December through April, when Caribbean humidity eases in Cancun and Los Cabos enjoys reliable sunshine with minimal rain. Cancun's hurricane season runs June through November, introducing meaningful weather risk. Los Cabos summer months bring occasional tropical storms but are generally drier and less volatile than the Caribbean side, making Zoëtry a marginally safer shoulder-season bet.","activities":"Dreams Vista guests can surf the flowrider, dive, windsurf, rent watersports equipment, play golf, take yoga, and catch evening entertainment or the nightclub on-site, all within easy reach of Cancun's shopping and nightlife. Zoëtry guests have golf, tennis, yoga, and a swim-up bar on property, with San Jose del Cabo's art district, world-class sport fishing, whale watching, and the famous Corridor golf courses a short drive away."},"dreams-dominicus-la-romana-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Dominicus La Romana and Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos are both four-dollar-sign family all-inclusives, but they diverge sharply in size, beach quality, and overall ratings. Zoëtry scores a commanding 9.3 overall versus Dreams' solid 8.7, with particularly striking gaps in service (9.5 vs 8.8), cleanliness (9.4 vs 8.9), food (8.2 vs 7.2), and room quality (9.2 vs 8.6). The most dramatic difference, however, is the beach: Dreams rates 7.8 while Zoëtry scores just 3.5, a reflection of Los Cabos' notoriously rough, non-swimmable Pacific surf. Dreams compensates with a far broader activity roster—kids club for under-4s, teen club, waterpark, diving, snorkelling, nightclub, and babysitting—making it a genuine family infrastructure resort. Zoëtry is a smaller, more refined boutique property with golf, tennis, a heated pool, and exceptional service scores, but without the children's programming depth. Dreams is the busier, more amenity-packed Dominican beach holiday; Zoëtry is the quieter, higher-quality Mexican retreat where polish matters more than facilities breadth.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a high-amenity Dominican Republic all-inclusive with a waterpark, kids and teen clubs, babysitting, diving, snorkelling, and a nightclub on a genuinely swimmable Bayahibe beach at strong value for the price tier.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples or families with older children who prioritize exceptional service, immaculate rooms, outstanding food, and a tranquil boutique atmosphere in San Jose del Cabo, and who are comfortable with a non-swimmable beach offset by a heated pool and proximity to Cabo's golf and activities.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Dominicus is best visited November through April to avoid Dominican hurricane season and peak humidity. Zoëtry Casa del Mar is most appealing October through June, when Los Cabos enjoys dry, sunny weather; July through September brings higher humidity and occasional tropical storm risk to Baja. Both resorts carry peak-season rate premiums over the Christmas and New Year holiday period.","activities":"At Dreams Dominicus, guests can dive and snorkel the reefs of Bayahibe, visit the nearby Saona Island on catamaran day trips, and explore Altos de Chavón's colonial-replica village a short drive away. At Zoëtry Casa del Mar, guests can golf, play tennis, take whale-watching excursions (December through April), sport-fish the Sea of Cortez, and explore the galleries and restaurants of San Jose del Cabo's historic town center minutes away."},"breathless-punta-cana-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Breathless Punta Cana is a lively adults-only Dominican Republic all-inclusive on the Punta Cana coast, loaded with nightlife-oriented amenities: a casino, nightclub, lazy river, diving, snorkelling, and swim-up bar. Zoëtry Casa del Mar is a quieter, family-friendly boutique all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with a heated pool, yoga, golf access, and an intimate atmosphere focused on wellness and service. The numbers tell a clear story: Zoëtry leads on overall rating (9.3 vs 8.8), food (8.2 vs 7.6), rooms (9.2 vs 8.6), service (9.5 vs 8.9), cleanliness (9.4 vs 9.0), and value (8.8 vs 8.4). Breathless edges ahead only on beach (6.5 vs 3.5, though both underperform here) and pool atmosphere. Zoëtry's beach score of 3.5 is a significant liability — Los Cabos is not a swimming beach destination — while Breathless offers genuine Caribbean beach access. If you want a high-energy adults-only Caribbean party resort with a nightclub and casino, choose Breathless. If you want a refined, service-obsessed boutique experience in Baja California with superior rooms and food, choose Zoëtry.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults who want a high-energy, nightlife-forward Dominican Republic all-inclusive with a casino, nightclub, lazy river, diving, and a genuine Caribbean beach. Best suited to groups or couples who prioritise entertainment programming and a lively atmosphere over polished service and room quality.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families and couples who prioritise exceptional service, beautifully appointed rooms, and refined dining over beach access. Ideal for guests drawn to Baja California's desert-meets-sea landscape, wellness programming, and an intimate boutique atmosphere — and who understand Los Cabos is not a traditional swimming beach destination.","whenToVisit":"Breathless Punta Cana suits travel from December through April, when Dominican Republic weather is driest and the Caribbean is at its calmest; avoid hurricane season (August–October). Zoëtry Casa del Mar is best visited October through June, when Baja California's desert climate is mild and dry; July and August bring heat and occasional tropical moisture, though the resort's heated pool keeps things comfortable year-round.","activities":"At Breathless Punta Cana, guests can snorkel, dive, play tennis, use the lazy river and swim-up bar, and enjoy casino nights and a nightclub on one of the Caribbean's most activity-dense resort strips. At Zoëtry Casa del Mar, guests access yoga classes, a golf course, spa treatments, and evening entertainment, with the historic art galleries, restaurants, and boutiques of San Jose del Cabo's town centre a short drive away."},"dreams-estrella-del-mar-mazatlan-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Estrella del Mar Mazatlán is a large Mexican family all-inclusive on the Pacific coast with a waterpark, lazy river, kids club for under-4s, babysitting, and buffet dining at a property that scores strongly on rooms (9.5), cleanliness (9.4), and service (9.2), with a beach rating of 6.8 and food at 7.6. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a boutique San José del Cabo all-inclusive with tennis, a more refined food score (8.2), stronger atmosphere (8.0), and top-tier service (9.5), but a strikingly low beach rating of 3.5 — typical of Los Cabos where swimming conditions are often unsafe. Dreams Mazatlán wins on family infrastructure: waterparks, lazy river, kids club, and babysitting give it clear advantages for young families. Zoëtry wins on food, atmosphere, and service refinement in a quieter boutique setting. If you want a full-featured family all-inclusive on a swimmable Pacific beach with waterparks and kids programming, choose Dreams Mazatlán. If you want a polished, intimate Los Cabos boutique experience with superior dining and service and don't need a beach for swimming, choose Zoëtry Casa del Mar.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children who want a feature-rich Mexican Pacific all-inclusive with a waterpark, lazy river, kids club from infancy, babysitting, and a swimmable beach — all at a price point that delivers strong value scores.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples or families with older children who prioritize refined dining, exceptional service, and a boutique atmosphere in Los Cabos, and are comfortable with a beach that is scenic but not suitable for swimming.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Mazatlán is best visited November through April when Mazatlán's dry season keeps humidity low and rainfall rare. Zoëtry Los Cabos suits the same November-to-May window, avoiding the late-summer hurricane season that affects both Baja and Sinaloa coasts. Both resorts are busiest during U.S. holidays and spring break, when rates climb and availability tightens.","activities":"Dreams Mazatlán offers on-site golf, spa, yoga, waterparks, and lazy river, with Mazatlán's historic Old Town and Malecón boardwalk nearby. Zoëtry Los Cabos offers golf, tennis, spa, and yoga on-site, with the famous El Arco rock arch, whale watching (December–April), sport fishing, and the galleries and restaurants of San José del Cabo's art district all within easy reach."},"dreams-karibana-cartagena-golf-and-spa-resort-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Karibana Cartagena is a large Colombian family all-inclusive on the Caribbean coast with a kids club, babysitting, buffet, evening entertainment, pets allowed, and an on-site golf course, priced at the upper-mid tier and scoring well on rooms (9.0) and cleanliness (9.1) but notably weaker on food (7.0) and pool (6.9). Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a boutique Mexican all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with yoga, tennis, a swim-up bar, heated pool, and an adults-leaning intimate atmosphere, posting a higher overall score (9.3 vs 8.9) with standout marks for service (9.5), cleanliness (9.4), food (8.2), and atmosphere (8.0). Both resorts rate their beaches poorly (4.5 and 3.5 respectively), so neither suits beach-first travelers. Dreams Karibana wins on family infrastructure with a kids club and babysitting; Zoëtry wins decisively on dining, service, and refined atmosphere. If you want a full-service Colombian family all-inclusive with kids programming and golf, go to Dreams Karibana. If you want a polished boutique Los Cabos experience with superior food and service, go to Zoëtry Casa del Mar.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children who want a large Colombian all-inclusive with a dedicated kids club, babysitting, evening entertainment, and on-site golf in Cartagena, and can accept average food and pool ratings in exchange for strong room quality and overall value.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples or families with older children who prioritize exceptional service, superior dining, and a refined boutique atmosphere in Los Cabos, and value yoga, tennis, and a swim-up bar over dedicated kids programming.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Karibana in Cartagena is best visited December through April during Colombia's dry season, avoiding the heavier rains of October and November. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos suits travel from November through May, when Baja California Sur sees minimal rainfall and comfortable temperatures. Both resorts carry peak-season pricing over the Christmas and New Year holiday period.","activities":"Dreams Karibana guests can explore Cartagena's UNESCO-listed walled city, take boat trips to the Rosario Islands, and play on the resort's own golf course. Zoëtry Casa del Mar guests can access world-class sport fishing, whale watching from January to March, snorkeling at Cabo Pulmo National Park, ATV tours, and rounds at nearby championship golf courses in the Los Cabos corridor."},"dreams-macao-beach-punta-cana-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Macao Beach Punta Cana is a large Dominican Republic family all-inclusive on Macao Beach with a waterpark, lazy river, kids and teen clubs, nightclub, diving, snorkelling, archery, and restaurants requiring no reservations. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a smaller, more refined Mexican all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with a heated pool, spa, golf, and yoga, aimed at a quieter, more intimate experience. The ratings tell a clear story: Dreams edges ahead on beach (7.8 vs 3.5, a dramatic gap explained by Cabo's rough, non-swimmable Pacific surf), pool (7.4 vs 7.3), and activity breadth, while Zoëtry leads on food (8.2 vs 7.6), service (9.5 vs 9.0), cleanliness (9.4 vs 9.2), rooms (9.2 vs 9.0), and overall score (9.3 vs 9.0). Dreams is the choice for families who need waterslides, babysitting, and a swimmable beach; Zoëtry suits those who prioritize exceptional service and food in a boutique setting and can accept that ocean swimming is essentially off the table.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a large Dominican Republic all-inclusive on a swimmable beach with waterparks, a lazy river, kids and teen clubs, diving, snorkelling, and a nightclub, at a price point that delivers strong value across a full suite of amenities.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples or families with older children who want a boutique, service-first Mexican all-inclusive near San Jose del Cabo, with top-rated food, a spa, golf, and a refined atmosphere, and who understand that the Pacific beach here is scenic but not swimmable.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Macao Beach is best from December through April when Dominican Republic weather is dry and settled; hurricane season runs June through November. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos benefits from Los Cabos' reliably dry, sunny climate year-round, though August and September bring occasional tropical storms. Both resorts carry premium pricing in the December–January holiday window.","activities":"At Dreams Macao, guests can dive, snorkel, kayak, play tennis and archery, ride the lazy river, and use waterparks, with Macao Beach and nearby Indigenous Eyes Ecological Park adding excursion options. At Zoëtry Casa del Mar, guests can play golf, practice yoga, use the spa, and take excursions to the famous El Arco rock formation, whale watching trips (December–April), and the galleries and restaurants of San Jose del Cabo's art district."},"dreams-vallarta-bay-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Vallarta Bay and Zoëtry Casa del Mar are both four-dollar-sign Mexican family all-inclusives, but they differ sharply in size, amenity depth, and beach quality. Dreams scores higher on beach (6.0 vs. 3.5), which matters given Zoëtry's notoriously rough Baja surf making its beachfront largely unswimmable. Dreams compensates with a deeper activity stack: kids club, teen club, pool slide, diving, fishing, nightclub, babysitting, and a buffet where reservations aren't required — all calibrated for active families. Zoëtry counters with meaningfully better food (8.2 vs. 7.5), superior rooms (9.2 vs. 8.8), cleaner property (9.4 vs. 9.0), and noticeably stronger service (9.5 vs. 9.0). Its overall score of 9.3 edges Dreams' 8.9, reflecting a more refined, boutique experience. Dreams wins on pool energy and entertainment programming; Zoëtry wins on intimacy, culinary quality, and polished service. Dreams suits families who want a lively, activity-rich Pacific coast resort; Zoëtry suits those prioritizing a quieter, higher-quality stay near San José del Cabo despite the beach trade-off.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children and teenagers who want a lively Puerto Vallarta all-inclusive packed with kids clubs, a teen club, pool slide, diving, fishing, nightclub, and evening entertainment on a swimmable beach — and no reservation headaches at restaurants.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and families with older children who prioritize exceptional service, superior rooms, and refined dining in a quieter boutique setting near San José del Cabo, and who won't miss a swimmable beach in exchange for a more polished, intimate all-inclusive experience.","whenToVisit":"Puerto Vallarta's dry season runs November through April, with peak crowds December to March — shoulder months like November and April offer good weather with fewer guests. Los Cabos is drier year-round but faces hurricane risk July through October; November through May delivers the most reliable conditions. Both resorts share Mexico's high-season premium pricing around Christmas and spring break.","activities":"Dreams guests can dive, fish, play tennis, and use the pool slide on-site, with Puerto Vallarta's Malecón, whale watching (December–March), and zip-line tours nearby. Zoëtry guests have on-site golf, yoga, tennis, and spa access, with San José del Cabo's art district, Cabo San Lucas whale watching, sport fishing charters, and ATV desert excursions all within easy reach."},"secrets-riviera-cancun-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Riviera Cancun is an adults-only all-inclusive on Mexico's Caribbean coast in the Caracol area, with a nightclub, buffet, swim-up bar, and evening entertainment geared toward a lively, social atmosphere. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly all-inclusive on the Pacific side in San Jose del Cabo, with a heated pool, golf, yoga, tennis, and a quieter, wellness-oriented identity. Zoëtry outscores Secrets on nearly every rated dimension: overall 9.3 vs 8.6, food 8.2 vs 7.7, service 9.5 vs 9.1, cleanliness 9.4 vs 9.2, and value 8.8 vs 8.4. Both properties have beach access, but neither scores strongly there, with Secrets rating 4.8 and Zoëtry even lower at 3.5, reflecting the rough surf typical of Los Cabos. Secrets edges ahead on room ratings 9.0 vs 9.2 only narrowly, and its nightclub and no-reservation dining add social convenience that Zoëtry lacks. Zoëtry is the more refined, higher-performing property overall; Secrets is the livelier, adults-only Caribbean option.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples or groups who want a lively Caribbean all-inclusive on Mexico's Riviera Maya with a nightclub, swim-up bar, evening entertainment, and the flexibility of no-reservation dining, prioritizing social energy and an overall solid experience at a competitive luxury price point.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families or couples seeking a quieter, wellness-focused all-inclusive on the Pacific side of Mexico, where exceptional service ratings, golf, yoga, tennis, and a heated pool matter more than nightlife, and where superior food and value scores justify the Los Cabos setting.","whenToVisit":"Secrets Riviera Cancun benefits from the Yucatan's dry season, November through April, when heat is manageable and hurricane risk is low. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos enjoys reliable sunshine much of the year, though September brings occasional tropical storms to Baja. Both resorts are at their most comfortable and least crowded outside of major US school holidays.","activities":"Secrets Riviera Cancun guests can access the Riviera Maya's cenotes, Mayan ruins at Tulum and Cobá, and watersports along the Caribbean coast. Zoëtry Casa del Mar sits near San Jose del Cabo's art district, world-class sport fishing, whale watching from January through March, and multiple championship golf courses, with the dramatic Land's End rock formation a short drive away."},"secrets-baby-beach-aruba-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Baby Beach Aruba is an adults-only all-inclusive on Aruba's southeastern tip near San Nicolas, built around one of the Caribbean's most sheltered natural beaches, with strong scores across beach (8.5), rooms (9.4), cleanliness (9.5), and service (9.3). Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly luxury all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo, Mexico, with an exceptional overall rating (9.3 vs. 8.6), outstanding service (9.5), and a superior location score (9.0 vs. 8.4), but a strikingly low beach rating (3.5) reflecting the notoriously rough, non-swimmable Pacific surf at Los Cabos. Secrets edges ahead on beach quality and pool (8.0 vs. 7.3), while Zoëtry leads on overall score, location, value (8.8 vs. 8.5), and amenity depth — offering a heated pool, swim-up bar, yoga, tennis, golf, and evening entertainment that Secrets lacks. If you want a calm-water Caribbean beach experience in an adults-only setting, choose Secrets Baby Beach. If you want a high-rated luxury family resort in Baja with exceptional service and rich amenities but no swimmable beach, choose Zoëtry Casa del Mar.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples or solo travelers who want a serene Caribbean retreat anchored by a genuinely swimmable natural beach, excellent rooms and service, and a relaxed atmosphere without the complexity of a large amenity-heavy resort.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families or couples who prioritize exceptional overall quality, service, and a broad amenity lineup — heated pool, yoga, tennis, golf — over beach access, and who are drawn to the dramatic Baja landscape of San Jose del Cabo at a premium price point.","whenToVisit":"Aruba sits outside the hurricane belt, making Secrets Baby Beach a reliable year-round destination with consistent sunshine and trade winds; December through April is peak season. Los Cabos is best visited October through June, avoiding the late-summer hurricane season and peak heat. Both resorts carry a premium in the December–January holiday window.","activities":"At Secrets Baby Beach, guests can snorkel the sheltered bay, explore Aruba's rugged San Nicolas art district, visit Arikok National Park, or arrange off-site watersports. At Zoëtry Casa del Mar, guests can practice yoga, play tennis, golf nearby courses, take excursions to the famous El Arco rock formation, whale-watch seasonally, or explore the charming galleries and restaurants of San Jose del Cabo's historic town center."},"dreams-riviera-cancun-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Riviera Cancun Resort & Spa is a large family all-inclusive on Mexico's Caribbean coast near Puerto Morelos, built around an extensive amenity set: kids club, teen club, lazy river, pool slide, diving, nightclub, babysitting, and no-reservation restaurants. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a smaller, more refined all-inclusive on the Pacific side in San Jose del Cabo, with golf, yoga, tennis, and a significantly higher service rating of 9.5 versus Dreams' already-strong 9.0. Zoëtry edges out Dreams on nearly every quality metric — overall 9.3 vs 8.8, food 8.2 vs 7.5, rooms 9.2 vs 8.7, cleanliness 9.4 vs 9.1 — but Dreams dominates on family infrastructure and entertainment programming. Both score poorly on beach (Dreams 4.8, Zoëtry 3.5), a known limitation of each location. Dreams is the better-value family activity hub; Zoëtry is the quieter, more polished retreat where service and room quality are the headline. If you want a Caribbean-side Mexican family all-inclusive with a lazy river, nightclub, and kids club, choose Dreams. If you want a refined Pacific-side retreat with exceptional service, golf, and yoga, choose Zoëtry.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with children of all ages who want a full-featured Caribbean Mexico all-inclusive with a kids club, teen club, lazy river, pool slide, nightclub, diving, and babysitting — all without worrying about restaurant reservations or managing a quiet, boutique atmosphere.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples or families with older children who want a refined, quieter Los Cabos all-inclusive where exceptional service (9.5), superior room quality (9.2), yoga, tennis, and golf take priority over waterslides and entertainment programming.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Riviera Cancun benefits from the Yucatan's dry season, November through April, when humidity drops and hurricane risk disappears. Zoëtry Casa del Mar in Los Cabos enjoys a drier, desert-influenced climate year-round, though late summer through October brings occasional tropical storms to both coasts. Winter and spring are the safest windows for either resort.","activities":"Dreams guests can dive the Caribbean reef, ride the lazy river, use the pool slide, and join evening entertainment or nightclub programming, with Puerto Morelos' protected reef reserve nearby for snorkelling excursions. Zoëtry guests can play golf, take yoga classes, and use tennis courts on-site, while San Jose del Cabo's art district, sport fishing, and whale-watching excursions (December through April) are all accessible from the property."},"dreams-aventuras-riviera-maya-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Aventuras Riviera Maya is a large family all-inclusive in Puerto Aventuras on the Riviera Maya with a waterpark for both small and big kids, an arcade, two kids clubs (including one for under-4s), diving, snorkelling, babysitting, and a swim-up bar. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a smaller, more refined family-friendly all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with a golf course, tennis, and notably higher ratings across food (8.2 vs 7), atmosphere (8 vs 6.9), rooms (9.2 vs 8.6), cleanliness (9.4 vs 8.9), and service (9.5 vs 9). Both sit at the same price level, but Zoëtry delivers a quieter, more polished experience while Dreams offers the broader activity infrastructure families with young children need. Beach scores are low at both, though Zoëtry's is significantly lower (3.5 vs 5.3), reflecting Los Cabos's famously rough Pacific surf. Dreams wins on sheer family programming; Zoëtry wins on quality and refinement across nearly every rated dimension.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children who want a full-service Riviera Maya all-inclusive with a waterpark, kids clubs starting from infancy, babysitting, diving, snorkelling, and evening entertainment — prioritising activity breadth over overall polish.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families or couples who want a refined, quieter Los Cabos all-inclusive with standout service, exceptional cleanliness, better food, and access to golf and tennis — and who won't miss a swimmable beach or an elaborate kids waterpark.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts are in Mexico but in different climate zones. The Riviera Maya around Puerto Aventuras is best November through April, avoiding hurricane season (June–October) and peak summer humidity. Los Cabos enjoys more year-round sunshine, though September and October bring occasional tropical storms. Winter and spring are the sweet spot for both, with December through March being the most reliable across either destination.","activities":"At Dreams Aventuras, guests can dive and snorkel directly from the Puerto Aventuras marina, explore the resort's waterparks, or visit nearby Tulum ruins and cenotes. At Zoëtry Casa del Mar, guests can play golf and tennis on-site, explore the charming streets and galleries of San Jose del Cabo's art district, take whale-watching excursions (December–April), or head to Cabo San Lucas for sport fishing and nightlife."},"dreams-rose-hall-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Rose Hall Resort and Spa is a mid-market Jamaican family all-inclusive in Montego Bay with a kids club, teen club, lazy river, nightclub, babysitting, and a lively entertainment program on a beach rated 6.0. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a premium boutique Mexican all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with yoga, a heated pool, room service, and free Wi-Fi, rated dramatically higher across almost every metric: overall 9.3 vs 8.5, food 8.2 vs 7.4, rooms 9.2 vs 8.2, service 9.5 vs 8.7, and cleanliness 9.4 vs 8.7. The beach gap is striking in the other direction: Dreams scores 6.0 while Zoëtry scores just 3.5, reflecting Los Cabos's rocky Pacific shoreline versus Jamaica's Caribbean beachfront. Dreams is the better choice for active families who want kids programming, a lazy river, and nightlife at a lower price point. Zoëtry is the better choice for guests who prioritize immaculate rooms, exceptional service, and refined dining and can accept a non-swimming beach in exchange for a significantly more polished, intimate resort experience.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children and teenagers who want a lively Jamaican all-inclusive with a kids club, teen club, lazy river, nightclub, and babysitting at a mid-market price, and for whom an actual swimmable Caribbean beach is a priority.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples or families with older children who want a premium, boutique Mexican all-inclusive in Los Cabos with exceptional service, beautifully appointed rooms, yoga, and refined dining, and who can forgo a swimmable beach in favor of a far more polished and intimate atmosphere.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Rose Hall is best visited November through mid-December or January through April to avoid Jamaica's hurricane season peak and summer humidity. Zoëtry Casa del Mar suits travel from October through June, when Los Cabos's desert climate is dry and mild. Both resorts see higher prices and crowds over the Christmas and New Year holiday period.","activities":"At Dreams Rose Hall, guests can golf, play tennis, snorkel the Caribbean, and explore Montego Bay's Hip Strip, Dunn's River Falls, and river rafting excursions nearby. At Zoëtry Casa del Mar, guests can practice yoga, play golf and tennis, take spa treatments, and venture out to Cabo San Lucas for whale watching, sport fishing, and the famous El Arco rock formation."},"zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos-vs-zoetry-marigot-bay-st-lucia":{"keyDifferences":"Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a luxury Mexican all-inclusive on the Sea of Cortez in San Jose del Cabo, with a heated pool, golf, yoga, tennis, swim-up bar, and evening entertainment, earning standout scores for service (9.5), cleanliness (9.4), and room quality (9.2). Its beach rating of 3.5 reflects the notoriously rough surf typical of Los Cabos. Zoëtry Marigot Bay St. Lucia sits in the dramatic natural harbour of Marigot Bay, offering fishing, babysitting, a swim-up bar, and spa in a lush rainforest setting, with a similarly low beach score of 2.5 but stronger marks for atmosphere (8.6 vs 8.0), food (8.6 vs 8.2), and sleep quality (9.2 vs 8.6). Casa del Mar edges ahead overall (9.3 vs 8.6) and on room rating (9.2 vs 8.8), while Marigot Bay counters with richer natural surroundings and babysitting. Neither property delivers a classic swim beach, so guests at both should arrive expecting pools and scenery over surf.","whoShouldChooseA":"Couples and families who want a polished, amenity-rich Mexican luxury all-inclusive with golf, tennis, yoga, and evening entertainment in San Jose del Cabo, and who prioritise exceptional service and room quality over a swimmable beach.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families with young children or couples who want a boutique St. Lucian all-inclusive tucked inside the lush, iconic Marigot Bay, valuing dramatic natural scenery, babysitting, and a quieter atmosphere over a broad activity roster.","whenToVisit":"Los Cabos is best from November through May, avoiding the late-summer hurricane season and peak heat. St. Lucia's dry season runs January through April, though its lush setting means some rain year-round. Both resorts command premium pricing in peak winter months, with modest shoulder-season savings available in late spring.","activities":"At Casa del Mar, guests can play golf, take yoga classes, use the tennis courts, and explore the art galleries and restaurants of San Jose del Cabo town minutes away. At Marigot Bay, fishing charters, spa treatments, and sailing excursions into St. Lucia's waters are the draws, with the Pitons, rainforest hikes, and the island's volcanic sulphur springs accessible by boat or road."},"breathless-montego-bay-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Breathless Montego Bay is an adults-only Jamaican all-inclusive in Montego Bay with a nightclub, swim-up bar, buffet, evening entertainment, spa, and gym at a lively, social price point. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a quieter, family-friendly Mexican all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with a heated pool, golf, yoga, spa, room service, and notably superior service and cleanliness ratings. Zoëtry outscores Breathless across nearly every measured category: overall (9.3 vs 8.5), food (8.2 vs 7.5), room (9.2 vs 8.7), service (9.5 vs 8.7), cleanliness (9.4 vs 8.9), and value (8.8 vs 8.3). Both resorts struggle with beach quality — Zoëtry scores a low 3.5 versus Breathless's already modest 5.5, reflecting Los Cabos's rough Pacific surf versus Montego Bay's calmer but unremarkable shoreline. Breathless edges ahead on atmosphere for guests who want a nightclub and party-oriented energy. Zoëtry is the stronger overall resort by the numbers, while Breathless suits those prioritising nightlife and a Jamaican adults-only setting.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults seeking a lively, party-forward Jamaican all-inclusive with a nightclub, evening entertainment, and swim-up bar energy in Montego Bay. Best suited to groups or couples who want social atmosphere and strong location access to MBJ airport rather than the highest marks for food or service.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families or couples who prioritise exceptional service (9.5), immaculate rooms (9.2), and a refined, tranquil atmosphere in San Jose del Cabo. Ideal for guests who value wellness amenities like yoga and heated pool, and who understand that Los Cabos beaches are not suited for swimming.","whenToVisit":"Breathless Montego Bay is best visited November through mid-December or January through April to avoid Jamaica's hurricane season peak. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos benefits from Los Cabos's more consistently dry climate, with October through May offering the most stable conditions. Both resorts carry a $$$ premium, so shoulder months in spring offer better availability and pricing.","activities":"Breathless guests can explore Montego Bay's Hip Strip, Doctor's Cave Beach, and nearby Dunn's River Falls, with on-site tennis, spa, gym, and nightclub. Zoëtry guests have access to on-site golf, yoga, heated pool, spa, and tennis, with San Jose del Cabo's art district, galleries, and Los Cabos corridor excursions — including whale watching from January through March — a short drive away."},"breathless-riviera-cancun-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Breathless Riviera Cancun is an adults-only all-inclusive on Mexico's Caribbean coast in Caracol, built around nightlife, a swim-up bar, buffet, and evening entertainment with a strong room score (8.9) and cleanliness (9.1) but a notably weak beach rating (4.8) and middling food score (7.6). Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly all-inclusive on the Pacific side in San Jose del Cabo, where service (9.5), cleanliness (9.4), and rooms (9.2) all outperform Breathless across the board, and food scores meaningfully higher at 8.2. Zoëtry also leads on overall rating 9.3 versus 8.8 and value 8.8 versus 8.4, despite a similarly premium price point. Neither property delivers an exceptional beach, but Zoëtry's 3.5 beach score trails even Breathless's already-low 4.8. Breathless wins on atmosphere-driven nightlife and an unrestricted dining format, while Zoëtry wins on quieter luxury, wellness programming including yoga and tennis, and consistent top-tier service. Choose Breathless for Caribbean energy and party atmosphere; choose Zoëtry for refined, service-led Pacific Mexico tranquility.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples or friend groups who want a lively Caribbean Mexico all-inclusive with a nightclub, swim-up bar, and no-reservation dining in a high-energy atmosphere. Best suited to guests who prioritize nightlife and convenience over exceptional food or a world-class beach.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families and couples who value exceptional service and refined, wellness-oriented surroundings over party atmosphere. Ideal for guests willing to forgo a great beach in exchange for top-rated rooms, consistently outstanding staff, yoga, tennis, golf access, and a calmer Pacific Mexico setting in San Jose del Cabo.","whenToVisit":"Breathless Riviera Cancun sits in the Caribbean hurricane belt, making November through April the most reliable window with lower humidity and minimal storm risk. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos enjoys a drier, more stable climate year-round, though Los Cabos can see late-summer tropical storms. October through June is the sweet spot for Zoëtry, with cooler temperatures and clear skies.","activities":"Breathless guests can access Cancun's hotel zone for water sports, cenote tours, Mayan ruins at Chichen Itza or Tulum, and marina excursions, plus on-site evening entertainment and nightclub programming. Zoëtry guests in San Jose del Cabo can explore the historic Art District, world-class sportfishing, whale watching from January through March, championship golf courses, and the vibrant Cabo San Lucas marina just a short drive away."},"secrets-wild-orchid-montego-bay-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Wild Orchid Montego Bay is an adults-only Jamaican all-inclusive on Montego Bay with a nightclub, casino, lazy river, diving, and swim-up bar in a lively, entertainment-forward setting. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly boutique all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo, Mexico, built around exceptional service (9.5 vs. 8.9), superior rooms (9.2 vs. 8.9), and a quieter, wellness-oriented atmosphere with yoga, a heated pool, and golf access. The most striking gap is beach: Secrets scores a respectable 6.8 while Zoëtry's beach rates a poor 3.5, reflecting the rocky, non-swimmable Pacific coastline typical of Los Cabos. Zoëtry leads on overall rating (9.3 vs. 8.6), cleanliness (9.4 vs. 9.0), and value (8.8 vs. 8.4), while Secrets wins on nightlife, diving, and a more energetic resort atmosphere. Secrets is for adults who want entertainment and a Caribbean beach; Zoëtry is for guests who prioritize service, room quality, and tranquility over beach access.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult couples and groups who want a lively Caribbean all-inclusive with a nightclub, casino, lazy river, diving, and swim-up bar on a genuine Jamaican beach. Best for those who value entertainment and atmosphere over pristine service polish.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families and couples who prioritize exceptional service, beautifully appointed rooms, and a calm, wellness-oriented atmosphere in Mexico's Los Cabos. Ideal for guests who don't require a swimmable beach and value tranquility, cleanliness, and boutique-resort attentiveness above nightlife.","whenToVisit":"Secrets Wild Orchid benefits from Jamaica's driest months of December through April, avoiding the Atlantic hurricane season peak of August through October. Zoëtry Casa del Mar is best visited October through June, when Los Cabos sees minimal rainfall and comfortable temperatures; July through September brings humidity, occasional tropical storms, and the highest risk of hurricane activity on the Pacific side.","activities":"At Secrets Wild Orchid, guests can dive directly from the resort, enjoy the casino and nightclub, float the lazy river, or explore Montego Bay's Hip Strip, Luminous Lagoon, and Dunn's River Falls nearby. At Zoëtry Casa del Mar, guests can practice yoga, access nearby golf courses, use the spa, and explore San Jose del Cabo's art galleries, local markets, and the stunning natural arch at Land's End by boat excursion."},"breathless-cancun-soul-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Breathless Cancun Soul Resort & Spa is an adults-only all-inclusive on Mexico's Caribbean coast near Puerto Morelos, oriented around nightlife, a swim-up bar, evening entertainment, and a lively beach atmosphere. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly boutique all-inclusive on the Pacific side in San Jose del Cabo, built around wellness, with yoga, tennis, golf, a heated pool, and exceptional service scoring 9.5 versus Breathless's 8.8. The trade-off is stark on beach quality: Breathless scores 7.8 while Zoëtry's Pacific-facing beach rates a very low 3.5, typical of Los Cabos where rough surf limits swimming. Zoëtry outperforms Breathless on overall rating (9.3 vs 8.4), food (8.2 vs 7.6), service, and value (8.8 vs 8.3), while Breathless leads on pool score marginally and brings a nightclub and buffet Zoëtry lacks. Breathless suits guests who want a Caribbean beach and party-forward adults-only energy; Zoëtry suits those prioritizing refined service, wellness, and a boutique atmosphere regardless of swimmable beach.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples or groups who want a lively Caribbean all-inclusive on Mexico's Riviera Maya with a swimmable beach, swim-up bar, nightclub, and evening entertainment at a competitive price point. Best for guests who want energy and a social atmosphere over boutique refinement.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families or wellness-focused couples who prioritize exceptional service, yoga, tennis, golf, and a boutique atmosphere in Los Cabos. Ideal guests are comfortable without a swimmable beach and value the intimate, polished Zoëtry experience over a party-oriented all-inclusive environment.","whenToVisit":"Breathless Cancun is best November through April when Caribbean humidity drops and hurricane risk is minimal; summer months bring heat and storm exposure. Zoëtry Los Cabos suits visits October through June, avoiding late-summer hurricane season on the Pacific side. Both resorts sit in Mexico's premium price window over Christmas and New Year, so booking well in advance is advisable for either property during peak holidays.","activities":"Breathless guests have access to the Caribbean for swimming and watersports, a nightclub, spa, and evening entertainment programs on the Riviera Maya. Zoëtry guests can pursue yoga, tennis, and golf on-site, with the boutique town of San Jose del Cabo and its art district walkable nearby. Both resorts offer spa treatments and swim-up bars; guests at either can arrange off-site excursions, with Cancun's cenotes and Mayan ruins or Cabo's whale watching and sport fishing as respective regional highlights."},"dreams-playa-esmeralda-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Playa Esmeralda is a family-focused Dominican Republic all-inclusive in El Cedro with a strong beach rating of 8.3, dedicated kids and teen clubs, babysitting, and a buffet-forward dining setup that scores 7.6 on food. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a boutique Mexican all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with a near-unusable beach rated 3.5, but it compensates with superior food (8.2), a swim-up bar, yoga, tennis, golf, and the highest service rating of the two at 9.5 versus Dreams' 9.2. Dreams leans heavily on family infrastructure and a genuinely swimmable Caribbean beach, while Zoëtry trades beach access for refined atmosphere (8.0 vs 7.5) and culinary quality in a more intimate setting. If you want a Caribbean family all-inclusive with a real beach, structured kids programming, and babysitting at a competitive price, Dreams Playa Esmeralda delivers. If you want a polished Mexican boutique all-inclusive with exceptional service, better food, yoga, and golf, and you can accept that the beach is effectively off the table, Zoëtry Casa del Mar is the stronger pick.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children who need dedicated kids and teen clubs, babysitting, and a real swimmable beach as the centrepiece of their holiday. The Dominican Republic's El Cedro setting and strong cleanliness and room scores make it a reliable, high-value Caribbean choice.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and families with older children who prioritise exceptional service, better dining, yoga, tennis, and golf over beach access. Guests who want a refined, boutique atmosphere in Los Cabos and are content spending pool time rather than ocean time will find Zoëtry Casa del Mar the more polished option.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Playa Esmeralda is best visited November through April, avoiding the Dominican Republic's Atlantic hurricane season which peaks August to October. Zoëtry Casa del Mar in Los Cabos is most reliably sunny October through June; late summer brings occasional tropical storms to Baja California Sur, though the region sees far fewer hurricanes than the Caribbean. Both resorts are at their busiest and most expensive over the Christmas and New Year period.","activities":"At Dreams Playa Esmeralda guests centre their days on the Caribbean beach, kids club, and teen programming, with spa treatments rounding out the schedule. Zoëtry Casa del Mar offers yoga classes, a heated swim-up pool, tennis, and access to nearby golf courses as the main activity anchors given the unusable beach. Both resorts sit near towns worth exploring: El Cedro is close to Higuey, while San Jose del Cabo's charming art-district town centre is easily accessible from Zoëtry."},"secrets-mirabel-cancun-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Mirabel Cancún is an adults-only all-inclusive on Mexico's Caribbean coast with a swim-up bar, buffet, evening entertainment, snorkelling, and spa, scoring 7.3 for beach and 7.5 for pool but excelling in sleep quality (9.2) and cleanliness (9.3). Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly all-inclusive in San José del Cabo on the Pacific side, with a heated pool, yoga, tennis, golf course access, and spa, but a strikingly low beach rating of 3.5 — typical of Los Cabos' rough surf coastline — offset by a higher overall score (9.3 vs 8.7), stronger service (9.5 vs 9.1), and better value (8.8 vs 8.6). Secrets Mirabel is the clear choice for Caribbean beachgoing and snorkelling in a livelier adults-only setting, while Zoëtry Casa del Mar suits guests who prioritise service, wellness, and Baja atmosphere over swimmable beach. If you want a Caribbean adults-only all-inclusive with actual beach and water activities, go to Secrets Mirabel. If you want a refined, family-welcoming Baja all-inclusive with exceptional service and wellness programming, go to Zoëtry Casa del Mar.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult couples and groups who want a Caribbean all-inclusive with a swimmable beach, snorkelling, swim-up bar, and evening entertainment in Cancún — a more active, beach-forward experience at a strong value for the luxury tier.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families or wellness-focused couples who prioritise exceptional service, yoga, tennis, and golf in a serene Baja setting, and won't be deterred by a beach that's scenic but unsuitable for swimming.","whenToVisit":"Secrets Mirabel Cancún is best visited November through April, avoiding hurricane season and summer humidity on the Caribbean coast. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos suits year-round travel, with October through May being ideal — Los Cabos sees very little rain, though summer months bring higher humidity and the occasional tropical storm to the Baja peninsula.","activities":"At Secrets Mirabel, guests can snorkel the Caribbean, use the swim-up bar, and explore Cancún's Hotel Zone, with Isla Mujeres day trips and Mayan ruins at Chichén Itzá within reach. At Zoëtry Casa del Mar, guests can practise yoga, play tennis, access nearby golf courses, and explore San José del Cabo's art district and weekly gallery walks, with whale watching and sportfishing available seasonally offshore."},"secrets-st-james-montego-bay-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets St. James Montego Bay is an adults-only Jamaican all-inclusive on Montego Bay with a casino, nightclub, diving, swim-up bar, and no-reservation restaurants, rated 8.5 overall with strong service (8.9) and cleanliness (9.0) but a notably weak beach score (6.8) and modest pool rating (7.2). Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly Mexican boutique all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo rated 9.3 overall, with exceptional service (9.5), cleanliness (9.4), and room quality (9.2), but a severely low beach score (3.5) reflecting Los Cabos's notoriously non-swimmable Pacific surf. Secrets edges out on entertainment variety with a casino and nightclub; Zoëtry counters with golf, yoga, and a quieter, more refined atmosphere. Secrets scores higher on beach relative to Zoëtry, but neither property is a true beach destination. If you want an adults-only Jamaican all-inclusive with lively nightlife, casino, and dining flexibility in Montego Bay, choose Secrets St. James. If you want a polished, family-welcome Mexican boutique resort with outstanding service and rooms near San Jose del Cabo, choose Zoëtry Casa del Mar.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult couples and groups who want a lively Jamaican all-inclusive with a casino, nightclub, diving, and flexible dining in Montego Bay. Those prioritizing entertainment variety and a well-rounded activities program over a pristine beach or ultra-refined atmosphere will feel at home here.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families and couples seeking a quiet, boutique-style Mexican all-inclusive near San Jose del Cabo where exceptional service, immaculate rooms, and a peaceful atmosphere take priority. Guests who plan to explore Cabo's town and culture rather than rely on a swimmable beach will get the most out of Zoëtry.","whenToVisit":"Secrets St. James is best visited December through April, when Jamaica's dry season delivers reliable sunshine and low humidity. Zoëtry Casa del Mar suits the same winter window, avoiding Los Cabos's hurricane-adjacent late-summer heat. Both resorts see peak pricing over Christmas and New Year; shoulder months like November or early December offer the best balance of weather and value at either property.","activities":"At Secrets St. James, guests can dive, play tennis, hit the casino, and enjoy nightly entertainment without leaving the resort, while Montego Bay's Hip Strip, Rose Hall Great House, and river rafting on the Great River are close by. At Zoëtry Casa del Mar, yoga, golf, and spa treatments anchor the on-site experience, and guests can easily explore San Jose del Cabo's art district, the iconic Arch at Land's End, and sport-fishing charters from the nearby marina."},"dreams-sands-cancun-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Sands Cancun is a large family all-inclusive on the Mexican Caribbean with a kids club, lazy river, buffet, and a beach rated 6.5, sitting on Cancun's busy Hotel Zone strip. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a boutique San Jose del Cabo all-inclusive with a heated pool, spa, yoga, tennis, swim-up bar, and golf access, rated significantly higher across nearly every dimension — overall 9.3 vs 8.5, food 8.2 vs 6.9, rooms 9.2 vs 7.8, and service 9.5 vs 8.7 — but with a beach rated just 3.5, typical of the Pacific Los Cabos coastline where swimming is often unsafe due to currents. Dreams Sands wins on beach accessibility and family infrastructure — kids clubs for under-4s, a lazy river, no-reservation dining — while Zoëtry Casa del Mar dominates on refinement, cleanliness (9.4 vs 8.5), and sleep quality (8.6 vs 8.1). If you want a lively Cancun Caribbean family resort with young-child amenities and a swimmable beach, choose Dreams Sands. If you want a quieter, more polished boutique experience in Los Cabos with exceptional service and rooms, choose Zoëtry Casa del Mar.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children, including toddlers, who want a Caribbean all-inclusive with a swimmable beach, lazy river, dedicated kids club for under-4s, and easy no-reservation dining in Cancun's well-connected Hotel Zone.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and families with older children who prioritize room quality, immaculate cleanliness, and exceptional service over beach swimming, and who appreciate a quieter, boutique atmosphere in Los Cabos with spa, yoga, and golf nearby.","whenToVisit":"Cancun's peak season runs December through April, with dry sunny weather and calm Caribbean waters — avoid hurricane season from August through October. Los Cabos is a year-round destination with more than 350 sunny days annually; summer months bring warmer temperatures and occasional tropical moisture, while winter and spring offer the most reliable, comfortable conditions for both resorts.","activities":"Dreams Sands guests enjoy Cancun's Hotel Zone nightlife, shopping at Plaza La Isla, snorkeling day trips to Isla Mujeres, and ATV or cenote excursions inland. Zoëtry Casa del Mar guests can access nearby San Jose del Cabo's art gallery district, whale watching from January through March, sport fishing, ATV dune rides, and the resort's own tennis courts, yoga classes, and spa treatments without leaving the property."},"dreams-sapphire-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Sapphire Resort & Spa is a large family all-inclusive on Mexico's Caribbean coast near Puerto Morelos, with a kids club, teen club, babysitting, diving, snorkelling, fishing, nightclub, and walk-up restaurants in a lively resort atmosphere. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a boutique Pacific-coast all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with a heated pool, golf course access, yoga, tennis, and a quieter, more refined setting that skews toward couples and families seeking calm over activity. The ratings tell a clear story: Zoëtry outscores Dreams Sapphire across almost every metric, with overall rating 9.3 vs 8.7, food 8.2 vs 7.2, rooms 9.2 vs 8.5, service 9.5 vs 9.0, and cleanliness 9.4 vs 8.8, though neither resort earns high marks for its beach, scoring 3.5 and 5.0 respectively. Dreams Sapphire wins on amenity breadth and family infrastructure; Zoëtry wins on quality, intimacy, and atmosphere. If you want a large Caribbean family all-inclusive with kids clubs, nightlife, and watersports near Puerto Morelos, choose Dreams Sapphire. If you want a polished boutique Pacific resort with superior food, rooms, and service in Los Cabos, choose Zoëtry.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children and teenagers who want a large Caribbean all-inclusive packed with structured programming, watersports, a nightclub, and walk-up dining without reservation hassles. Best for those who prioritise activity variety and family infrastructure over boutique refinement.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and families who prefer a quieter, boutique Pacific-coast all-inclusive with standout service, superior rooms, and a more intimate atmosphere. Golfers benefit from course access, and guests who value cleanliness and food quality above a full activity roster will feel well rewarded.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Sapphire sits on Mexico's Caribbean coast, where December through April brings dry, calm conditions and peak pricing; hurricane season runs June through November with lower rates and some weather risk. Zoëtry Los Cabos on the Pacific enjoys sunshine year-round, with September and October occasionally seeing tropical storm activity; the cooler, drier months of November through May are the most reliably pleasant for beach and outdoor activities.","activities":"Dreams Sapphire guests can dive, snorkel, and fish directly from the resort, explore the Puerto Morelos reef, and access the Mesoamerican Barrier Reef nearby. Zoëtry Los Cabos guests can visit the historic centro of San Jose del Cabo, take whale-watching excursions from January through March, explore the famous El Arco rock formation by boat, and access golf courses in the broader Los Cabos corridor."},"sunscape-dorado-pacifico-ixtapa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Sunscape Dorado Pacifico Ixtapa is a mid-market family all-inclusive on Mexico's Pacific coast in Ixtapa with beach access as its headline amenity, posting strong location (8.8) and value (8.3) scores but notably weak ratings for food (6.4), pool (6.2), and atmosphere (6.3). Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a premium boutique all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with a heated pool, spa, yoga, tennis, swim-up bar, golf, and room service, scoring significantly higher across nearly every category: overall 9.3 vs 8.6, food 8.2 vs 6.4, room 9.2 vs 8.2, service 9.5 vs 8.6, and cleanliness 9.4 vs 8.6. The one striking reversal is beach: Sunscape scores 6.8 while Zoëtry scores just 3.5, reflecting the notoriously rough, non-swimmable surf typical of Los Cabos beaches. Sunscape suits budget-conscious families who prioritize Pacific beach access and solid location value; Zoëtry suits guests willing to pay more for exceptional service, refined food, and a polished boutique atmosphere while accepting a beach that is largely scenic rather than swimmable.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families and beach-focused travelers who want a reasonably priced Pacific Mexico all-inclusive in Ixtapa where actual ocean swimming is possible. Best for those who can overlook average food and pool ratings in exchange for good location scores and solid overall value at a mid-market price point.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and families who prioritize exceptional service, high-quality food, immaculate rooms, and a refined boutique atmosphere over a swimmable beach. Ideal for guests willing to pay premium rates for a polished Los Cabos experience and who are happy using a heated pool rather than the ocean.","whenToVisit":"Ixtapa's dry season runs November through April, avoiding the Pacific hurricane season that peaks August to October. Los Cabos is a year-round destination with warm, sunny weather and very little rainfall, though late summer brings occasional tropical storms. Both destinations are most crowded and expensive over US holidays and spring break; shoulder months of May and November offer better rates.","activities":"At Sunscape Ixtapa, guests are close to Ixtapa Island for snorkelling and boat trips, plus parasailing and watersports along the Ixtapa strip. Zoëtry Los Cabos guests have access to on-site tennis, yoga, spa treatments, golf, and a swim-up bar; nearby San Jose del Cabo offers art gallery walks, the historic town centre, and whale-watching excursions from January through March."},"secrets-tulum-resort-and-beach-club-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Tulum Resort & Beach Club is an adults-only Mexican all-inclusive on the Riviera Maya with a strong atmosphere rating of 8.5, excellent sleep quality at 9.1, and clean, high-quality rooms at 8.9, but a notably weak beach score of 5.5 that reflects Tulum's rocky, seaweed-prone coastline. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with a higher overall rating of 9.3 versus Secrets' 8.3, outstanding service at 9.5 versus 8.8, and better value at 8.8 versus 7.9, though its beach scores even lower at 3.5 due to the Pacific's rough surf making swimming unsafe. Secrets Tulum edges ahead on pool (8.0 vs 7.3) and atmosphere (8.5 vs 8.0), while Zoëtry leads on location (9.0 vs 7.8), service, and overall satisfaction. Neither resort delivers a strong beach experience, so both guests will anchor their days around the pool and resort amenities rather than the shore.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples or solo travelers who want a lively Tulum atmosphere, exceptional sleep quality, and stylish rooms at a premium price point, and who are comfortable with a poor beach and can accept slightly lower food and value scores in exchange for strong ambiance.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families or couples who prioritize exceptional service, high overall satisfaction, and a quiet, intimate setting in San Jose del Cabo, and who value strong room quality and good value for money at a luxury price point over a swimmable beach.","whenToVisit":"Tulum's peak season runs December through April when humidity drops and sargassum seaweed is less prevalent, though the beach score suggests conditions remain limited year-round. Los Cabos is sunny almost year-round with peak season October through May; summer brings humidity and the occasional late-season hurricane risk. Both resorts sit at the same price tier, so seasonal rate differences rather than weather are the main timing consideration.","activities":"At Secrets Tulum, guests can explore the UNESCO-listed Tulum ruins, swim in cenotes, snorkel the Mesoamerican Barrier Reef, and visit Sian Ka'an Biosphere Reserve nearby. At Zoëtry Casa del Mar, the resort's own golf course, tennis courts, yoga classes, spa, and heated pool cover most needs on-property, while whale watching, sport fishing, and the art galleries of San Jose del Cabo's historic town center are within easy reach."},"sunscape-dominicus-la-romana-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Sunscape Dominicus La Romana is a Dominican Republic family all-inclusive in La Romana built around beach and water-based activities, with a kids club, teen club, and both small and large waterparks driving its appeal for families. Its beach scores an 8.0, but food, pool, and atmosphere all rate a low 6.2, suggesting a property where the beach and kids amenities carry the experience. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a boutique adult-leaning family all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo, Mexico, with a heated pool, spa, yoga, tennis, golf, and swim-up bar, earning a 9.3 overall versus Sunscape's 8.1. Zoëtry dominates on service (9.5 vs 8.3), rooms (9.2 vs 8.0), cleanliness (9.4 vs 8.5), and food (8.2 vs 6.2). The critical caveat: Zoëtry's beach rates just 3.5, a reflection of Los Cabos's rough Pacific surf, while Sunscape's swimmable Caribbean beach scores 8.0. If beach swimming and kids waterparks matter most, Sunscape wins on those terms. If refined service, food quality, and luxurious rooms are priorities and you can live without a safe swimming beach, Zoëtry is the clear choice.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children and teens who want a swimmable Caribbean beach, waterparks, and dedicated kids and teen clubs in the Dominican Republic. Those for whom beach access and water-based fun for kids outweigh food quality, atmosphere, and overall room refinement.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and families who prioritize exceptional service, high-quality food, and beautifully appointed rooms in a boutique Mexican setting. Guests comfortable foregoing a swimmable beach in exchange for a polished, intimate atmosphere with spa, yoga, tennis, and one of the stronger overall ratings in Los Cabos.","whenToVisit":"Sunscape Dominicus is best visited November through April when the Dominican Republic's dry season delivers reliable sunshine and calm Caribbean waters. Zoëtry Casa del Mar suits travel from November through May, avoiding Los Cabos's hurricane season and summer heat. Both properties offer good winter escapes, but Zoëtry's year-round mild desert climate gives it slightly more scheduling flexibility.","activities":"At Sunscape Dominicus, guests have waterparks, beach activities, and kids and teen club programming, with La Romana's nearby Altos de Chavón artisan village and Casa de Campo golf courses offering excursion options. At Zoëtry Casa del Mar, guests can use the heated pool, spa, yoga classes, tennis courts, and an adjacent golf course, with the charming galleries and restaurants of San Jose del Cabo's historic town center a short drive away."},"zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos-vs-zoetry-montego-bay-jamaica":{"keyDifferences":"Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly boutique all-inclusive on Mexico's Baja Peninsula in San Jose del Cabo, with a heated pool, swim-up bar, golf course, tennis, yoga, spa, and evening entertainment. Zoëtry Montego Bay Jamaica is an adults-only boutique all-inclusive on Jamaica's north coast with a similar luxury positioning but no swim-up bar, golf, or evening entertainment listed among its amenities. Casa del Mar scores meaningfully higher across almost every rating category: overall 9.3 vs 8.2, rooms 9.2 vs 8.7, service 9.5 vs 8.8, cleanliness 9.4 vs 8.9, and value 8.8 vs 7.9. Both resorts share weak beach scores — Casa del Mar at 3.5 and Montego Bay at 4.0 — reflecting the rocky or narrow shorelines typical of boutique properties in each destination. Pool ratings also disappoint at both, 7.3 and 6.7 respectively. The key split is guest profile: Casa del Mar welcomes families and outscores Montego Bay comprehensively, while Montego Bay's adults-only structure suits couples seeking a quieter Jamaican escape despite the lower overall ratings.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families or couples who want a high-performing boutique Mexican all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo, where service ratings of 9.5 and room ratings of 9.2 set a clear quality benchmark, and who value access to golf, tennis, and a swim-up bar alongside a refined Zoëtry atmosphere.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adult couples seeking a quieter, adults-only Zoëtry experience in Montego Bay, Jamaica, who prioritize good sleep quality (8.9) and a peaceful atmosphere over a full amenity roster, and who are comfortable with a lower overall value score of 7.9.","whenToVisit":"Los Cabos is best visited October through June, avoiding hurricane season and summer heat; March and April offer ideal weather before the dry season peaks. Montego Bay is enjoyable year-round but December through April delivers the driest, coolest conditions. Both destinations carry hurricane risk in late summer and fall, with Jamaica more exposed — August through October is the peak of Jamaica's hurricane season and worth avoiding.","activities":"At Casa del Mar, guests can play golf on nearby Cabo courses, take yoga classes, use the tennis courts, and explore San Jose del Cabo's art district and marina. At Zoëtry Montego Bay, guests are well placed for snorkelling, nearby Dunn's River Falls excursions, and Montego Bay's Hip Strip dining and nightlife scene. Both properties offer spa treatments and are within reach of water-based excursions including fishing and boat tours."},"dreams-bahia-mita-surf-and-spa-resort-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Bahia Mita Surf & Spa Resort is a family-focused all-inclusive on Mexico's Pacific Riviera Nayarit coast near Punta de Mita, with a kids club, babysitting, evening entertainment, and restaurants without reservation requirements. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a boutique family all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with a heated pool, swim-up bar, yoga, tennis, golf, and room service, earning a notably higher overall rating of 9.3 versus Dreams' 8.6. Zoëtry outperforms on food (8.2 vs 7.3), atmosphere (8.0 vs 7.4), service (9.5 vs 9.0), and cleanliness (9.4 vs 9.2). Neither resort excels on beach, but Dreams edges ahead there (4.8 vs 3.5). Dreams wins on amenities for young families with its kids club and babysitting, while Zoëtry's polished service scores and boutique atmosphere make it the stronger pick for guests prioritizing quality over programming breadth. Both sit at the same price tier, making Zoëtry's rating advantages meaningful.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with very young children who want a Pacific coast Mexico all-inclusive with dedicated kids club programming, babysitting, and evening entertainment in the relaxed surf-town setting of Punta de Mita, where convenience and family infrastructure matter more than culinary refinement.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families and couples seeking a boutique Los Cabos all-inclusive with standout service ratings, better food, yoga, tennis, and golf access in San Jose del Cabo, where a more intimate, polished atmosphere and higher overall scores justify the stay over a more amenity-heavy alternative.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts enjoy dry, sunny winters from November through April. Dreams Bahia Mita sits on the Pacific coast, where summer brings more surf swell and occasional tropical moisture. Zoëtry Los Cabos benefits from Baja's desert climate, making shoulder months like May and October good value windows with reliable weather. Avoid hurricane-season peaks in September for both.","activities":"Dreams Bahia Mita guests can surf nearby Punta de Mita breaks, explore the Marieta Islands by boat, and access whale-watching tours from December through March. Zoëtry Los Cabos guests can play golf on nearby Cabo courses, visit the historic San Jose del Cabo art district, snorkel at Cabo Pulmo, or take whale-watching excursions in the Sea of Cortez during winter months."},"dreams-los-cabos-suites-golf-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Both resorts sit in San Jose del Cabo at the same $$$$ price level with similarly limited beach ratings (Dreams 3.3, Zoëtry 3.5), reflecting the Pacific-facing surf conditions common to the area. But Zoëtry Casa del Mar outscores Dreams Los Cabos on nearly every meaningful metric: overall rating 9.3 vs. 8.6, food 8.2 vs. 7.5, room 9.2 vs. 8.7, service 9.5 vs. 8.7, cleanliness 9.4 vs. 8.9, and atmosphere 8.0 vs. 7.2. Zoëtry also edges ahead on value (8.8 vs. 8.3) despite being a boutique wellness-oriented property with a heated pool, golf course, spa, yoga, tennis, and swim-up bar. Dreams compensates with a kids club for under-4s and a no-reservation dining policy that suits larger, more chaotic family trips. Zoëtry is the stronger all-round resort on measurable quality, while Dreams is the more practical choice for families with toddlers who want flexible, casual dining without the formality of a smaller boutique property.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with very young children who want a large, easygoing all-inclusive where toddlers are formally catered for and restaurants are walk-up casual. Those who prioritize convenience and a forgiving, high-energy atmosphere over boutique refinement will find Dreams Los Cabos the more practical fit.","whoShouldChooseB":"Guests who want measurably better food, service, rooms, and atmosphere in a boutique Los Cabos setting with wellness amenities including yoga, spa, heated pool, and golf. Couples and families with older children who are willing to pay a premium for a quieter, higher-quality experience will find Zoëtry consistently outperforms on nearly every rated dimension.","whenToVisit":"Both resorts benefit from Los Cabos' best weather from November through May, when rainfall is minimal and temperatures are warm but not oppressive. Peak holiday weeks in December and March drive up prices and occupancy at both properties. June through October brings heat and occasional hurricane-season swells, which further limits the already-restricted beach access both resorts share.","activities":"Both resorts offer access to the broader Los Cabos corridor, including world-class sportfishing, whale watching from January through March, ATV desert tours, and the famous Arch of Cabo San Lucas by boat. Zoëtry guests have on-site golf, tennis, yoga, and a spa. Dreams guests can explore nearby golf courses independently. The two-hour drive to Todos Santos adds a bohemian art-town excursion option for guests at either property."},"dreams-natura-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Natura in Puerto Morelos and Zoëtry Casa del Mar in San Jose del Cabo are both upscale Mexican family all-inclusives at the same price tier, but they diverge sharply on overall quality and amenity depth. Zoëtry scores meaningfully higher overall (9.3 vs 8.5), on food (8.2 vs 7.3), atmosphere (8.0 vs 6.9), location (9.0 vs 8.0), and room quality (9.2 vs 8.8), while delivering superior service (9.5 vs 8.7) and cleanliness (9.4 vs 9.0). Both resorts share a low beach score, though Dreams Natura's beach rating (4.5) is actually worse than Zoëtry's already-modest 3.5. Zoëtry's amenity list is considerably broader, with a heated pool, gym, golf, yoga, spa, swim-up bar, tennis, room service, and evening entertainment, while Dreams Natura's standout distinction is a dedicated kids club for under-4s and a no-reservation restaurant policy. Dreams Natura pools score nearly identically to Zoëtry (7.2 vs 7.3). For families prioritizing infant-friendly programming and casual dining flexibility on the Caribbean side, Dreams Natura is the pick; for those prioritizing room quality, service, and a fuller amenity spread in Los Cabos, Zoëtry wins decisively.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with very young children, particularly infants and toddlers, who want a Caribbean-side Mexican all-inclusive with a dedicated under-4s kids club and the relaxed convenience of no restaurant reservations. A solid choice if the Riviera Maya setting matters more than breadth of resort amenities.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families and couples who want a premium Los Cabos all-inclusive experience with standout service (9.5), beautifully appointed rooms (9.2), and a full amenity spread including spa, golf, yoga, and tennis. Best suited to guests who prioritize quality and polish over a kids-specific program.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Natura in Puerto Morelos benefits from the Riviera Maya's dry season, roughly December through April, when humidity and hurricane risk drop. Zoëtry Casa del Mar in San Jose del Cabo sits on the Pacific-Sea of Cortez corridor; September brings hurricane risk, while October through June offers the most reliable sunny weather. Both resorts carry premium pricing year-round at the $$$$ tier.","activities":"Dreams Natura guests have Puerto Morelos's proximity to the Mesoamerican Reef for snorkelling and diving, plus the low-key town of Puerto Morelos itself nearby. Zoëtry Casa del Mar guests in San Jose del Cabo can access world-class golf on resort and nearby courses, sport fishing, whale watching seasonally from January to March, and the art galleries and restaurants of San Jose del Cabo's historic downtown just minutes away."},"secrets-st-lucia-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets St. Lucia Resort & Spa is an adults-only luxury all-inclusive on the island of Saint Lucia, rated 8.6 overall, with standout scores for service (9.2), sleep quality (9.2), and cleanliness (9.1), but a notably modest beach rating of 6.8 and a pool score of 7.6. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo, Mexico, rated higher overall at 9.3, with exceptional service (9.5), room quality (9.2), and cleanliness (9.4), though its beach rating is a striking 3.5, reflecting the notoriously rough and unswimmable surf typical of Los Cabos. Zoëtry edges out Secrets on nearly every metric, including food (8.2 vs. 8.0), value (8.8 vs. 8.6), and atmosphere (8.0 vs. 7.8), and adds a heated pool, gym, yoga, tennis, spa, swim-up bar, and evening entertainment. Secrets counters with a more Caribbean island setting and an adults-only environment. If you want a refined, quiet adults-only Caribbean retreat in Saint Lucia, go to Secrets. If you want a higher-rated, amenity-rich family or couples all-inclusive in Los Cabos with superior rooms and service, go to Zoëtry Casa del Mar.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult couples and honeymooners seeking a serene, adults-only Caribbean escape in Saint Lucia, where exceptional service, clean rooms, and a relaxed island atmosphere matter more than a full amenity list or a resort beach rated for swimming.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families, couples, or wellness-focused travelers who want a top-rated all-inclusive in Los Cabos with outstanding rooms, attentive service, yoga, tennis, a spa, and a heated pool, and who understand that swimming in the ocean is not the draw here.","whenToVisit":"Saint Lucia's dry season runs December through April, making those months ideal for Secrets. Los Cabos enjoys warm, sunny weather most of the year, with peak season October through May avoiding the late-summer hurricane risk. Both resorts sit in the premium price tier year-round, but shoulder months at either property can offer slightly better availability.","activities":"At Secrets St. Lucia, guests can explore the island's dramatic rainforest, visit the Piton mountains, take sailing or diving excursions, and enjoy Saint Lucia's rich culinary and cultural scene. At Zoëtry Casa del Mar, guests can play tennis, practice yoga, use the gym, golf nearby, visit the charming arts district of San Jose del Cabo on foot, and take whale-watching or snorkeling excursions in the Sea of Cortez."},"dreams-tulum-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Tulum Resort & Spa is a family all-inclusive on Mexico's Caribbean coast with a kids club for under-4s, no-reservation dining, a genuine beach, and solid across-the-board ratings in the mid-range of the scale. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a boutique family all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with a dramatically higher overall rating (9.3 vs 8.2), exceptional service (9.5 vs 8.5), superior rooms (9.2 vs 8.1), and outstanding cleanliness (9.4 vs 8.6), but its beach rating collapses to 3.5 against Dreams Tulum's already modest 6.3. Zoëtry compensates with a heated pool, swim-up bar, spa, yoga, tennis, golf, and evening entertainment. Dreams Tulum wins on beach quality by a wide margin and offers structured programming for toddlers. Zoëtry wins on virtually every other quality metric and packs in far more amenities. If you want a Caribbean beach family all-inclusive with toddler programming at a solid value, choose Dreams Tulum. If you want a refined, amenity-rich boutique resort in Los Cabos where room quality and service are the priority, choose Zoëtry Casa del Mar.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with toddlers and young children who prioritize a genuine Caribbean beach experience and relaxed no-reservation dining in a well-maintained Tulum setting, and are willing to accept average food ratings (7.0) in exchange for easier access to the water.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families and couples who value exceptional service, beautifully appointed rooms, and a full amenity set including spa, yoga, tennis, and golf in a boutique Los Cabos atmosphere, and who can look past a very poor beach rating in favor of near-perfect ratings across every other quality measure.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Tulum suits winter and spring visits (December through April) when Caribbean humidity is manageable and hurricane risk is low; avoid late summer through October during hurricane season. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is best from October through June when the Sea of Cortez is calm; July and August bring heat and occasional tropical storms to Baja, though the Pacific-facing Cabo area is generally less hurricane-prone than the Caribbean.","activities":"At Dreams Tulum, the ancient ruins of Tulum sit minutes away, and guests can explore cenotes, the Sian Ka'an Biosphere Reserve, and snorkeling in the Caribbean. At Zoëtry Casa del Mar, on-site tennis, golf, yoga, and a spa keep guests occupied, while nearby San Jose del Cabo offers sport fishing, whale watching from January through March, ATV tours through the desert, and easy access to the famous Land's End arch at Cabo San Lucas."},"sunscape-coco-punta-cana-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Sunscape Coco Punta Cana is a family-focused Dominican Republic all-inclusive on a Punta Cana beach with a kids club and teen club, sitting at a mid-range price point with solid overall scores but notably weak food (6.2), pool (6.2), and atmosphere (6.2) ratings. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a premium Mexican all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with an exceptional service rating (9.5), near-perfect cleanliness (9.4), and outstanding rooms (9.2), but a critically low beach score (3.5) reflecting the notoriously rough Pacific surf at Cabo. Sunscape Coco delivers a true Caribbean beach experience at a lower price, while Zoëtry compensates for its unusable beach with superior food (8.2 vs 6.2), a heated pool, spa, yoga, golf, and tennis. The gap in overall ratings is significant: 9.3 vs 8.2. If you want an affordable Dominican family all-inclusive with a proper swimmable Caribbean beach, kids programming, and acceptable value, choose Sunscape Coco. If you want a luxury Mexican boutique all-inclusive with exceptional service and rooms, but no real beach, choose Zoëtry Casa del Mar.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young children and teenagers who want a straightforward, affordable Caribbean all-inclusive on a swimmable Punta Cana beach, with dedicated kids and teen clubs and solid value for money without needing premium food or atmosphere.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples or families who prioritize exceptional service, spotless rooms, fine dining, and a full amenity set including spa, golf, yoga, and tennis in a refined Los Cabos setting, and who won't miss a swimmable beach.","whenToVisit":"Sunscape Coco Punta Cana is best visited December through April when Dominican Republic weather is dry and consistent. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos benefits from Los Cabos' near year-round sunshine, though June through October brings occasional hurricane-season humidity and the risk of tropical storms; November through May is the safest and most pleasant window for both destinations.","activities":"Sunscape Coco guests have a swimmable Caribbean beach and structured kids and teen programming. Zoëtry guests can use a heated pool, spa, gym, tennis courts, golf course, and yoga classes on-site, and are well-placed in San Jose del Cabo to explore the historic town center, art galleries, and the Corridor's world-class sport fishing and diving just minutes away."},"dreams-puerto-morelos-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Puerto Morelos Resort & Spa is a large family all-inclusive on Mexico's Caribbean coast with a waterpark for both young and older kids, a no-reservation dining policy, and solid scores for rooms (8.5) and cleanliness (8.6), but weaker numbers for beach (5.0) and pool (6.7). Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a boutique Pacific-side all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with standout scores across the board — overall 9.3 versus Dreams' 7.8, service 9.5, rooms 9.2, value 8.8, and cleanliness 9.4 — but an even lower beach score (3.5), typical of Los Cabos' non-swimmable Pacific surf. Dreams wins on kid-specific infrastructure with waterparks and a kids club; Zoëtry counters with a spa, yoga, tennis, golf access, heated pool, and swim-up bar in a quieter, more refined atmosphere (8.0 vs. 6.9). Dreams suits families chasing Caribbean beach energy; Zoëtry suits those prioritizing elevated service and a tranquil, amenity-rich environment over beach swimming.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with young and older children who want a lively Caribbean all-inclusive with dedicated waterparks, a kids club, and casual no-reservation dining on Mexico's Riviera Maya coast. A strong fit for those who want structured kids' activities and solid rooms at a reasonable price for the category.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families and couples who prioritize exceptional service (9.5), beautifully appointed rooms (9.2), and a refined boutique atmosphere over beach swimming. Ideal for those drawn to Los Cabos' dramatic Pacific scenery, with spa, yoga, tennis, and golf rounding out a polished, quieter all-inclusive experience.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Puerto Morelos benefits from the Yucatán's dry season, November through April, when Caribbean humidity drops and hurricane risk disappears; avoid September and October. Zoëtry Casa del Mar in San Jose del Cabo enjoys warm, sunny weather from October through June, with summer months bringing occasional tropical moisture to the Baja Peninsula. Both resorts are in peak demand over US holidays and spring break, when prices rise sharply.","activities":"At Dreams Puerto Morelos, guests can snorkel the nearby Mesoamerican Barrier Reef — the world's second largest — explore Puerto Morelos village, or take day trips to Tulum and Chichen Itza. At Zoëtry Casa del Mar, guests can access championship golf courses, take yoga classes, visit the art galleries and restaurants of San Jose del Cabo's historic town center, or arrange whale-watching excursions (December through April) and sport fishing in the Sea of Cortez."},"zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos-vs-zoetry-curacao-resort-and-spa":{"keyDifferences":"Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly all-inclusive on the Sea of Cortez in San Jose del Cabo, Mexico, with a heated pool, swim-up bar, golf, tennis, yoga, spa, and evening entertainment, carrying a strong overall rating of 9.3 against Zoëtry Curaçao's 7.6. Both resorts share similarly modest beach scores — 3.5 versus 3.3 — reflecting rocky or limited shorelines rather than wide Caribbean strands. Casa del Mar pulls ahead decisively on service (9.5 vs 8.2), value (8.8 vs 7.4), and room quality (9.2 vs 8.8). Zoëtry Curaçao is an adults-only property near Willemstad with spa access but a thinner amenity list and lower pool score (6.9 vs 7.3). Casa del Mar is the higher-performing, better-value resort with broader family programming, while Curaçao suits adults seeking a quieter, boutique-style escape near a culturally rich city. If you want a polished, amenity-rich Mexican all-inclusive with excellent service and family-friendly facilities, choose Casa del Mar. If you want an adults-only retreat near Willemstad's Dutch-Caribbean architecture with a more intimate atmosphere, choose Zoëtry Curaçao.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families and couples who want a high-performing, amenity-rich Mexican all-inclusive with exceptional service (9.5), golf, tennis, yoga, and a swim-up bar in San Jose del Cabo. Those who prioritize cleanliness, room quality, and strong overall value at a luxury price point will find Casa del Mar consistently delivers.","whoShouldChooseB":"Adults without children who want a quieter, boutique-style all-inclusive near Willemstad, Curaçao's colorful Dutch-Caribbean capital. Best suited to couples or solo travelers drawn more by the island's culture and diving scene than by a long resort amenity list, and who accept a lower overall rating for a more intimate setting.","whenToVisit":"Los Cabos is best visited October through June, avoiding the summer hurricane season and peak heat; December through April offers the driest, most comfortable weather. Curaçao sits outside the main hurricane belt, making it a genuinely year-round destination, though January through September delivers the most reliably sunny skies. Both resorts command premium pricing over the Christmas and New Year holiday window.","activities":"At Casa del Mar, guests can play golf, take yoga classes, use the tennis courts, and explore the Sea of Cortez through whale-watching excursions, sport fishing, and snorkeling trips out of San Jose del Cabo. In Curaçao, world-class reef diving, snorkeling, and kayaking are the draws, alongside day trips into Willemstad's UNESCO-listed waterfront district for its Dutch Colonial architecture, local markets, and floating pontoon bridge."},"dreams-playa-bonita-panama-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Playa Bonita Panama and Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos are both family-oriented luxury all-inclusives at the same price tier, but their ratings tell starkly different stories. Zoëtry outperforms Dreams on nearly every metric: overall (9.3 vs 7.4), food (8.2 vs 6.7), atmosphere (8.0 vs 6.5), rooms (9.2 vs 7.6), value (8.8 vs 7.2), cleanliness (9.4 vs 8.0), and service (9.5 vs 8.1). Neither property excels at the beach — Dreams scores 4.0 and Zoëtry a marginal 3.5 — so both are better framed as pool-and-resort destinations. Dreams sits near Panama City, giving it a stronger location story for guests blending city exploration with a resort stay, and its kids club for under-4s addresses very young families. Zoëtry, in San Jose del Cabo, compensates for its beach limitations with a heated pool, spa, golf, yoga, tennis, and a swim-up bar, all delivered at a quality level Dreams cannot match. At the same price point, Zoëtry delivers considerably more for your money.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with toddlers who want a Panama City-adjacent base for combining resort time with urban exploration. Those willing to accept middling food and atmosphere ratings in exchange for proximity to one of Latin America's most accessible and culturally rich capital cities.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families and couples who prioritize exceptional service, spotless rooms, and high-quality dining in a boutique Los Cabos setting. Guests who want yoga, golf, spa, and a heated pool over a strong beach, and who expect the full value of a luxury price tag to actually show up in every rating.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Playa Bonita is best visited December through April, Panama's dry season, when humidity and rainfall are manageable. Zoëtry Casa del Mar suits travel from November through May, when Los Cabos enjoys dry, sunny weather. Both properties are warm year-round, but hurricane-adjacent shoulder months — October in Panama, September in Baja — carry higher weather risk and typically lower room rates.","activities":"At Dreams Playa Bonita, guests can day-trip into Panama City to visit the Canal, Casco Viejo, and Miraflores Locks. Zoëtry Casa del Mar guests have access to golf, yoga, tennis, spa, and a swim-up bar on-site, plus proximity to San Jose del Cabo's gallery district, whale watching from January through March, and world-class sport fishing in the Sea of Cortez. Both properties offer limited beach activity given their low beach scores."},"sunscape-puerto-vallarta-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Sunscape Puerto Vallarta is a mid-market family all-inclusive on Mexico's Pacific coast with solid overall scores (8.0) but notably weaker food (6.2), pool (6.0), and beach (5.3) ratings, compensating with strong location (8.3) and service (8.3). Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a premium family all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with dramatically higher scores across nearly every category: overall 9.3, food 8.2, rooms 9.2, cleanliness 9.4, service 9.5, and value 8.8 despite its higher price tier. The beach gap is notable in both directions — Sunscape's beach scores a still-modest 5.3 while Zoëtry's scores just 3.5, reflecting Los Cabos's characteristically rough, non-swimmable Pacific surf. Zoëtry compensates with a heated pool, golf, yoga, spa, tennis, and swim-up bar. The 1.3-point overall gap and Zoëtry's near-perfect service and cleanliness scores suggest it delivers a genuinely more refined experience. Sunscape suits budget-conscious families wanting Puerto Vallarta's calmer bay setting; Zoëtry suits guests who prioritize room quality and exceptional service over beach access.","whoShouldChooseA":"Budget-conscious families who want a solid Puerto Vallarta all-inclusive on a calmer bay beach without paying premium prices. Strong location and service scores make it a reliable choice for those who prioritize value and a well-connected Pacific Coast destination over top-tier food and room quality.","whoShouldChooseB":"Discerning families and couples willing to pay more for exceptional service (9.5), immaculate rooms (9.2), and outstanding cleanliness (9.4) in a refined Los Cabos setting. Ideal for guests who understand the beach is not swimmable but want a polished, upscale all-inclusive experience with golf, spa, yoga, and tennis.","whenToVisit":"Puerto Vallarta's dry season runs November through April, with peak comfort in February and March. Los Cabos shares a similar dry-season window but sits in a desert microclimate — warm and sunny year-round with very little rainfall. Both destinations can be visited outside peak season, though Los Cabos sees hurricane risk in late summer and early fall, as does Puerto Vallarta, making November through April the safest window for both.","activities":"Sunscape Puerto Vallarta guests can explore Puerto Vallarta's vibrant Malecon boardwalk, old town, and Banderas Bay watersports. Zoëtry Casa del Mar guests have access to on-site golf, tennis, yoga, spa, and a heated swim-up pool, with San Jose del Cabo's art district galleries, whale watching excursions from January to March, and Los Cabos's famous Land's End rock arch reachable by boat nearby."},"sunscape-sabor-cozumel-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Sunscape Sabor Cozumel is a budget-friendly family all-inclusive on Mexico's Cozumel island, rated 7.6 overall with modest food (6.1) and beach (5.8) scores but solid service (8.2) and cleanliness (8.0). Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a luxury boutique all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo rated 9.3 overall, with standout scores for service (9.5), cleanliness (9.4), and rooms (9.2), though its beach scores even lower at 3.5, typical of the rough Pacific-facing Cabo coastline. Zoëtry costs significantly more but justifies it with a heated pool, spa, yoga, tennis, golf access, and room service that Sunscape simply doesn't offer. Sunscape wins on price and island beach access in Cozumel, while Zoëtry dominates every quality metric. The 1.7-point overall gap reflects a genuine difference in experience caliber, not just amenity count. If you want an affordable Caribbean island family base with decent service on a budget, choose Sunscape. If you want a polished, amenity-rich Baja luxury retreat and can accept a non-swimmable beach, choose Zoëtry.","whoShouldChooseA":"Budget-conscious families who want a straightforward Caribbean all-inclusive on Cozumel island, where the real draw is world-class nearby reef diving and snorkeling rather than the resort beach itself, and who prioritize value and clean, well-serviced rooms over premium amenities.","whoShouldChooseB":"Luxury-seeking families or couples willing to pay top-dollar for exceptional service (9.5), immaculate rooms (9.2), and a full amenity suite including spa, yoga, heated pool, and golf, and who are comfortable knowing the Pacific beach at Los Cabos is scenic but not swimmable.","whenToVisit":"Cozumel is best November through April when humidity drops and hurricane risk fades, though the island enjoys year-round diving conditions. Los Cabos is a desert destination with over 300 sunny days annually; visit October through June to avoid the late-summer tropical storm window. Both resorts offer drier, more predictable weather in winter months, making December through March the overlap sweet spot for either destination.","activities":"Cozumel is one of the world's top dive and snorkel destinations, with Palancar Reef minutes offshore, plus jeep tours, cenote visits, and downtown San Miguel for local color. Los Cabos offers whale watching from January through March, sportfishing, ATV desert tours, the famous El Arco rock arch by boat, and golf on championship courses, with Zoëtry itself providing tennis, yoga, and spa treatments on property."},"dreams-cozumel-cape-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Cozumel Cape Resort & Spa and Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos are both Mexican family all-inclusives at the same price tier, but their ratings tell starkly different stories. Zoëtry outscores Dreams on nearly every metric: overall 9.3 vs 7.3, service 9.5 vs 8.3, cleanliness 9.4 vs 8.5, food 8.2 vs 6.8, and rooms 9.2 vs 8.2. Neither property excels on the beach — Dreams scores a weak 5.3 while Zoëtry is even lower at 3.5, reflecting the rocky Los Cabos coastline. Dreams compensates with Cozumel's world-class reef diving just offshore, pushing its location rating to 8.3, while Zoëtry's San Jose del Cabo setting earns a 9.0 driven by proximity to town and the art district. Dreams offers a kids club for under-4s and casual dining without reservations; Zoëtry counters with a gym, golf, tennis, yoga, a spa, and a heated pool. For overall quality and service consistency, Zoëtry is clearly the stronger resort.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with very young children who want a laid-back Cozumel all-inclusive with easy reef access and casual dining, and can accept middling food scores and a modest beach in exchange for Cozumel's exceptional snorkelling and diving on their doorstep.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families or couples who prioritize impeccable service, spotless rooms, and refined dining in a boutique Los Cabos setting, and are happy to forgo a swimmable beach in favor of a heated pool, spa, golf, tennis, and the culture of San Jose del Cabo nearby.","whenToVisit":"Cozumel is best November through April when hurricane season has passed and visibility for diving peaks. Los Cabos enjoys near-year-round sunshine with low humidity, though August and September carry occasional tropical storm risk. Both destinations are busiest over US holidays and spring break, so booking well in advance is advisable for either property during those windows.","activities":"Dreams guests can access Cozumel's famous coral reef for snorkelling and scuba diving, plus glass-bottom boat tours and local town exploring. Zoëtry guests can golf nearby, take yoga classes on-site, use the spa and tennis courts, and explore San Jose del Cabo's galleries and weekly art walk. Neither beach is ideal for swimming, so pool time is central to both resort experiences."},"dreams-acapulco-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Acapulco and Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos are both Mexican family all-inclusives, but their ratings tell very different stories. Zoëtry outscores Dreams in nearly every category: overall 9.3 vs 7.4, food 8.2 vs 6.5, rooms 9.2 vs 7.4, service 9.5 vs 7.7, and cleanliness 9.4 vs 7.9. The one area where Dreams holds an edge is beach, rating 6.0 versus Zoëtry's strikingly low 3.5, reflecting Los Cabos's rough Pacific surf that makes ocean swimming impractical. Dreams sits in Acapulco, a historic but troubled destination that punches well on location (7.7) for travelers comfortable with the city. Zoëtry is a premium boutique resort in San Jose del Cabo with a heated pool, spa, yoga, swim-up bar, tennis, and golf access, and its value rating of 8.8 despite a $$$$ price tag signals guests feel they get what they pay for. Dreams offers a kids club for toddlers under 4 and no-reservation dining, making it more casual and accessible. Zoëtry delivers a quieter, more polished experience across the board.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with very young children who want a casual, lower-cost Mexican Pacific all-inclusive and are comfortable with the Acapulco destination. Those who prioritize actual ocean swimming, simple no-reservation dining, and don't need premium finishes in rooms or service.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families and couples who want a premium boutique all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with exceptional service (9.5), immaculate rooms (9.2), and strong food (8.2). Guests who don't need a swimmable beach but value spa, yoga, tennis, and a genuinely refined atmosphere at a price they consider justified.","whenToVisit":"Acapulco's dry season runs November through April, with calmer, sunnier weather and lower humidity. Los Cabos is sunny nearly year-round but peaks October through June before summer heat and hurricane-season humidity arrive. Both destinations see elevated pricing around Christmas and spring break. Los Cabos's shoulder months of October and early November offer good weather at slightly reduced rates.","activities":"Dreams Acapulco guests can explore Acapulco's famous cliff divers at La Quebrada, take bay boat tours, and enjoy the resort's beach and pool. Zoëtry Los Cabos guests can arrange whale watching (December through April), visit the famous El Arco rock formation, play golf on nearby courses, take ATV excursions into the desert, or explore the galleries and restaurants of San Jose del Cabo's art district, a short drive away."},"secrets-aura-cozumel-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Aura Cozumel is an adults-only Mexican all-inclusive on Cozumel island, rated 7.4 overall, leaning on its strong service (8.3), location (8.3), and sleep quality (8.3) in one of the Caribbean's top dive destinations. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo rated 9.3 overall, with standout scores in service (9.5), cleanliness (9.4), rooms (9.2), and value (8.8) that put it in a different tier entirely. The gap in overall rating is nearly two full points, and Zoëtry leads in every measurable category except beach, where both resorts underperform — Zoëtry at a notably low 3.5 versus Secrets at 5.5, reflecting the rougher Pacific surf at Los Cabos. Secrets offers a livelier adults-only Caribbean island atmosphere, while Zoëtry delivers a quieter, more polished wellness-oriented experience for families and couples willing to forgo a swimmable beach in exchange for exceptional rooms, service, and overall execution at the same premium price point.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults who want a Caribbean island base for diving and snorkelling in Cozumel's world-class reefs, with a relaxed all-inclusive setup, strong service, and the freedom to explore a genuine island destination beyond the resort gates.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families and couples who prioritise exceptional rooms, impeccable service, and a refined wellness atmosphere over a swimmable beach, and who want a polished, high-value all-inclusive experience in the quieter, more sophisticated San Jose del Cabo end of Los Cabos.","whenToVisit":"Cozumel's peak diving season runs November through April when water visibility peaks and hurricane risk drops, though summer brings lush conditions and lower rates. Los Cabos is a year-round destination with consistently dry, sunny weather; summer months bring higher humidity and occasional tropical storms, making November through May the safest and most comfortable window for both resorts.","activities":"Secrets Aura guests have immediate access to Cozumel's legendary coral reefs for diving and snorkelling, plus the island's colourful downtown San Miguel for shopping and restaurants. Zoëtry Casa del Mar guests can use the heated pool, gym, yoga classes, tennis, spa, and swim-up bar on property, while the galleries, restaurants, and boutiques of San Jose del Cabo's historic art district sit close by, with whale watching available December through April."},"dreams-curacao-resort-spa-and-casino-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Curaçao and Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos are both $$$$ family all-inclusives, but their ratings tell very different stories. Zoëtry outscores Dreams across nearly every category by substantial margins: overall 9.3 vs 6.4, service 9.5 vs 7.3, cleanliness 9.4 vs 7.8, rooms 9.2 vs 7.3, and value 8.8 vs 6.4. The one area where Dreams holds a clear edge is beach, scoring 5.3 against Zoëtry's notably weak 3.5, though neither resort excels there. Dreams sits near Willemstad in Curaçao with casino access and a kids club for toddlers, while Zoëtry is a boutique intimate property in San Jose del Cabo with a heated pool, spa, yoga, tennis, golf, and swim-up bar. Dreams is a larger, livelier property with a casino and no-reservation dining, while Zoëtry delivers a quieter, more refined all-inclusive experience where room quality, service, and atmosphere are the headline strengths. The gap in overall and value scores makes Zoëtry the stronger proposition for most guests at this price tier.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with toddlers who want a Curaçao base close to Willemstad's colorful capital, value casino access and evening energy, and can accept a more average overall experience. Best for guests prioritizing location convenience and a lively atmosphere over polished service and room quality.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families and couples who want a boutique, high-service Mexican all-inclusive near San Jose del Cabo where room quality, cleanliness, and attentive service are exceptional. Ideal for guests who prioritize a refined, peaceful atmosphere with yoga, spa, and tennis over a strong beach.","whenToVisit":"Curaçao sits outside the hurricane belt, making Dreams a reliable year-round destination with dry, sunny weather peaking December through April. Los Cabos is also largely sunny year-round, but late summer through October brings occasional tropical storm risk. Both destinations are most crowded and expensive over North American holiday periods.","activities":"Dreams guests can explore Willemstad's UNESCO-listed colonial architecture and waterfront just minutes away, plus diving, snorkeling, and watersports along Curaçao's calm southern coast. Zoëtry guests have on-site tennis, golf, yoga, and a spa, with San Jose del Cabo's art district, whale watching from January through March, and deep-sea fishing charters all accessible nearby."},"breathless-puerto-vallarta-resort-and-spa-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Breathless Puerto Vallarta is an adults-only Mexican all-inclusive on the Pacific coast with a strong location score (8.7) and excellent rooms (9.1), catering to a lively, social crowd with a party-forward atmosphere. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a family-friendly boutique all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with superior service (9.5 vs. 9.2), better food (8.2 vs. 7.7), and a higher overall rating, but a dramatically weaker beach score (3.5 vs. 6.5) — a known limitation of the Sea of Cortez coastline. Breathless wins on beach quality and atmosphere energy, while Zoëtry leads on food, service, and overall refinement. The gap in food ratings (8.2 vs. 7.7) and service (9.5 vs. 9.2) suggests Zoëtry delivers a more polished, intimate experience. If you want an adults-only Puerto Vallarta all-inclusive with a livelier atmosphere and a better swimming beach, choose Breathless. If you want a refined, family-welcoming boutique experience in Los Cabos with superior dining and service despite a swimmable-beach tradeoff, choose Zoëtry.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults and couples who want a social, energetic Puerto Vallarta all-inclusive with a genuine beach, strong location, and a lively atmosphere — and are not prioritizing fine dining or boutique-level service polish over fun and value.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families and couples who prioritize exceptional service, refined dining, and a tranquil boutique atmosphere in Los Cabos and are prepared for a beach that is scenic but not safe for swimming due to Pacific surf conditions.","whenToVisit":"Puerto Vallarta's dry season runs November through April, making winter the prime window for Breathless. Los Cabos enjoys more year-round sunshine with over 350 sunny days annually, though late summer brings hurricane season risk to both destinations. Both resorts sit in the same broad weather window, but Los Cabos tends to be drier and more reliably sunny outside of August and September.","activities":"Breathless guests enjoy Puerto Vallarta's vibrant Malecon boardwalk, Zona Romantica dining, whale watching from December to March, zip-lining in the Sierra Madre jungle, and sport fishing. Zoëtry guests have access to golf courses near San Jose del Cabo, yoga classes, spa treatments, tennis, the art district gallery walk on Thursdays, and snorkeling and diving excursions in the clearer waters of the Sea of Cortez."},"sunscape-curacao-resort-spa-and-casino-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Sunscape Curacao is a mid-to-large family all-inclusive on the island of Curaçao near Willemstad, with a casino, spa, and direct beach access, scoring a 6.3 on beach and a modest 7.3 overall. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a boutique luxury all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo, Mexico, with a heated pool, golf, yoga, tennis, spa, and swim-up bar, scoring a 9.3 overall but just 3.5 on beach — the Cabo coastline is famously non-swimmable. The gaps are stark: Zoëtry leads on rooms (9.2 vs 7.4), service (9.5 vs 7.8), cleanliness (9.4 vs 8.0), food (8.2 vs 6.2), atmosphere (8.0 vs 6.2), and value (8.8 vs 7.2). Sunscape's lone advantages are its swimmable beach and the novelty of Curaçao as a destination. If you want a swimmable Caribbean beach in a colorful Dutch-colonial island setting at a lower performance threshold, go to Sunscape Curacao. If you want a high-performing boutique Mexican all-inclusive with outstanding service, rooms, and food where beach swimming is not the draw, go to Zoëtry Casa del Mar.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families and couples who want a swimmable Caribbean beach all-inclusive in the distinctive, less-traveled setting of Curaçao, and are comfortable accepting more modest food, pool, and atmosphere scores in exchange for genuine beach access and an interesting island to explore.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families and couples who prioritize exceptional service, immaculate rooms, and high-quality food over beach swimming, and who want the refined boutique experience of San Jose del Cabo with golf, yoga, tennis, and spa amenities at a property that dramatically outperforms its price category on nearly every metric.","whenToVisit":"Curaçao sits outside the hurricane belt and offers reliable sunshine year-round, making Sunscape a viable choice any month; its driest stretch runs November through May. Los Cabos enjoys over 300 sunny days annually, but peak comfort at Zoëtry falls between October and June before summer humidity and occasional tropical storms arrive. Both destinations command premium pricing during U.S. holiday windows.","activities":"At Sunscape Curacao, guests can explore Willemstad's UNESCO-listed colonial waterfront, dive or snorkel Curaçao's clear reef walls, and try the on-site casino. At Zoëtry Casa del Mar, the property itself covers considerable ground with golf, tennis, yoga, a heated pool with swim-up bar, and a spa, while nearby San Jose del Cabo offers art galleries, sport fishing, whale watching, and ATV excursions into the Baja desert."},"dreams-grand-island-cancun-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Dreams Grand Island Cancun is a large family all-inclusive on Mexico's Costa Mujeres with a kids club for under-4s, no-reservation dining, and strong scores for service (9.1), cleanliness (9.0), and sleep quality (9.0), but noticeably weaker ratings for food (7.2) and beach (6.1). Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos is a boutique San Jose del Cabo all-inclusive with an exceptional overall rating (9.3) and standout scores for service (9.5), cleanliness (9.4), rooms (9.2), and food (8.2) — a full point higher than Dreams — though its beach rating (3.5) reflects the rough Pacific surf typical of the Baja coast. Dreams wins on location access to Cancun's Caribbean waters and offers dedicated toddler programming, while Zoëtry delivers a more refined, intimate experience with heated pool, spa, tennis, yoga, and golf at better perceived value (8.8 vs. 7.9). If you want a large Caribbean family all-inclusive near Cancun with toddler-specific programming, choose Dreams Grand Island. If you want a boutique, high-service Baja resort where food and atmosphere are meaningfully better, choose Zoëtry Casa del Mar.","whoShouldChooseA":"Families with very young children, including toddlers, who want a large Caribbean all-inclusive near Cancun with dedicated kids programming, no-reservation dining flexibility, and reliable service and cleanliness at a busy, activity-rich resort.","whoShouldChooseB":"Couples and families with older children who prioritize exceptional service, superior food quality, and an intimate boutique atmosphere in Los Cabos, and who won't mind forgoing a swimmable beach in exchange for a dramatically higher overall resort experience.","whenToVisit":"Dreams Grand Island Cancun is best visited November through April, avoiding the June–November hurricane season that affects the Caribbean coast. Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos benefits from Los Cabos' more stable climate, with October through June offering the most reliable conditions; late summer brings increased humidity and occasional tropical storms to Baja but the resort remains largely sheltered.","activities":"Dreams Grand Island sits in Costa Mujeres, close to Isla Mujeres for day trips, snorkeling, and Cancun's hotel zone shopping and nightlife. Zoëtry Casa del Mar offers on-site golf, spa, yoga, and tennis, with San Jose del Cabo's art district, gallery walks, and whale-watching excursions nearby from December through April, plus sport fishing departures from the Cabo San Lucas marina."},"iberostar-coral-holguin-vs-iberostar-selection-praia-do-forte":{"keyDifferences":"Iberostar Coral Holguin is a budget adults-only all-inclusive on Cuba's north coast near Rafael Freyre, with archery, tennis, snorkelling, a spa, and evening entertainment. Iberostar Selection Praia Do Forte is a premium family all-inclusive on Brazil's Bahia coast with a kids club, babysitting, diving, yoga, swim-up bar, nightclub, and rooms for five or more guests. Coral Holguin scores significantly higher overall (9.5 vs 8.9), on rooms (9.1 vs 8.8), value (9.0 vs 8.2), and atmosphere (6.6 vs 7.4, where Praia do Forte edges ahead). Food is notably better at Praia do Forte (7.4 vs 6.6). Praia do Forte costs substantially more but delivers a fuller family amenity set with diving and a nightclub. Coral Holguin is a rare high-scoring Cuban adults-only bargain, while Praia do Forte is a high-end Brazilian family resort where you pay for breadth of programming and access to Bahia's distinctive coastline. The gap in price level is dramatic: one dollar sign versus four.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adult couples or solo travellers who want a high-value, quietly atmospheric Cuban beach escape with strong room quality, reliable service, and a relaxed adults-only environment at one of the most competitive price points in the Caribbean.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families with children of all ages who want a premium Brazilian all-inclusive on the Bahia coast with a kids club, babysitting, diving, a nightclub, and large-group room configurations, and who are willing to pay significantly more for that breadth of programming.","whenToVisit":"Coral Holguin suits travel from November through April when Cuba's north coast is dry and cooler. Praia do Forte in Bahia benefits from visits between September and March, the drier season, though Brazil's northeast coast is warm year-round. Both destinations are most crowded and expensive during the Christmas and New Year period.","activities":"At Coral Holguin guests can snorkel offshore, play tennis, try archery, and explore the relatively untouristed Holguin province including nearby Guardalavaca beach. At Praia do Forte guests can dive, snorkel, take yoga classes, and visit the famous Tamar sea turtle conservation project adjacent to the resort, with the historic village of Praia do Forte and its natural pools within easy reach."},"secrets-macao-beach-punta-cana-vs-zoetry-casa-del-mar-los-cabos":{"keyDifferences":"Secrets Macao Beach Punta Cana is an adults-only Dominican Republic all-inclusive on one of the Caribbean's most celebrated natural beaches, posting a beach rating of 8.2 versus Zoëtry Casa del Mar Los Cabos's striking 3.5 — the single most important gap between these two properties. Zoëtry is a family-friendly boutique all-inclusive in San Jose del Cabo with a heated pool, golf, yoga, tennis, spa, and swim-up bar, but its Pacific-coast beach is unsafe for swimming, making the pool the main aquatic draw. Secrets Macao counters with a genuinely swimmable Caribbean beach and a room score of 9.1 versus Zoëtry's 9.2 — essentially tied — though Zoëtry edges ahead on service (9.5 vs. 9.2) and overall rating (9.3 vs. 8.5). Secrets Macao is the beach holiday; Zoëtry is a refined Baja boutique retreat where land-based amenities and exceptional service carry the experience. Both sit at $$$$ pricing, but the experiential tradeoff is fundamental: if the ocean is central to your trip, Macao wins decisively.","whoShouldChooseA":"Adults-only couples or solo travelers who want a strong Caribbean beach holiday in the Dominican Republic, with genuinely swimmable turquoise water, well-rated rooms, and reliable service at a premium all-inclusive price point where the beach itself is the primary attraction.","whoShouldChooseB":"Families or couples drawn to the Baja California aesthetic who prioritize exceptional service, refined boutique atmosphere, spa, golf, and heated pool over beach swimming — and who accept that the Los Cabos Pacific coast is not a swimming beach in exchange for a polished, intimate San Jose del Cabo experience.","whenToVisit":"Secrets Macao is best November through April when Dominican Republic humidity drops and hurricane risk is minimal. Zoëtry Casa del Mar suits visits from November through May, avoiding Baja's humid summer season and the late-summer hurricane window that occasionally affects Los Cabos. Both properties offer their most comfortable conditions in the shared winter-to-spring window.","activities":"At Secrets Macao guests swim and snorkel off Macao beach, one of Punta Cana's least developed stretches of coastline. At Zoëtry Casa del Mar, land and pool activities dominate: guests access a heated pool with swim-up bar, a spa, yoga classes, tennis, and nearby golf courses. Both properties sit close to town centers — San Jose del Cabo's art district and Punta Cana's tourist corridor — offering dining and excursion options beyond the resort gates."}}
